WEBVTT

00:00:31.620 --> 00:00:34.340
The first book of Moses, called Genesis.

00:00:37.560 --> 00:00:40.960
In the beginning God created the heaven and the earth.

00:00:41.520 --> 00:00:47.820
And the earth was without form and void, and darkness was upon the face of the deep, and

00:00:47.820 --> 00:00:51.140
the Spirit of God moved upon the face of the waters.

00:00:52.040 --> 00:00:56.600
And God said, Let there be light, and there was light.

00:00:57.380 --> 00:01:03.380
And God saw the light, that it was good, and God divided the light from the darkness.

00:01:04.400 --> 00:01:10.860
And God called the light day, and the darkness He called night, and the evening and the morning

00:01:10.860 --> 00:01:12.200
were the first day.

00:01:13.740 --> 00:01:19.460
And God said, Let there be a firmament in the midst of the waters, and let it divide

00:01:19.460 --> 00:01:21.400
the waters from the waters.

00:01:22.180 --> 00:01:27.620
And God made the firmament, and divided the waters which were under the firmament from

00:01:27.620 --> 00:01:31.580
the waters which were above the firmament, and it was so.

00:01:32.360 --> 00:01:38.560
And God called the firmament heaven, and the evening and the morning were the second day.

00:01:40.200 --> 00:01:46.560
And God said, Let the waters under the heaven be gathered together unto one place, and let

00:01:46.560 --> 00:01:49.760
the dry land appear, and it was so.

00:01:50.660 --> 00:01:56.680
And God called the dry land earth, and the gathering together of the waters called He

00:01:56.680 --> 00:01:59.920
seas, and God saw that it was good.

00:02:01.000 --> 00:02:07.260
And God said, Let the earth bring forth grass, the herb yielding seed, and the fruit tree

00:02:07.260 --> 00:02:14.300
yielding fruit after His kind, whose seed is in itself upon the earth, and it was so.

00:02:15.160 --> 00:02:21.220
And the earth brought forth grass, and herb yielding seed after His kind, and the tree

00:02:21.220 --> 00:02:27.960
yielding fruit whose seed was in itself after His kind, and God saw that it was good.

00:02:28.780 --> 00:02:31.980
And the evening and the morning were the third day.

00:02:33.500 --> 00:02:39.660
And God said, Let there be lights in the firmament of the heaven to divide the day from the night,

00:02:40.060 --> 00:02:46.620
and let them be for signs, and for seasons, and for days, and years, and let them be for

00:02:46.620 --> 00:02:52.260
lights in the firmament of the heaven to give light upon the earth, and it was so.

00:02:53.300 --> 00:02:59.080
And God made two great lights, the greater light to rule the day, and the lesser light

00:02:59.080 --> 00:03:02.440
to rule the night, He made the stars also.

00:03:03.360 --> 00:03:09.100
And God set them in the firmament of the heaven to give light upon the earth, and to rule

00:03:09.100 --> 00:03:15.900
the day and over the night, and to divide the light from the darkness, and God saw that

00:03:15.900 --> 00:03:16.920
it was good.

00:03:17.580 --> 00:03:20.640
And the evening and the morning were the fourth day.

00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:29.100
And God said, Let the waters bring forth abundantly the moving creature that hath life, and fowl

00:03:29.100 --> 00:03:32.940
that may fly above the earth in the open firmament of heaven.

00:03:33.800 --> 00:03:39.900
And God created great whales, and every living creature that moveth, which the waters brought

00:03:39.900 --> 00:03:47.220
forth abundantly after their kind, and every winged fowl after his kind, and God saw that

00:03:47.220 --> 00:03:48.080
it was good.

00:03:49.240 --> 00:03:56.120
And God blessed them, saying, Be fruitful and multiply, and fill the waters in the seas,

00:03:56.640 --> 00:03:59.240
and let fowl multiply in the earth.

00:03:59.920 --> 00:04:03.160
And the evening and the morning were the fifth day.

00:04:04.800 --> 00:04:11.140
And God said, Let the earth bring forth the living creature after his kind, cattle and

00:04:11.140 --> 00:04:16.580
creeping thing, and beast of the earth after his kind, and it was so.

00:04:17.400 --> 00:04:23.460
And God made the beast of the earth after his kind, and cattle after their kind, and

00:04:23.460 --> 00:04:29.420
everything that creepeth upon the earth after his kind, and God saw that it was good.

00:04:30.920 --> 00:04:38.160
And God said, Let us make man in our image after our likeness, and let them have dominion

00:04:38.160 --> 00:04:44.020
over the fish of the sea, and over the fowl of the air, and over the cattle, and over

00:04:44.020 --> 00:04:48.740
all the earth, and over every creeping thing that creepeth upon the earth.

00:04:49.640 --> 00:04:56.740
So God created man in his own image, in the image of God created he him, male and female

00:04:56.740 --> 00:04:58.040
created he them.

00:04:59.000 --> 00:05:05.820
And God blessed them, and God said unto them, Be fruitful and multiply, and replenish the

00:05:05.820 --> 00:05:11.680
earth and subdue it, and have dominion over the fish of the sea, and over the fowl of

00:05:11.680 --> 00:05:16.040
the air, and over every living thing that moveth upon the earth.

00:05:16.890 --> 00:05:23.040
And God said, Behold, I have given you every herb bearing seed which is upon the face of

00:05:23.040 --> 00:05:28.360
all the earth, and every tree in the which is the fruit of a tree yielding seed.

00:05:28.740 --> 00:05:30.680
To you it shall be for meat.

00:05:31.440 --> 00:05:36.920
And to every beast of the earth, and to every fowl of the air, and to everything that creepeth

00:05:36.920 --> 00:05:42.280
upon the earth wherein there is life, I have given every green herb for meat.

00:05:42.480 --> 00:05:43.860
And it was so.

00:05:44.580 --> 00:05:51.240
And God saw everything that he had made, and behold, it was very good, and the evening

00:05:51.240 --> 00:05:53.720
and the morning were the sixth day.

00:05:56.760 --> 00:06:01.480
Thus the heavens and the earth were finished, and all the host of them.

00:06:02.120 --> 00:06:07.820
And on the seventh day God ended his work which he had made, and he rested on the seventh

00:06:07.820 --> 00:06:10.420
day from all his work which he had made.

00:06:11.060 --> 00:06:17.100
And God blessed the seventh day and sanctified it, because that in it he had rested from

00:06:17.100 --> 00:06:20.400
all his work which God created and made.

00:06:21.800 --> 00:06:27.240
These are the generations of the heavens and of the earth when they were created, in the

00:06:27.240 --> 00:06:32.800
day that the Lord God made the earth and the heavens, and every plant of the field before

00:06:32.800 --> 00:06:37.020
it was in the earth, and every herb of the field before it grew.

00:06:37.440 --> 00:06:43.000
For the Lord God had not caused it to rain upon the earth, and there was not a man to

00:06:43.000 --> 00:06:43.860
till the ground.

00:06:44.720 --> 00:06:49.460
But there went up a mist from the earth and watered the whole face of the ground.

00:06:50.560 --> 00:06:56.000
And the Lord God formed man of the dust of the ground, and breathed into his nostrils

00:06:56.000 --> 00:07:00.140
the breath of life, and man became a living soul.

00:07:01.040 --> 00:07:07.500
And the Lord God planted a garden eastward in Eden, and there he put the man whom he

00:07:07.500 --> 00:07:08.240
had formed.

00:07:08.920 --> 00:07:14.320
And out of the ground made the Lord God to grow every tree that is pleasant to the sight

00:07:14.320 --> 00:07:20.940
and good for food, the tree of life also in the midst of the garden, and the tree of knowledge

00:07:20.940 --> 00:07:22.240
of good and evil.

00:07:23.540 --> 00:07:29.200
And a river went out of Eden to water the garden, and from thence it was parted and

00:07:29.200 --> 00:07:30.960
became into four heads.

00:07:31.780 --> 00:07:37.820
The name of the first is Pison, that is it which compasseth the whole land of Havilla,

00:07:38.240 --> 00:07:44.240
where there is gold, and the gold of that land is good, there is Bedelium and the Onyx

00:07:44.240 --> 00:07:44.700
Stone.

00:07:45.620 --> 00:07:51.200
And the name of the second river is Gihon, the same is it that compasseth the whole land

00:07:51.200 --> 00:07:52.140
of Ethiopia.

00:07:53.260 --> 00:07:58.900
And the name of the third river is Hittical, that is it which goeth toward the east of

00:07:58.900 --> 00:08:02.260
Syria, and the fourth river is Euphrates.

00:08:03.520 --> 00:08:09.080
And the Lord God took the man and put him into the garden of Eden to dress it and to

00:08:09.080 --> 00:08:09.640
keep it.

00:08:10.280 --> 00:08:16.420
And the Lord God commanded the man, saying, Of every tree of the garden thou mayest freely

00:08:16.420 --> 00:08:23.280
eat, but of the tree of the knowledge of good and evil thou shalt not eat of it, for in

00:08:23.280 --> 00:08:26.920
the day that thou eatest thereof thou shalt surely die.

00:08:28.080 --> 00:08:34.260
And the Lord God said, It is not good that the man should be alone, I will make him and

00:08:34.260 --> 00:08:35.680
help meet for him.

00:08:36.480 --> 00:08:42.100
And out of the ground the Lord God formed every beast of the field and every fowl of

00:08:42.100 --> 00:08:47.860
the air, and brought them unto Adam to see what he would call them, and whatsoever Adam

00:08:47.860 --> 00:08:51.760
called every living creature that was the name thereof.

00:08:52.660 --> 00:08:58.540
And Adam gave names to all cattle and to the fowl of the air and to every beast of the

00:08:58.540 --> 00:09:02.920
field, but for Adam there was not found and help meet for him.

00:09:03.920 --> 00:09:10.200
And the Lord God caused a deep sleep to fall upon Adam, and he slept, and he took one of

00:09:10.200 --> 00:09:17.100
his ribs and closed up the flesh instead thereof, and the rib which the Lord God had taken from

00:09:17.100 --> 00:09:21.180
the man, made he a woman, and brought her unto the man.

00:09:22.240 --> 00:09:28.820
And Adam said, This is now bone of my bones, and flesh of my flesh, she shall be called

00:09:28.820 --> 00:09:31.860
woman because she was taken out of man.

00:09:33.080 --> 00:09:38.420
Therefore shall a man leave his father and his mother, and shall cleave unto his wife,

00:09:38.720 --> 00:09:40.680
and they shall be one flesh.

00:09:41.440 --> 00:09:46.320
And they were both naked, the man and his wife, and were not ashamed.

00:09:50.360 --> 00:09:55.920
Now the serpent was more subtle than any beast of the field which the Lord God had made,

00:09:56.280 --> 00:10:02.900
and he said unto the woman, Yea, hath God said, He shall not eat of every tree of the

00:10:02.900 --> 00:10:03.300
garden?

00:10:04.320 --> 00:10:09.600
And the woman said unto the serpent, We may eat of the fruit of the trees of the garden,

00:10:09.940 --> 00:10:15.520
but of the fruit of the tree which is in the midst of the garden, God hath said, He shall

00:10:15.520 --> 00:10:19.440
not eat of it, neither shall ye touch it, lest ye die.

00:10:20.220 --> 00:10:24.600
And the serpent said unto the woman, He shall not surely die.

00:10:25.120 --> 00:10:31.740
For God doth know that in the day ye eat thereof, then your eyes shall be opened, and ye shall

00:10:31.740 --> 00:10:35.180
be as God's, knowing good and evil.

00:10:36.720 --> 00:10:42.140
And when the woman saw that the tree was good for food, and that it was pleasant to the

00:10:42.140 --> 00:10:48.560
eyes, and a tree to be desired to make one wise, she took of the fruit thereof, and did

00:10:48.560 --> 00:10:53.560
eat, and gave also unto her husband with her, and he did eat.

00:10:54.440 --> 00:11:00.100
And the eyes of them both were opened, and they knew that they were naked, and they sewed

00:11:00.100 --> 00:11:03.140
fig-leaves together, and made themselves aprons.

00:11:03.940 --> 00:11:10.240
And they heard the voice of the Lord God walking in the garden in the cool of the day, and

00:11:10.240 --> 00:11:15.380
Adam and his wife hid themselves from the presence of the Lord God amongst the trees

00:11:15.380 --> 00:11:16.180
of the garden.

00:11:17.140 --> 00:11:22.140
And the Lord God called unto Adam, and said unto him, Where art thou?

00:11:22.840 --> 00:11:29.440
And he said, I heard thy voice in the garden, and I was afraid because I was naked, and

00:11:29.440 --> 00:11:30.460
I hid myself.

00:11:31.260 --> 00:11:34.780
And he said, Who told thee that thou was naked?

00:11:35.520 --> 00:11:40.540
Hast thou eaten of the tree whereof I commanded thee that thou shouldst not eat?

00:11:41.260 --> 00:11:47.480
And the man said, The woman whom thou gavest to be with me, she gave me of the tree, and

00:11:47.480 --> 00:11:48.380
I did eat.

00:11:49.240 --> 00:11:53.680
And the Lord God said unto the woman, What is this that thou hast done?

00:11:54.120 --> 00:11:58.300
And the woman said, The serpent beguiled me, and I did eat.

00:11:58.900 --> 00:12:04.940
And the Lord God said unto the serpent, Because thou hast done this, thou art cursed above

00:12:04.940 --> 00:12:08.280
all cattle, and above every beast of the field.

00:12:08.820 --> 00:12:14.380
Upon thy belly shalt thou go, and dust shalt thou eat all the days of thy life.

00:12:14.900 --> 00:12:20.680
And I will put enmity between thee and the woman, and between thy seed and her seed.

00:12:21.200 --> 00:12:24.860
It shall bruise thy head, and thou shalt bruise his heel.

00:12:25.880 --> 00:12:33.060
Unto the woman he said, I will greatly multiply thy sorrow and thy conception, in sorrow thou

00:12:33.060 --> 00:12:39.200
shalt bring forth children, and thy desire shall be to thy husband, and he shall rule

00:12:39.200 --> 00:12:40.020
over thee.

00:12:41.180 --> 00:12:47.400
And unto Adam he said, Because thou hast hearkened unto the voice of thy wife, and hast eaten

00:12:47.400 --> 00:12:54.020
of the tree of which I commanded thee, saying, Thou shalt not eat of it, cursed is the ground

00:12:54.020 --> 00:12:59.000
for thy sake, in sorrow shalt thou eat of it all the days of thy life.

00:12:59.680 --> 00:13:05.480
Thorns also and thistles shall it bring forth to thee, and thou shalt eat the herb of the

00:13:05.480 --> 00:13:05.880
field.

00:13:06.580 --> 00:13:12.520
In the sweat of thy face shalt thou eat bread till thou return unto the ground, for out

00:13:12.520 --> 00:13:18.680
of it wast thou taken, for dust thou art, and unto dust shalt thou return.

00:13:19.960 --> 00:13:25.560
And Adam called his wife's name Eve, because she was the mother of all living.

00:13:27.020 --> 00:13:33.200
Unto Adam also and to his wife did the Lord God make coats of skins and clothe them.

00:13:34.280 --> 00:13:41.640
And the Lord God said, Behold the man is become as one of us to know good and evil, and now

00:13:41.640 --> 00:13:47.740
lest he put forth his hand and take also of the tree of life and eat and live for ever.

00:13:48.680 --> 00:13:53.920
Therefore the Lord God sent him forth from the Garden of Eden to till the ground from

00:13:53.920 --> 00:13:54.940
whence he was taken.

00:13:55.760 --> 00:14:01.920
So he drove out the man, and he placed at the east of the Garden of Eden cherubims and

00:14:01.920 --> 00:14:07.520
a flaming sword which turned every way to keep the way of the tree of life.

00:14:10.300 --> 00:14:17.340
And Adam knew Eve his wife, and she conceived and bare Cain, and said, I have gotten a man

00:14:17.340 --> 00:14:18.220
from the Lord.

00:14:18.980 --> 00:14:21.640
And she again bare his brother Abel.

00:14:21.920 --> 00:14:26.280
And Abel was a keeper of sheep, but Cain was a tiller of the ground.

00:14:27.060 --> 00:14:32.540
And in process of time it came to pass that Cain brought of the fruit of the ground an

00:14:32.540 --> 00:14:34.040
offering unto the Lord.

00:14:34.720 --> 00:14:40.420
And Abel he also brought of the firstlings of his flock, and of the fat thereof.

00:14:41.080 --> 00:14:46.740
And the Lord had respect unto Abel and to his offering, but unto Cain and to his offering

00:14:46.740 --> 00:14:52.220
he had not respect, and Cain was very wroth, and his countenance fell.

00:14:53.220 --> 00:14:58.780
And the Lord said unto Cain, Why art thou wroth, and why is thy countenance fallen?

00:14:59.360 --> 00:15:06.660
If thou doest well, shalt thou not be accepted, and if thou doest not well, sin lieth at the

00:15:06.660 --> 00:15:12.160
door, and unto thee shall be his desire, and thou shalt rule over him.

00:15:13.060 --> 00:15:18.640
And Cain talked with Abel his brother, and it came to pass when they were in the field

00:15:18.640 --> 00:15:23.360
that Cain rose up against Abel his brother and slew him.

00:15:24.160 --> 00:15:28.500
And the Lord said unto Cain, Where is Abel thy brother?

00:15:28.900 --> 00:15:32.860
And he said, I know not, am I my brother's keeper?

00:15:33.740 --> 00:15:36.340
And he said, What hast thou done?

00:15:36.800 --> 00:15:40.600
The voice of thy brother's blood crieth unto me from the ground.

00:15:41.700 --> 00:15:47.200
And now art thou cursed from the earth which hath opened her mouth to receive thy brother's

00:15:47.200 --> 00:15:48.740
blood from thy hand.

00:15:48.740 --> 00:15:55.120
When thou tillest the ground, it shall not henceforth yield unto thee her strength, a

00:15:55.120 --> 00:15:58.460
fugitive and a vagabond shalt thou be in the earth.

00:15:59.340 --> 00:16:03.920
And Cain said unto the Lord, My punishment is greater than I can bear.

00:16:04.780 --> 00:16:10.360
Behold, thou hast driven me out this day from the face of the earth, and from thy face shall

00:16:10.360 --> 00:16:16.080
I be hid, and I shall be a fugitive and a vagabond in the earth, and it shall come to

00:16:16.080 --> 00:16:19.620
pass that every one that findeth me shall slay me.

00:16:20.520 --> 00:16:26.920
And the Lord said unto him, Therefore whosoever slayeth Cain, vengeance shall be taken on

00:16:26.920 --> 00:16:28.360
him sevenfold.

00:16:29.100 --> 00:16:34.500
And the Lord set a mark upon Cain, lest any finding him should kill him.

00:16:35.700 --> 00:16:41.380
And Cain went out from the presence of the Lord and dwelt in the land of Nod on the east

00:16:41.380 --> 00:16:41.940
of Eden.

00:16:42.870 --> 00:16:49.480
And Cain knew his wife, and she conceived, and bare Enoch, and he builded a city, and

00:16:49.480 --> 00:16:53.240
called the name of the city after the name of his son, Enoch.

00:16:54.420 --> 00:17:02.520
And unto Enoch was born Ired, and Ired begat Mehujael, and Mehujael begat Methusael, and

00:17:02.520 --> 00:17:04.560
Methusael begat Lamech.

00:17:05.380 --> 00:17:11.400
And Lamech took unto him two wives, the name of the one was Ada, and the name of the other

00:17:11.400 --> 00:17:11.960
Zilla.

00:17:12.760 --> 00:17:19.120
And Ada bare Jabal, he was the father of such as dwell in tents, and of such as have cattle.

00:17:19.920 --> 00:17:25.880
And his brother's name was Jubal, he was the father of all such as handle the harp and

00:17:25.880 --> 00:17:26.220
organ.

00:17:27.300 --> 00:17:34.420
And Zilla she also bare Tubalcain, an instructor of every artificer in brass and iron, and

00:17:34.420 --> 00:17:37.000
the sister of Tubalcain was Nehema.

00:17:37.740 --> 00:17:44.640
And Lamech said unto his wives Ada and Zilla, Hear my voice, ye wives of Lamech, hearken

00:17:44.640 --> 00:17:50.700
unto my speech, for I have slain a man to my wounding, and a young man to my hurt.

00:17:51.460 --> 00:17:57.040
If Cain shall be avenged sevenfold, truly Lamech, seventy and sevenfold.

00:17:58.280 --> 00:18:03.940
And Adam knew his wife again, and she bare a son, and called his name Seth.

00:18:04.360 --> 00:18:11.060
For God, said she, hath appointed me another seed instead of Abel, whom Cain slew.

00:18:12.160 --> 00:18:17.440
And to Seth, to him also, there was born a son, and he called his name Enos.

00:18:17.960 --> 00:18:21.460
Then began men to call upon the name of the Lord.

00:18:24.000 --> 00:18:27.480
This is the book of the generations of Adam.

00:18:28.000 --> 00:18:34.900
In the day that God created man, in the likeness of God made he him, male and female created

00:18:34.900 --> 00:18:40.620
he them, and blessed them, and called their name Adam, in the day when they were created.

00:18:41.660 --> 00:18:47.580
And Adam lived an hundred and thirty years, and begat a son in his own likeness after

00:18:47.580 --> 00:18:50.280
his image, and called his name Seth.

00:18:51.000 --> 00:18:56.720
And the days of Adam, after he had begotten Seth, were eight hundred years, and he begat

00:18:56.720 --> 00:19:02.700
sons and daughters, and all the days that Adam lived were nine hundred and thirty years,

00:19:02.840 --> 00:19:03.840
and he died.

00:19:04.760 --> 00:19:11.120
And Seth lived an hundred and five years, and begat Enos, and Seth lived after he begat

00:19:11.120 --> 00:19:17.540
Enos eight hundred and seven years, and begat sons and daughters, and all the days of Seth

00:19:17.540 --> 00:19:20.980
were nine hundred and twelve years, and he died.

00:19:21.700 --> 00:19:29.320
And Enos lived ninety years, and begat Kainan, and Enos lived after he begat Kainan eight

00:19:29.320 --> 00:19:35.900
hundred and fifteen years, and begat sons and daughters, and all the days of Enos were

00:19:35.900 --> 00:19:38.780
nine hundred and five years, and he died.

00:19:39.980 --> 00:19:46.400
And Kainan lived seventy years, and begat Mahalalel, and Kainan lived after he begat

00:19:46.400 --> 00:19:52.760
Mahalalel eight hundred and forty years, and begat sons and daughters, and all the days

00:19:52.760 --> 00:19:56.880
of Kainan were nine hundred and ten years, and he died.

00:19:58.180 --> 00:20:05.520
And Mahalalel lived sixty and five years, and begat Jared, and Mahalalel lived after

00:20:05.520 --> 00:20:12.090
he begat Jared eight hundred and thirty years, and begat sons and daughters, and all the

00:20:12.090 --> 00:20:16.910
days of Mahalalel were eight hundred and ninety and five years, and he died.

00:20:17.950 --> 00:20:24.270
And Jared lived a hundred and sixty and two years, and he begat Enoch, and Jared lived

00:20:24.270 --> 00:20:30.370
after he begat Enoch eight hundred years, and begat sons and daughters, and all the

00:20:30.370 --> 00:20:34.790
days of Jared were nine hundred and sixty and two years, and he died.

00:20:35.670 --> 00:20:42.290
And Enoch lived sixty and five years, and begat Methuselah, and Enoch walked with God

00:20:42.290 --> 00:20:48.990
after he begat Methuselah three hundred years, and begat sons and daughters, and all the

00:20:48.990 --> 00:20:55.030
days of Enoch were three hundred sixty and five years, and Enoch walked with God, and

00:20:55.030 --> 00:20:57.490
he was not, for God took him.

00:20:58.070 --> 00:21:04.570
And Methuselah lived an hundred eighty and seven years, and begat Lamech, and Methuselah

00:21:04.570 --> 00:21:11.010
lived after he begat Lamech seven hundred eighty and two years, and begat sons and daughters,

00:21:11.530 --> 00:21:17.030
and all the days of Methuselah were nine hundred sixty and nine years, and he died.

00:21:18.090 --> 00:21:23.550
And Lamech lived an hundred eighty and two years, and begat his son, and he called his

00:21:23.550 --> 00:21:29.930
name Noah, saying, This same shall comfort us concerning our work and toil of our hands,

00:21:30.370 --> 00:21:32.910
because of the ground which the Lord hath cursed.

00:21:33.790 --> 00:21:39.770
And Lamech lived after he begat Noah five hundred ninety and five years, and begat sons

00:21:39.770 --> 00:21:45.150
and daughters, and all the days of Lamech were seven hundred seventy and seven years,

00:21:45.370 --> 00:21:46.330
and he died.

00:21:47.050 --> 00:21:53.590
And Noah was five hundred years old, and Noah begat Shem, Ham, and Japheth.

00:21:54.890 --> 00:21:59.630
And it came to pass, when men began to multiply

00:21:59.630 --> 00:22:05.030
on the face of the earth, and daughters were born unto them, that the sons of God saw the

00:22:05.030 --> 00:22:10.610
daughters of men, that they were fair, and they took them wives of all which they chose.

00:22:11.250 --> 00:22:18.330
And the Lord said, My spirit shall not always strive with man, for that he also is flesh,

00:22:18.830 --> 00:22:21.950
yet his days shall be an hundred and twenty years.

00:22:23.170 --> 00:22:28.650
There were giants in the earth in those days, and also after that, when the sons of God

00:22:28.650 --> 00:22:34.430
came in unto the daughters of men, and they bare children to them, the same became mighty

00:22:34.430 --> 00:22:37.490
men which were of old, men of renown.

00:22:38.330 --> 00:22:43.970
And God saw that the wickedness of man was great in the earth, and that every imagination

00:22:43.970 --> 00:22:47.670
of the thoughts of his heart was only evil continually.

00:22:48.690 --> 00:22:53.730
And it repented the Lord that he had made man on the earth, and it grieved him at his

00:22:53.730 --> 00:22:54.150
heart.

00:22:54.950 --> 00:23:00.430
And the Lord said, I will destroy man whom I have created from the face of the earth,

00:23:00.790 --> 00:23:06.490
both man and beast, and the creeping thing, and the fowls of the air, for it repenteth

00:23:06.490 --> 00:23:08.250
me that I have made them.

00:23:08.890 --> 00:23:11.910
But Noah found grace in the eyes of the Lord.

00:23:13.880 --> 00:23:15.770
These are the generations of Noah.

00:23:16.270 --> 00:23:21.710
Noah was a just man, and perfect in his generations, and Noah walked with God.

00:23:22.430 --> 00:23:26.750
And Noah begat three sons, Shem, Ham, and Japeth.

00:23:27.750 --> 00:23:32.850
The earth also was corrupt before God, and the earth was filled with violence.

00:23:33.430 --> 00:23:38.990
And God looked upon the earth, and behold, it was corrupt, for all flesh had corrupted

00:23:38.990 --> 00:23:40.750
his way upon the earth.

00:23:41.750 --> 00:23:47.930
And God said unto Noah, The end of all flesh is come before me, for the earth is filled

00:23:47.930 --> 00:23:52.730
with violence through them, and behold, I will destroy them with the earth.

00:23:53.830 --> 00:23:59.750
Make thee an ark of gopher wood, rooms shalt thou make in the ark, and shalt pitch it within

00:23:59.750 --> 00:24:01.370
and without with pitch.

00:24:02.030 --> 00:24:05.230
And this is the fashion which thou shalt make it of.

00:24:05.650 --> 00:24:10.710
The length of the ark shall be three hundred cubits, the breadth of it fifty cubits, and

00:24:10.710 --> 00:24:12.730
the height of it thirty cubits.

00:24:13.690 --> 00:24:19.770
A window shalt thou make to the ark, and in a cubit shalt thou finish it above, and the

00:24:19.770 --> 00:24:25.490
door of the ark shalt thou set in the side thereof, with lower, second, and third stories

00:24:25.490 --> 00:24:26.870
shalt thou make it.

00:24:27.670 --> 00:24:34.290
And behold, I, even I, do bring a flood of waters upon the earth to destroy all flesh

00:24:34.290 --> 00:24:40.190
wherein is the breath of life from under heaven, and every thing that is in the earth shall

00:24:40.190 --> 00:24:40.730
die.

00:24:41.590 --> 00:24:47.510
But with thee will I establish my covenant, and thou shalt come into the ark thou and

00:24:47.510 --> 00:24:51.590
thy sons and thy wife and thy sons' wives with thee.

00:24:52.170 --> 00:24:57.990
And of every living thing of all flesh, two of every sort shalt thou bring into the ark

00:24:57.990 --> 00:25:02.210
to keep them alive with thee, they shall be male and female.

00:25:03.170 --> 00:25:08.990
Of fowls after their kind, and of cattle after their kind, of every creeping thing of the

00:25:08.990 --> 00:25:14.810
earth after his kind, two of every sort shall come unto thee to keep them alive.

00:25:15.370 --> 00:25:22.230
And take thou unto thee of all food that is eaten, and thou shalt gather it to thee, and

00:25:22.230 --> 00:25:25.130
it shall be for food for thee and for them.

00:25:26.170 --> 00:25:31.810
Thus did Noah, according to all that God commanded him, so did he.

00:26:07.210 --> 00:26:14.410
And the Lord said unto Noah, Come thou and all thy house into the ark, for thee have

00:26:14.410 --> 00:26:17.690
I seen righteous before me in this generation.

00:26:19.210 --> 00:26:28.790
Of every clean beast thou shalt take to thee by sevens, the male and his female, and of

00:26:28.790 --> 00:26:37.190
of fowls also of the air by sevens, the male and the female, to keep seed alive upon the

00:26:37.190 --> 00:26:38.710
face of all the earth.

00:26:39.470 --> 00:26:45.590
For yet seven days, and I will cause it to rain upon the earth forty days and forty nights,

00:26:46.090 --> 00:26:51.630
and every living substance that I have made will I destroy from off the face of the earth.

00:26:52.570 --> 00:26:56.590
And Noah did according unto all that the Lord commanded him.

00:26:57.420 --> 00:27:02.250
And Noah was six hundred years old when the flood of waters was upon the earth.

00:27:03.590 --> 00:27:09.910
And Noah went in, and his sons, and his wife, and his sons' wives with him, into the ark,

00:27:10.190 --> 00:27:12.270
because of the waters of the flood.

00:27:13.690 --> 00:27:19.370
Of clean beasts, and of beasts that are not clean, and of fowls, and of every thing that

00:27:19.370 --> 00:27:25.790
creepeth upon the earth, there went in two and two unto Noah into the ark, the male and

00:27:25.790 --> 00:27:28.650
the female, as God had commanded Noah.

00:27:30.450 --> 00:27:36.010
And it came to pass after seven days that the waters of the flood were upon the earth.

00:27:37.370 --> 00:27:42.630
In the six hundredth year of Noah's life, in the second month, the seventeenth day of

00:27:42.630 --> 00:27:48.630
the month, the same day were all the fountains of the great deep broken up, and the windows

00:27:48.630 --> 00:27:49.990
of heaven were opened.

00:27:50.790 --> 00:27:54.990
And the rain was upon the earth forty days and forty nights.

00:27:56.330 --> 00:28:03.210
In the selfsame day entered Noah, and Shem, and Ham, and Japeth, the sons of Noah, and

00:28:03.210 --> 00:28:09.870
Noah's wife, and the three wives of his sons with them, into the ark, they and every beast

00:28:09.870 --> 00:28:15.830
after his kind, and all the cattle after their kind, and every creeping thing that creepeth

00:28:15.830 --> 00:28:22.990
upon the earth after his kind, and every fowl after his kind, every bird of every sort.

00:28:23.810 --> 00:28:30.330
And they went in unto Noah into the ark two and two of all flesh wherein is the breath

00:28:30.330 --> 00:28:31.150
of life.

00:28:31.750 --> 00:28:38.350
And they that went in, went in male and female of all flesh, as God had commanded him, and

00:28:38.350 --> 00:28:39.750
the Lord shut him in.

00:28:40.590 --> 00:28:46.810
And the flood was forty days upon the earth, and the waters increased and bare up the ark,

00:28:47.170 --> 00:28:49.430
and it was lift up above the earth.

00:28:50.250 --> 00:28:56.010
And the waters prevailed and were increased greatly upon the earth, and the ark went upon

00:28:56.010 --> 00:28:57.350
the face of the waters.

00:28:58.130 --> 00:29:03.350
And the waters prevailed exceedingly upon the earth, and all the high hills that were

00:29:03.350 --> 00:29:05.450
under the whole heaven were covered.

00:29:06.670 --> 00:29:11.550
Fifteen cubits upward did the waters prevail, and the mountains were covered.

00:29:12.450 --> 00:29:19.130
And all flesh died that moved upon the earth, both of fowl and of cattle and of beast and

00:29:19.130 --> 00:29:25.630
of every creeping thing that creepeth upon the earth and every man, all in whose nostrils

00:29:25.630 --> 00:29:30.330
was the breath of life, of all that was in the dry land, died.

00:29:31.230 --> 00:29:37.050
And every living substance was destroyed which was upon the face of the ground, both man

00:29:37.050 --> 00:29:42.530
and cattle and the creeping things and the fowl of the heaven, and they were destroyed

00:29:42.530 --> 00:29:48.470
from the earth, and Noah only remained alive and they that were with him in the ark.

00:29:49.510 --> 00:29:53.730
And the waters prevailed upon the earth and hundred and fifty days.

00:29:56.970 --> 00:30:02.650
And God remembered Noah and every living thing and all the cattle that was with him in the

00:30:02.650 --> 00:30:08.110
ark, and God made a wind to pass over the earth and the waters assuaged.

00:30:08.810 --> 00:30:14.370
The fountains also of the deep and the windows of heaven were stopped and the rain from heaven

00:30:14.370 --> 00:30:20.950
was restrained, and the waters returned from off the earth continually, and after the end

00:30:20.950 --> 00:30:24.430
of the hundred and fifty days the waters were abated.

00:30:25.710 --> 00:30:30.790
And the ark rested in the seventh month on the seventeenth day of the month upon the

00:30:30.790 --> 00:30:32.110
mountains of Ararat.

00:30:33.130 --> 00:30:38.610
And the waters decreased continually until the tenth month, in the tenth month on the

00:30:38.610 --> 00:30:42.090
first day of the month were the tops of the mountains seen.

00:30:42.890 --> 00:30:48.630
And it came to pass at the end of forty days that Noah opened the window of the ark which

00:30:48.630 --> 00:30:55.270
he had made, and he sent forth a raven which went forth to and fro until the waters were

00:30:55.270 --> 00:30:57.090
dried up from off the earth.

00:30:58.290 --> 00:31:04.250
Also he sent forth a dove from him to see if the waters were abated from off the face

00:31:04.250 --> 00:31:05.030
of the ground.

00:31:05.630 --> 00:31:11.050
But the dove found no rest for the sole of her foot, and she returned under him into

00:31:11.050 --> 00:31:14.850
the ark, for the waters were on the face of the whole earth.

00:31:15.290 --> 00:31:21.010
Then he put forth his hand and took her and pulled her in unto him into the ark.

00:31:22.190 --> 00:31:28.830
And he stayed yet other seven days, and again he sent forth the dove out of the ark, and

00:31:28.830 --> 00:31:34.710
the dove came into him in the evening, and lo, in her mouth was an olive-leaf plucked

00:31:34.710 --> 00:31:39.390
off, so Noah knew that the waters were abated from off the earth.

00:31:40.070 --> 00:31:46.550
And he stayed yet other seven days, and sent forth the dove, which returned not again unto

00:31:46.550 --> 00:31:47.830
him any more.

00:31:49.090 --> 00:31:54.530
And it came to pass in the six hundredth and first year, in the first month, the first

00:31:54.530 --> 00:32:00.450
day of the month, the waters were dried up from off the earth, and Noah removed the covering

00:32:00.450 --> 00:32:05.270
of the ark, and looked, and behold, the face of the ground was dry.

00:32:06.110 --> 00:32:11.090
And in the second month, on the seventh and twentieth day of the month, was the earth

00:32:11.090 --> 00:32:11.610
dried.

00:32:13.030 --> 00:32:19.710
And God spake unto Noah, saying, Go forth of the ark thou and thy wife and thy sons

00:32:19.710 --> 00:32:21.890
and thy sons' wives with thee.

00:32:22.710 --> 00:32:28.810
Bring forth with thee every living thing that is with thee of all flesh, both of fowl and

00:32:28.810 --> 00:32:34.230
of cattle, and of every creeping thing that creepeth upon the earth, that they may breed

00:32:34.230 --> 00:32:39.230
abundantly in the earth and be fruitful and multiply upon the earth.

00:32:40.430 --> 00:32:45.510
And Noah went forth and his sons and his wife and his sons' wives with him.

00:32:46.290 --> 00:32:52.190
Every beast, every creeping thing, and every fowl, and whatsoever creepeth upon the earth

00:32:52.190 --> 00:32:55.530
after their kinds, went forth out of the ark.

00:32:56.730 --> 00:33:02.770
And Noah builded an altar unto the Lord, and took of every clean beast and of every clean

00:33:02.770 --> 00:33:06.090
fowl, and offered burnt offerings on the altar.

00:33:06.950 --> 00:33:13.110
And the Lord smelled a sweet savor, and the Lord said in his heart, I will not again curse

00:33:13.110 --> 00:33:19.230
the ground any more for man's sake, for the imagination of man's heart is evil from his

00:33:19.230 --> 00:33:25.170
youth, neither will I again smite any more every thing living as I have done.

00:33:25.870 --> 00:33:32.750
While the earth remaineth seed-time and harvest and cold and heat and summer and winter and

00:33:32.750 --> 00:33:35.610
day and night shall not cease.

00:33:40.210 --> 00:33:46.810
And God blessed Noah and his sons and said unto them, Be fruitful and multiply and replenish

00:33:46.810 --> 00:33:52.630
the earth, and the fear of you and the dread of you shall be upon every beast of the earth,

00:33:52.830 --> 00:33:58.770
and upon every fowl of the air, upon all that moveth upon the earth, and upon all the fishes

00:33:58.770 --> 00:34:02.210
of the sea, into your hand are they delivered.

00:34:03.350 --> 00:34:08.850
Every moving thing that liveth shall be meat for you, even as the green herb have I given

00:34:08.850 --> 00:34:10.150
you all things.

00:34:10.890 --> 00:34:16.210
But flesh with the life thereof, which is the blood thereof, shall ye not eat.

00:34:16.770 --> 00:34:22.390
And surely your blood of your lives will I require, at the hand of every beast will I

00:34:22.390 --> 00:34:28.170
require it, and at the hand of man, at the hand of every man's brother will I require

00:34:28.170 --> 00:34:29.470
the life of man.

00:34:30.370 --> 00:34:36.770
Whoso shedeth man's blood, by man shall his blood be shed, for in the image of God made

00:34:36.770 --> 00:34:37.670
he man.

00:34:38.350 --> 00:34:45.270
And you, be ye fruitful and multiply, bring forth abundantly in the earth, and multiply

00:34:45.270 --> 00:34:46.030
therein.

00:34:47.210 --> 00:34:54.470
And God spake unto Noah and to his sons with him, saying, And I, behold, I establish my

00:34:54.470 --> 00:34:59.910
covenant with you, and with your seed after you, and with every living creature that is

00:34:59.910 --> 00:35:05.770
with you, of the fowl, of the cattle, and of every beast of the earth with you, from

00:35:05.770 --> 00:35:09.350
all that go out of the ark to every beast of the earth.

00:35:09.830 --> 00:35:15.730
And I will establish my covenant with you, neither shall all flesh be cut off any more

00:35:15.730 --> 00:35:21.550
by the waters of a flood, neither shall there be any more of flood to destroy the earth.

00:35:22.610 --> 00:35:28.990
And God said, This is the token of the covenant which I make between me and you, and every

00:35:28.990 --> 00:35:32.750
living creature that is with you, for perpetual generations.

00:35:33.230 --> 00:35:39.390
I do set my bow in the cloud, and it shall be for a token of a covenant between me and

00:35:39.390 --> 00:35:40.130
the earth.

00:35:40.750 --> 00:35:45.670
And it shall come to pass, when I bring a cloud over the earth, that the bow shall be

00:35:45.670 --> 00:35:52.690
cloud, and I will remember my covenant which is between me and you and every living creature

00:35:52.690 --> 00:35:58.930
of all flesh, and the waters shall no more become a flood to destroy all flesh.

00:35:59.750 --> 00:36:05.590
And the bow shall be in the cloud, and I will look upon it, that I may remember the everlasting

00:36:05.590 --> 00:36:11.330
covenant between God and every living creature of all flesh that is upon the earth.

00:36:12.190 --> 00:36:18.210
And God said unto Noah, This is the token of the covenant which I have established between

00:36:18.210 --> 00:36:21.150
me and all flesh that is upon the earth.

00:36:22.950 --> 00:36:29.070
And the sons of Noah that went forth of the ark were Shem and Ham and Japheth, and Ham

00:36:29.070 --> 00:36:30.630
is the father of Canaan.

00:36:31.730 --> 00:36:36.950
These were the three sons of Noah, and of them was the whole earth overspread.

00:36:37.610 --> 00:36:43.730
And Noah began to be an husbandman, and he planted a vineyard, and he drank of the wine,

00:36:43.850 --> 00:36:47.510
and was drunken, and he was uncovered within his tent.

00:36:48.230 --> 00:36:54.790
And Ham, the father of Canaan, saw the nakedness of his father, and told his two brethren without.

00:36:55.610 --> 00:37:01.550
And Shem and Japheth took a garment, and laid it upon both their shoulders, and went backward,

00:37:01.550 --> 00:37:07.030
and covered the nakedness of their father, and their faces were backward, and they saw

00:37:07.030 --> 00:37:09.090
not their father's nakedness.

00:37:10.270 --> 00:37:15.550
And Noah awoke from his wine, and knew what his younger son had done unto him.

00:37:16.030 --> 00:37:22.250
And he said, Cursed be Canaan, a servant of servants shall he be unto his brethren.

00:37:23.170 --> 00:37:28.650
And he said, Blessed be the Lord God of Shem, and Canaan shall be his servant.

00:37:29.450 --> 00:37:35.330
God shall enlarge Japheth, and he shall dwell in the tents of Shem, and Canaan shall be

00:37:35.330 --> 00:37:36.150
his servant.

00:37:37.710 --> 00:37:41.750
And Noah lived after the flood three hundred and fifty years.

00:37:42.390 --> 00:37:47.290
And all the days of Noah were nine hundred and fifty years, and he died.

00:37:50.390 --> 00:37:57.010
Now these are the generations of the sons of Noah, Shem, Ham, and Japheth, and unto

00:37:57.010 --> 00:37:59.590
them were sons born after the flood.

00:38:00.770 --> 00:38:08.150
The sons of Japheth, Gomer, and Magog, and Medai, and Javan, and Tubal, and Meshach,

00:38:08.390 --> 00:38:09.150
and Tyrus.

00:38:10.030 --> 00:38:14.790
And the sons of Gomer, Ashkenaz, and Riphoth, and Togarmah.

00:38:15.430 --> 00:38:21.110
And the sons of Javan, Elisha, and Tarshish, Kitim, and Dodenim.

00:38:21.890 --> 00:38:27.750
By these were the Isles of the Gentiles divided in their lands, every one after his tongue,

00:38:28.070 --> 00:38:30.630
after their families, in their nations.

00:38:32.050 --> 00:38:37.130
And the sons of Ham, Cush, and Misraim, and Foot, and Canaan.

00:38:38.110 --> 00:38:44.530
And the sons of Cush, Seba, and Havilah, and Sabta, and Rehema, and Sabtika.

00:38:45.210 --> 00:38:48.270
And the sons of Rehema, Sheba, and Dedan.

00:38:48.270 --> 00:38:56.330
And Cush begat Nimrod, he began to be a mighty one in the earth. He was a mighty hunter before

00:38:56.330 --> 00:39:04.170
the Lord, wherefore it is said, even as Nimrod the mighty hunter before the Lord. And the

00:39:04.170 --> 00:39:10.670
beginning of his kingdom was Babel, and Urek, and Akkad, and Calni, in the land of Shinar.

00:39:11.850 --> 00:39:19.030
Out of that land went forth Asher, and builded Nineveh, and the city Rehoboth, and Cala,

00:39:19.330 --> 00:39:23.790
and Rezin, between Nineveh and Cala, the same as a great city.

00:39:25.110 --> 00:39:32.640
And Misraim begat Ludim, and Adimim, and Lahabim, and Naphtihim, and Pathrasim, and Chazlehim,

00:39:33.490 --> 00:39:36.510
out of whom came Philistim, and Kaftorim.

00:39:37.310 --> 00:39:44.110
And Canaan begat Sidon his first born, and Heth, and the Jebusite, and the Amorite, and

00:39:44.110 --> 00:39:50.450
the Gergosite, and the Hivite, and the Arkite, and the Sinite, and the Arvidite, and the

00:39:50.450 --> 00:39:56.010
Zemurite, and the Haemothite. And afterward were the families of the Canaanites spread

00:39:56.010 --> 00:39:56.510
abroad.

00:39:58.090 --> 00:40:03.410
And the border of the Canaanites was from Sidon as thou comest to Girar, unto Gaza,

00:40:03.870 --> 00:40:11.850
as thou goest unto Sodom, and Gomorrah, and Adma, and Zeboam, even unto Lesha. These

00:40:11.850 --> 00:40:16.570
are the sons of Ham after their families, after their tongues, in their countries,

00:40:16.930 --> 00:40:18.130
and in their nations.

00:40:19.570 --> 00:40:25.210
Unto Shem also the father of all the children of Eber, the brother of Japheth the elder,

00:40:25.590 --> 00:40:33.050
even to him were children born. The children of Shem, Elam and Asher, and Arphaxad, and

00:40:33.050 --> 00:40:41.450
Lod, and Aram. And the children of Aram, Uz, and Hul, and Gether, and Mash. And Arphaxad

00:40:41.450 --> 00:40:48.550
begat Sala, and Sala begat Eber. And unto Eber were born two sons, the name of one was

00:40:48.550 --> 00:40:53.950
Peleg, for in his days was the earth divided, and his brother's name was Joktan.

00:40:55.530 --> 00:41:03.030
And Joktan begat El-Modad, and Shelef, and Hazar-Meveth, and Jira, and Hadorim, and Uzzal,

00:41:03.050 --> 00:41:11.770
and Dikla, and Obel, and Abimeel, and Sheba, and Ophir, and Havilah, and Jobab. All these

00:41:11.770 --> 00:41:17.770
were the sons of Joktan. And their dwelling was from Misha as thou goest unto Seafar,

00:41:18.130 --> 00:41:24.590
a mount of the east. These are the sons of Shem after their families, after their tongues,

00:41:24.850 --> 00:41:31.750
in their lands, after their nations. These are the families of the sons of Noah, after

00:41:31.750 --> 00:41:37.590
their generations, in their nations, and by these were the nations divided in the earth

00:41:37.590 --> 00:41:38.730
after the flood.

00:41:42.290 --> 00:41:48.370
And the whole earth was of one language and of one speech. And it came to pass, as they

00:41:48.370 --> 00:41:53.650
journeyed from the east, that they found a plain in the land of Shinar, and they dwelt

00:41:53.650 --> 00:42:00.690
there. And they said one to another, Go to, let us make brick, and burn them throughly.

00:42:01.010 --> 00:42:07.330
And they had brick for stone, and slime had they for mortar. And they said, Go to, let

00:42:07.330 --> 00:42:13.430
us build us a city and a tower, whose top may reach unto heaven, and let us make us

00:42:13.430 --> 00:42:17.690
a name, lest we be scattered abroad upon the face of the whole earth.

00:42:18.610 --> 00:42:24.330
And the Lord came down to see the city and the tower which the children of men builded.

00:42:24.330 --> 00:42:31.130
And the Lord said, Behold, the people is one, and they have all one language, and this they

00:42:31.130 --> 00:42:37.010
begin to do, and now nothing will be restrained from them which they have imagined to do.

00:42:37.930 --> 00:42:43.610
Go to, let us go down, and there confound their language, that they may not understand

00:42:43.610 --> 00:42:49.770
one another's speech. So the Lord scattered them abroad from thence upon the face of all

00:42:49.770 --> 00:42:56.350
the earth, and they left off to build the city. Therefore is the name of it called Babel,

00:42:56.590 --> 00:43:01.990
because the Lord did there confound the language of all the earth, and from thence did the

00:43:01.990 --> 00:43:05.430
Lord scatter them abroad upon the face of all the earth.

00:43:06.830 --> 00:43:12.990
These are the generations of Shem. Shem was an hundred years old, and begat Arphaxid two

00:43:12.990 --> 00:43:19.310
years after the flood. And Shem lived after he begat Arphaxid five hundred years, and

00:43:19.310 --> 00:43:26.790
begat sons and daughters. And Arphaxid lived five and thirty years, and begat Sala. And

00:43:26.790 --> 00:43:33.130
Arphaxid lived after he begat Sala four hundred and three years, and begat sons and daughters.

00:43:34.070 --> 00:43:40.990
And Sala lived thirty years, and begat Ybar. And Sala lived after he begat Ybar four hundred

00:43:40.990 --> 00:43:47.790
and three years, and begat sons and daughters. And Ybar lived four and thirty years, and

00:43:47.790 --> 00:43:52.710
begat Peleg. And Eber lived after he begat Peleg four hundred and

00:43:52.710 --> 00:43:58.010
thirty years, and begat sons and daughters. And Peleg lived thirty

00:43:58.010 --> 00:44:03.850
years, and begat Riou. And Peleg lived after he begat Riou two hundred

00:44:03.850 --> 00:44:09.430
and nine years, and begat sons and daughters. And Riou lived two and

00:44:09.430 --> 00:44:14.850
thirty years, and begat Siirog. And Riou lived after he begat Siirog

00:44:14.850 --> 00:44:18.730
two hundred and seven years, and begat sons and daughters.

00:44:19.810 --> 00:44:23.170
And Si-ragh lived thirty years, and begat Nahor.

00:44:23.790 --> 00:44:29.070
And Si-ragh lived after he begat Nahor, two hundred years, and begat sons

00:44:29.070 --> 00:44:29.850
and daughters.

00:44:30.790 --> 00:44:34.630
And Nahor lived nine and twenty years, and begat Terah.

00:44:35.150 --> 00:44:39.790
And Nahor lived after he begat Terah, and a hundred and nineteen years,

00:44:40.050 --> 00:44:41.970
and begat sons and daughters.

00:44:42.710 --> 00:44:47.950
And Tyra lived seventy years, and begat Abram, Nahor, and Haran.

00:44:49.490 --> 00:44:56.450
Now these are the generations of Tyra. Tyra begat Abram, Nahor, and Haran, and Haran begat

00:44:56.450 --> 00:45:04.030
Lot. And Haran died before his father Tyra in the land of his nativity in Ur of the Chaldees.

00:45:05.110 --> 00:45:11.290
And Abram and Nahor took them wives. The name of Abram's wife was Sarai, and the name of

00:45:11.290 --> 00:45:17.470
Nahor's wife, Milka, the daughter of Haran, the father of Milka, and the father of Iska.

00:45:18.410 --> 00:45:25.690
But Sarai was barren, she had no child. And Tyra took Abram his son, and Lot the son of

00:45:25.690 --> 00:45:32.550
Haran his son's son, and Sarai his daughter-in-law, his son Abram's wife, and they went forth

00:45:32.550 --> 00:45:38.470
with them from Ur of the Chaldees to go into the land of Canaan, and they came unto Haran

00:45:38.470 --> 00:45:45.410
and dwelt there. And the days of Tyra were two hundred and five years, and Tyra died

00:45:45.410 --> 00:45:46.450
in Haran.

00:45:49.230 --> 00:45:55.130
Now the LORD had said unto Abram, Get thee out of thy country, and from thy kindred,

00:45:55.450 --> 00:46:01.050
and from thy father's house, unto a land that I will show thee. And I will make of thee

00:46:01.050 --> 00:46:06.910
a great nation, and I will bless thee, and make thy name great, and thou shalt be a blessing.

00:46:07.430 --> 00:46:13.450
And I will bless them that bless thee, and curse him that curseth thee, and in thee shall

00:46:13.450 --> 00:46:15.710
all families of the earth be blessed.

00:46:17.430 --> 00:46:23.730
So Abram departed as the LORD had spoken unto him, and Lot went with him, and Abram was

00:46:23.730 --> 00:46:30.630
seventy and five years old when he departed out of Haran. And Abram took Sarai his wife,

00:46:31.010 --> 00:46:36.230
and Lot his brother's son, and all their substance that they had gathered, and the souls that

00:46:36.230 --> 00:46:41.970
they had gotten in Haran, and they went forth to go into the land of Canaan, and into the

00:46:41.970 --> 00:46:43.770
land of Canaan they came.

00:46:45.070 --> 00:46:51.570
And Abram passed through the land unto the place of Sycam, unto the plain of Moray, and

00:46:51.570 --> 00:46:58.350
the Canaanite was then in the land. And the LORD appeared unto Abram, and said, Unto thy

00:46:58.350 --> 00:47:04.890
seed will I give this land, and their ability an altar unto the LORD who appeared unto him.

00:47:05.550 --> 00:47:10.990
And he removed from thence unto a mountain on the east of Bethel, and pitched his tent,

00:47:11.470 --> 00:47:17.270
having Bethel on the west, and Haei on the east, and there he builded an altar unto the

00:47:17.270 --> 00:47:24.070
LORD, and called upon the name of the LORD. And Abram journeyed, going on still toward

00:47:24.070 --> 00:47:24.830
the south.

00:47:26.450 --> 00:47:32.070
And there was a famine in the land, and Abram went down into Egypt to sojourn there, for

00:47:32.070 --> 00:47:37.770
the famine was grievous in the land. And it came to pass, when he was come near to

00:47:37.770 --> 00:47:44.110
enter into Egypt, that he said unto Sarai his wife, Behold now, I know that thou art

00:47:44.110 --> 00:47:50.090
a fair woman to look upon. Therefore it shall come to pass, when the Egyptians shall see

00:47:50.090 --> 00:47:55.710
thee, that they shall say, This is his wife, and they will kill me, but they will save

00:47:55.710 --> 00:47:56.670
thee alive.

00:47:57.650 --> 00:48:04.290
Say, I pray thee, thou art my sister, that it may be well with me for thy sake, and my

00:48:04.290 --> 00:48:06.350
soul shall live because of thee.

00:48:07.510 --> 00:48:13.330
And it came to pass, that, when Abram was come into Egypt, the Egyptians beheld the

00:48:13.330 --> 00:48:19.950
woman, that she was very fair. The princes also of Pharaoh saw her, and commended her

00:48:19.950 --> 00:48:26.770
before Pharaoh, and the woman was taken into Pharaoh's house. And he entreated Abram well

00:48:26.770 --> 00:48:33.630
for her sake, and he had sheep, and oxen, and he-asses, and men-servants, and maid-servants,

00:48:33.870 --> 00:48:40.970
and she-asses, and camels. And the LORD plagued Pharaoh and his house with great plagues because

00:48:40.970 --> 00:48:48.130
of Sarai, Abram's wife. And Pharaoh called Abram, and said, What is this that thou hast

00:48:48.130 --> 00:48:54.690
done unto me? Why didst thou not tell me that she was thy wife? Why saidst thou, She is

00:48:54.690 --> 00:49:01.890
my sister? So I might have taken her to me to wife. Now therefore, behold thy wife, take

00:49:01.890 --> 00:49:08.730
her, and go thy way. And Pharaoh commanded his men concerning him, and they sent him

00:49:08.730 --> 00:49:12.070
away, and his wife, and all that he had.

00:49:48.250 --> 00:49:54.230
And Abram went up out of Egypt, he and his wife, and all that he had, and lot with him,

00:49:54.290 --> 00:50:01.010
into the south. And Abram was very rich in cattle, in silver, and in gold. And he went

00:50:01.010 --> 00:50:06.190
on his journeys from the south, even to Bethel, unto the place where his tent had been at

00:50:06.190 --> 00:50:11.910
the beginning, between Bethel and Hiai, unto the place of the altar which he had made there

00:50:11.910 --> 00:50:18.390
at the first, and there Abram called on the name of the Lord. And lot also which went

00:50:18.390 --> 00:50:24.490
with Abram had flocks, and herds, and tents. And the land was not able to bear them that

00:50:24.490 --> 00:50:29.750
they might dwell together, for their substance was great, so that they could not dwell together.

00:50:30.430 --> 00:50:35.890
And there was a strife between the herdsmen of Abram's cattle and the herdsmen of lot's cattle,

00:50:36.270 --> 00:50:42.710
and the Canaanite and Perizzite then dwelled in the land. And Abram said unto lot,

00:50:43.110 --> 00:50:48.730
Let there be no strife, I pray thee, between me and thee, and between my herdsmen and thy

00:50:48.730 --> 00:50:55.950
herdsmen, for we be brethren. Is not the whole land before thee? Separate thyself, I pray thee,

00:50:55.950 --> 00:51:01.970
from me. If thou wilt take the left hand, then I will go to the right, or if thou depart

00:51:01.970 --> 00:51:08.810
to the right hand, then I will go to the left. And lot lifted up his eyes, and beheld all

00:51:08.810 --> 00:51:14.210
the plain of Jordan, that it was well watered everywhere, before the Lord destroyed Sodom

00:51:14.210 --> 00:51:19.970
and Gomorrah, even as the garden of the Lord, like the land of Egypt, as thou comest unto

00:51:19.970 --> 00:51:27.290
Zohar. Then lot chose him all the plain of Jordan, and lot journeyed east, and they separated

00:51:27.290 --> 00:51:33.550
themselves the one from the other. Abram dwelled in the land of Canaan, and lot dwelled in

00:51:33.550 --> 00:51:39.690
the cities of the plain, and pitched his tent towards Sodom. But the men of Sodom were wicked

00:51:39.690 --> 00:51:46.190
and sinners before the Lord exceedingly. And the Lord said unto Abram, after that lot

00:51:46.190 --> 00:51:51.350
was separated from him, Lift up now thine eyes, and look from the place where thou art,

00:51:51.550 --> 00:51:57.290
northward, and southward, and eastward, and westward, for all the land which thou seest,

00:51:57.610 --> 00:52:03.970
to thee will I give it, and to thy seed, for ever. And I will make thy seed as the dust

00:52:03.970 --> 00:52:09.010
of the earth, so that if a man can number the dust of the earth, then shall thy seed

00:52:09.010 --> 00:52:14.750
also be numbered. Arise, walk through the land, in the length of it, and in the breadth

00:52:14.750 --> 00:52:21.310
of it, for I will give it unto thee. Then Abram removed his tent, and came and dwelt

00:52:21.310 --> 00:52:27.050
in the plain of Mamre, which is in Hebron, and built there an altar unto the Lord.

00:52:28.290 --> 00:52:32.590
And it came to pass in the days of Amraphel,

00:52:32.610 --> 00:52:39.430
king of Shinar, Eriak, king of Alasar, Kederleomer, king of Elam, and Tidal, king of nations,

00:52:39.430 --> 00:52:45.670
that these made war with Bira, king of Sodom, and with Bersha, king of Gomorrah, Shinab,

00:52:45.710 --> 00:52:52.730
king of Adma, and Shemebr, king of Zeboyim, and the king of Bela, which is Zohar. All

00:52:52.730 --> 00:52:58.810
these were joined together in the vale of Sidim, which is the salt sea. Twelve years

00:52:58.810 --> 00:53:05.230
they served Kederleomer, and in the thirteenth year they rebelled. And in the fourteenth

00:53:05.230 --> 00:53:10.790
year came Kederleomer, and the kings that were with him, and smote the Raphayims in

00:53:10.790 --> 00:53:17.550
Ash-Tiroth-Kirneim, and the Zuzims in Ham, and the Imims in Shavakirithayim, and the

00:53:17.550 --> 00:53:23.830
Horites in their Mount Seir, unto El-Piran, which is by the wilderness. And they returned

00:53:23.830 --> 00:53:29.770
and came to Enmishpet, which is Kadesh, and smote all the country of the Amalekites and

00:53:29.770 --> 00:53:36.610
also the Amorites that dwelt in Hazesan-Temar. And there went out the king of Sodom, and

00:53:36.610 --> 00:53:41.590
the king of Gomorrah, and the king of Adma, and the king of Zeboyim, and the king of Bela,

00:53:41.950 --> 00:53:47.690
the same is Zohar, and they joined battle with them in the vale of Sidim, with Kederleomer,

00:53:47.790 --> 00:53:53.270
the king of Elam, and with Tidal, king of Nations, and Amreful, king of Shinar, and

00:53:53.750 --> 00:54:00.550
king of Alesar, four kings with five. And the vale of Sidim was full of slime-pits,

00:54:00.890 --> 00:54:06.210
and the kings of Sodom and Gomorrah fled and fell there, and they that remained fled to

00:54:06.210 --> 00:54:11.950
the mountain. And they took all the goods of Sodom and Gomorrah and all their victuals

00:54:11.950 --> 00:54:18.630
and went their way. And they took Lot, Abram's brother's son, who dwelt in Sodom and his

00:54:18.630 --> 00:54:25.610
goods, and departed. And there came one that had escaped and told Abram the Hebrew, for

00:54:25.610 --> 00:54:31.090
he dwelt in the plain of Mamre the Amorite, brother of Eshkol and brother of Anor, and

00:54:31.090 --> 00:54:36.930
these were confederate with Abram. And when Abram heard that his brother was taken captive,

00:54:37.330 --> 00:54:44.290
he armed his trained servants, born in his own house, 318, and pursued them unto Dan.

00:54:44.850 --> 00:54:50.930
And he divided himself against them, he and his servants, by night, and smote them, and

00:54:50.930 --> 00:54:56.770
pursued them unto Hobar, which is on the left hand of Damascus. And he brought back all

00:54:56.770 --> 00:55:02.870
the goods, and also brought again his brother Lot, and his goods, and the women also, and

00:55:02.870 --> 00:55:08.550
the people. And the king of Sodom went out to meet him after his return from the slaughter

00:55:08.550 --> 00:55:13.810
of Kederleomer and of the kings that were with him, at the vale of Sheva, which is the

00:55:13.810 --> 00:55:21.090
king's dale. And Melchizedek, king of Salem, brought forth bread and wine, and he was the

00:55:21.090 --> 00:55:27.230
priest of the Most High God. And he blessed him, and said, Blessed be Abram of the Most

00:55:27.230 --> 00:55:33.130
High God, possessor of heaven and earth, and blessed be the Most High God, which hath delivered

00:55:33.130 --> 00:55:39.890
thine enemies into thy hand. And he gave him tithes of all. And the king of Sodom said

00:55:39.890 --> 00:55:46.030
unto Abram, Give me the persons, and take the goods to thyself. And Abram said to the

00:55:46.030 --> 00:55:52.110
king of Sodom, I have lift up mine hand unto the Lord, the Most High God, the possessor

00:55:52.110 --> 00:55:57.730
of heaven and earth, that I will not take from a thread even to a shoe-latchet, and

00:55:57.730 --> 00:56:03.430
that I will not take anything that is thine, lest thou shouldst say, I have made Abram

00:56:03.430 --> 00:56:08.830
rich. Save only that which the young men have eaten, and the portion of the men which went

00:56:08.830 --> 00:56:13.650
with me, Anor, Eshkol, and Mamrie, let them take their portion.

00:56:15.850 --> 00:56:20.550
After these things the word of the Lord came

00:56:20.550 --> 00:56:27.490
unto Abram in a vision, saying, Fear not, Abram, I am thy shield, and thy exceeding

00:56:27.490 --> 00:56:34.450
great reward. And Abram said, Lord God, what wilt thou give me, seeing I go childless,

00:56:34.970 --> 00:56:42.230
and the steward of my house is this Eleazar of Damascus? And Abram said, Behold, to me

00:56:42.230 --> 00:56:49.010
thou hast given no seed, and lo, one born in my house is mine heir. And behold, the

00:56:49.010 --> 00:56:54.390
word of the Lord came unto him, saying, This shall not be thine heir, but he that shall

00:56:54.390 --> 00:57:00.230
come forth out of thine own bowels shall be thine heir. And he brought him forth abroad,

00:57:00.230 --> 00:57:06.090
and said, Look now toward heaven, and tell the stars if thou be able to number them.

00:57:06.550 --> 00:57:12.790
And he said unto him, So shall thy seed be. And he believed in the Lord, and he counted

00:57:12.790 --> 00:57:19.330
it to him for righteousness. And he said unto him, I am the Lord that brought thee out of

00:57:19.330 --> 00:57:26.330
oar of the Chaldees to give thee this land to inherit it. And he said, Lord God, whereby

00:57:26.330 --> 00:57:32.670
shall I know that I shall inherit it? And he said unto him, Take me an heifer of three

00:57:32.670 --> 00:57:39.090
years old, and a she-goat of three years old, and a ram of three years old, and a turtle-dove,

00:57:39.250 --> 00:57:45.150
and a young pigeon. And he took unto him all these, and divided them in the midst, and

00:57:45.150 --> 00:57:51.750
laid each piece one against another, but the birds divided he not. And when the fowls came

00:57:51.750 --> 00:57:58.230
down upon the carcasses, Abram drove them away. And when the sun was going down, a deep

00:57:58.230 --> 00:58:04.990
sleep fell upon Abram, and lo, and horror of great darkness fell upon him. And he said

00:58:04.990 --> 00:58:10.890
unto Abram, Know of a surety that thy seed shall be a stranger and a land that is not

00:58:10.890 --> 00:58:17.190
theirs, and shall serve them, and they shall afflict them four hundred years. And also

00:58:17.190 --> 00:58:22.390
that nation whom they shall serve will I judge, and afterward shall they come out with

00:58:22.390 --> 00:58:28.510
great substance. And thou shalt go to thy fathers in peace, thou shalt be buried in

00:58:28.510 --> 00:58:34.930
a good old age. But in the fourth generation they shall come hither again, for the iniquity

00:58:34.930 --> 00:58:41.550
of the Amorites is not yet full. And it came to pass that when the sun went down, and it

00:58:41.550 --> 00:58:47.590
was dark, behold a smoking furnace, and a burning lamp that passed between those pieces.

00:58:49.030 --> 00:58:54.870
In the same day the Lord made a covenant with Abram, saying, Unto thy seed have I given

00:58:54.870 --> 00:59:01.170
this land, from the river of Egypt unto the great river, the river Euphrates, the Kenites,

00:59:01.510 --> 00:59:06.810
and the Canisites, and the Cadmonites, and the Hittites, and the Perizzites, and the

00:59:06.810 --> 00:59:12.470
Ephemes, and the Amorites, and the Caninites, and the Girgashites, and the Jebusites.

00:59:15.950 --> 00:59:22.370
Now Sarai, Abram's wife, bear him no children, and she had an handmaid, an Egyptian, whose

00:59:22.370 --> 00:59:28.830
name was Hagar. And Sarai said unto Abram, Behold now, the Lord hath restrained me from

00:59:28.830 --> 00:59:35.610
bearing. I pray thee, go in unto my maid. It may be that I may obtain children by her.

00:59:35.970 --> 00:59:42.530
And Abram hearkened to the voice of Sarai. And Sarai Abram's wife took Hagar her maid,

00:59:42.670 --> 00:59:48.110
the Egyptian, after Abram had dwelt ten years in the land of Canaan, and gave her to her

00:59:48.110 --> 00:59:54.590
husband Abram to be his wife. And he went in unto Hagar, and she conceived, and when

00:59:54.590 --> 01:00:01.290
she saw that she had conceived, her mistress was despised in her eyes. And Sarai said unto

01:00:01.290 --> 01:00:07.650
Abram, My wrong be upon thee. I have given my maid into thy bosom, and when she saw that

01:00:07.650 --> 01:00:14.970
she had conceived, I was despised in her eyes. The Lord judged between me and thee. But Abram

01:00:14.970 --> 01:00:21.850
said unto Sarai, Behold, thy maid is in thy hand, due to her as it pleaseth thee. And

01:00:21.850 --> 01:00:28.250
when Sarai dealt hardly with her, she fled from her face. And the angel of the Lord found

01:00:28.250 --> 01:00:34.010
her by a fountain of water in the wilderness, by the fountain in the way to shore. And

01:00:34.010 --> 01:00:41.010
he said, Hagar, Sarai's maid, whence camest thou, and whither wilt thou go? And she said,

01:00:41.310 --> 01:00:48.630
I flee from the face of my mistress Sarai. And the angel of the Lord said unto her, Return

01:00:48.630 --> 01:00:53.950
to thy mistress, and submit thyself under her hands. And the angel of the Lord said

01:00:53.950 --> 01:00:59.610
unto her, I will multiply thy seed exceedingly, that it shall not be numbered for multitude.

01:01:00.250 --> 01:01:06.650
And the angel of the Lord said unto her, Behold, thou art with child, and shalt bear a son,

01:01:07.050 --> 01:01:13.390
and shalt call his name Ishmael, because the Lord hath heard thy affliction. And he will

01:01:13.390 --> 01:01:19.970
be a wild man, his hand will be against every man, and every man's hand against him, and

01:01:19.970 --> 01:01:25.570
he shall dwell in the presence of all his brethren. And she called the name of the Lord

01:01:25.570 --> 01:01:32.490
that spake unto her, Thou God, seest me. For she said, Have I also here looked after him

01:01:32.490 --> 01:01:39.370
that seeth me? Wherefore the well was called Bir-Lehi-Roy. Behold, it is between Kadesh

01:01:39.370 --> 01:01:46.770
and Bir-Ed. And Hagar bare Abram a son, and Abram called his son's name, which Hagar

01:01:46.770 --> 01:01:53.820
bare, Ishmael. And Abram was fourscore and six years old when Hagar bare Ishmael to Abram.

01:01:55.950 --> 01:02:00.290
And when Abram was ninety years old and nine,

01:02:00.510 --> 01:02:06.690
the Lord appeared to Abram, and said unto him, I am the Almighty God, walk before me,

01:02:06.830 --> 01:02:12.890
and be thou perfect, and I will make my covenant between me and thee, and will multiply thee

01:02:12.890 --> 01:02:20.430
exceedingly. And Abram fell on his face, and God talked with him, saying, Ask for me, behold,

01:02:20.590 --> 01:02:26.950
my covenant is with thee, and thou shalt be a father of many nations. Neither shall thy

01:02:26.950 --> 01:02:32.950
name any more be called Abram, but thy name shall be Abraham, for a father of many nations

01:02:32.950 --> 01:02:38.570
have I made thee. And I will make thee exceeding fruitful, and I will make nations out thee,

01:02:38.570 --> 01:02:44.490
and kings shall come out of thee. And I will establish my covenant between me and thee

01:02:44.490 --> 01:02:50.710
and thy seed after thee and their generations, for an everlasting covenant, to be a God unto

01:02:50.710 --> 01:02:57.410
thee, and to thy seed after thee. And I will give unto thee, and to thy seed after thee,

01:02:57.650 --> 01:03:03.450
the land wherein thou art a stranger, all the land of Canaan, for an everlasting possession,

01:03:03.750 --> 01:03:10.750
and I will be their God. And God said unto Abraham, Thou shalt keep my covenant therefore,

01:03:11.050 --> 01:03:18.210
thou and thy seed after thee, in their generations. This is my covenant, which ye shall keep between

01:03:18.210 --> 01:03:24.570
me and you and thy seed after thee. Every man-child among you shall be circumcised,

01:03:25.130 --> 01:03:30.310
and ye shall circumcise the flesh of your foreskin, and it shall be a token of the covenant

01:03:30.310 --> 01:03:36.730
betwixt me and you. And he that is eight days old shall be circumcised among you, every

01:03:36.730 --> 01:03:42.370
man-child in your generations, he that is born in the house or bought with money of

01:03:42.370 --> 01:03:48.830
any stranger which is not of thy seed. He that is born in thy house and he that is bought

01:03:48.830 --> 01:03:54.530
with thy money must needs be circumcised, and my covenant shall be in your flesh for

01:03:54.530 --> 01:04:00.670
an everlasting covenant. And the uncircumcised man-child whose flesh of his foreskin is

01:04:00.670 --> 01:04:06.810
not circumcised, that soul shall be cut off from his people, he hath broken my covenant.

01:04:07.930 --> 01:04:14.290
And God said unto Abraham, As for Sarai thy wife, thou shalt not call her name Sarai,

01:04:14.670 --> 01:04:21.390
but Sarah shall her name be. And I will bless her and give thee a son also of her, yea I

01:04:21.390 --> 01:04:26.770
will bless her and she shall be a mother of nations, kings of people shall be of her.

01:04:27.890 --> 01:04:34.130
Then Abraham fell upon his face and laughed, and said in his heart, Shall a child be born

01:04:34.130 --> 01:04:39.590
unto him that is an hundred years old, and shall Sarah that is ninety years old bear?

01:04:40.310 --> 01:04:47.130
And Abraham said unto God, O that Ishmael might live before thee. And God said, Sarah

01:04:47.130 --> 01:04:53.230
thy wife shall bear thee a son indeed, and thou shalt call his name Isaac, and I will

01:04:53.230 --> 01:04:59.770
establish my covenant with him for an everlasting covenant, and with his seed after him. And

01:04:59.770 --> 01:05:05.410
as for Ishmael, I have heard thee, behold I have blessed him and will make him fruitful

01:05:05.410 --> 01:05:11.130
and will multiply him exceedingly, twelve princes shall he beget, and that will make

01:05:11.130 --> 01:05:18.190
a great nation. But my covenant will I establish with Isaac, which Sarah shall bear unto thee

01:05:18.190 --> 01:05:25.090
at this set time in the next year. And he left off talking with him, and God went up

01:05:25.090 --> 01:05:31.550
from Abraham. And Abraham took Ishmael his son, and all that were born in his house,

01:05:31.890 --> 01:05:37.250
and all that were bought with his money, every male among the men of Abraham's house, and

01:05:37.250 --> 01:05:43.270
circumcised the flesh of their foreskin in the self-same day as God had said unto him.

01:05:44.170 --> 01:05:49.870
And Abraham was ninety years old and nine when he was circumcised in the flesh of his

01:05:49.870 --> 01:05:56.350
foreskin. And Ishmael his son was thirteen years old when he was circumcised in the flesh

01:05:56.350 --> 01:06:02.930
of his foreskin. In the self-same day was Abraham circumcised, and Ishmael his son.

01:06:03.470 --> 01:06:08.410
And all the men of his house, born in the house and bought with money of the stranger,

01:06:08.850 --> 01:06:10.650
were circumcised with him.

01:06:13.090 --> 01:06:17.010
And the LORD appeared unto him in the plains

01:06:17.010 --> 01:06:22.290
of Mamrie, and he sat in the tent-door in the heat of the day, and he lift up his eyes

01:06:22.290 --> 01:06:28.410
and looked, and lo, three men stood by him. And when he saw them, he ran to meet them

01:06:28.410 --> 01:06:32.430
from the tent-door, and bowed himself toward the ground, and said,

01:06:32.790 --> 01:06:38.930
My LORD, if now I have found favour in thy sight, pass not away, I pray thee, from thy

01:06:38.930 --> 01:06:45.210
servant. Let a little water, I pray you, be fetched, and wash your feet, and rest yourselves

01:06:45.210 --> 01:06:51.310
under the tree, and I will fetch a morsel of bread, and comfort ye your hearts. After

01:06:51.310 --> 01:06:56.390
that ye shall pass on, for therefore are ye come to your servant. And they said,

01:06:56.390 --> 01:06:58.650
So do as thou hast said.

01:06:59.390 --> 01:07:05.130
And Abraham hastened into the tent unto Sarah, and said, Make ready quickly three measures

01:07:05.130 --> 01:07:11.630
of fine meal, knead it, and make cakes upon the hearth. And Abraham ran unto the herd,

01:07:12.010 --> 01:07:17.610
and fetched a calf tender and good, and gave it unto a young man, and he hasted to dress

01:07:17.610 --> 01:07:23.710
it. And he took butter and milk, and the calf which he had dressed, and set it before them,

01:07:23.710 --> 01:07:30.030
and he stood by them under the tree, and they did eat. And they said unto him, Where is

01:07:30.030 --> 01:07:36.810
Sarah thy wife? And he said, Behold in the tent. And he said, I will certainly return

01:07:36.810 --> 01:07:43.730
unto thee according to the time of life, and lo, Sarah thy wife shall have a son. And Sarah

01:07:43.730 --> 01:07:46.290
heard it in the tent-door which was behind him.

01:07:47.190 --> 01:07:53.330
Now Abraham and Sarah were old and well stricken in age, and it ceased to be with Sarah after

01:07:53.330 --> 01:07:59.890
the manner of women. Therefore Sarah laughed within herself, saying, After I am waxed old

01:07:59.890 --> 01:08:06.610
shall I have pleasure, my lord being old also? And the lord said unto Abraham, Wherefore

01:08:06.610 --> 01:08:13.270
did Sarah laugh, saying, Shall I of a surety bear a child which am old? Is anything too

01:08:13.270 --> 01:08:18.830
hard for the lord? At the time appointed I will return unto thee according to the time

01:08:18.830 --> 01:08:21.550
of life, and Sarah shall have a son.

01:08:22.290 --> 01:08:29.390
Then Sarah denied, saying, I laughed not, for she was afraid. And he said, Nay, but

01:08:29.390 --> 01:08:30.510
thou didst laugh.

01:08:31.810 --> 01:08:36.670
And the men rose up from thence, and looked towards Sodom, and Abraham went with them

01:08:36.670 --> 01:08:42.770
to bring them on the way. And the lord said, Shall I hide from Abraham that thing which

01:08:42.770 --> 01:08:48.730
I do, seeing that Abraham shall surely become a great and mighty nation, and all the nations

01:08:48.730 --> 01:08:53.870
of the earth shall be blessed in him? For I know him that he will command his children

01:08:53.870 --> 01:08:59.310
and his household after him, and they shall keep the way of the lord to do justice and

01:08:59.310 --> 01:09:04.250
judgment, that the lord may bring upon Abraham that which he hath spoken of him.

01:09:05.170 --> 01:09:10.990
And the lord said, Because the cry of Sodom and Gomorrah is great, and because their sin

01:09:10.990 --> 01:09:16.690
is very grievous, I will go down now, and see what they have done altogether according

01:09:16.690 --> 01:09:21.150
to the cry of it which has come unto me, and if not, I will know.

01:09:22.050 --> 01:09:27.150
And the men turned their faces from thence, and went towards Sodom, but Abraham stood

01:09:27.150 --> 01:09:33.850
yet before the lord. And Abraham drew near, and said, Wilt thou also destroy the righteous

01:09:33.850 --> 01:09:39.670
with the wicked? Peradventure there be fifty righteous within the city. Wilt thou also

01:09:39.670 --> 01:09:45.670
destroy and not spare the place for the fifty righteous that are therein? That be far from

01:09:45.670 --> 01:09:51.770
this manner, to slay the righteous with the wicked, and that the righteous should be as

01:09:51.770 --> 01:09:57.070
the wicked, that be far from thee, shall not the judge of all the earth do right?

01:09:57.670 --> 01:10:03.770
And the lord said, If I find in Sodom fifty righteous within the city, then I will spare

01:10:03.770 --> 01:10:10.250
all the place for their sakes. And Abraham answered and said, Behold now, I have taken

01:10:10.250 --> 01:10:15.970
upon me to speak unto the lord, which am but dust and ashes. Peradventure there shall

01:10:15.970 --> 01:10:21.430
be lack five of the fifty righteous. Wilt thou destroy all the city for lack of five?

01:10:21.770 --> 01:10:28.190
And he said, If I find there forty and five, I will not destroy it. And he spake unto him

01:10:28.190 --> 01:10:34.290
yet again, and said, Peradventure there shall be forty found there. And he said, I will

01:10:34.290 --> 01:10:40.230
not do it for forty's sake. And he said unto him, O, let not the lord be angry, and I will

01:10:40.230 --> 01:10:46.110
speak. Peradventure there shall thirty be found there. And he said, I will not do it

01:10:46.110 --> 01:10:52.690
if I find thirty there. And he said, Behold now, I have taken upon me to speak unto the

01:10:52.690 --> 01:10:59.410
lord. Peradventure there shall be twenty found there. And he said, I will not destroy it

01:10:59.410 --> 01:11:05.610
for twenty's sake. And he said, O, let not the lord be angry, and I will speak yet but

01:11:05.610 --> 01:11:12.390
this once. Peradventure ten shall be found there. And he said, I will not destroy it

01:11:12.390 --> 01:11:18.730
for ten's sake. And the lord went his way as soon as he had left communing with Abraham,

01:11:18.730 --> 01:11:21.850
and Abraham returned unto his place.

01:11:54.470 --> 01:12:00.950
And there came two angels to Sodom at even, and Lot sat in the gate of Sodom, and Lot,

01:12:00.950 --> 01:12:06.050
seeing them, rose up to meet them, and he bowed himself with his face toward the ground,

01:12:06.370 --> 01:12:12.750
and he said, Behold now, my lords, turn in, I pray you, into your servant's house, and

01:12:12.750 --> 01:12:18.490
tarry all night, and wash your feet, and ye shall rise up early, and go on your ways.

01:12:18.490 --> 01:12:22.890
And they said, Nay, but we will abide in the street all night.

01:12:23.750 --> 01:12:29.150
And he pressed upon them greatly, and they turned in unto him, and entered into his house,

01:12:29.450 --> 01:12:33.790
and he made them a feast, and did bake unleavened bread, and they did eat.

01:12:34.870 --> 01:12:40.410
But before they lay down, the men of the city, even the men of Sodom, compassed the house

01:12:40.410 --> 01:12:46.450
round, both old and young, all the people from every quarter, and they called unto Lot

01:12:46.450 --> 01:12:50.450
and said unto him, Where are the men which came into thee this night?

01:12:50.870 --> 01:12:53.610
Bring them out unto us, that we may know them.

01:12:54.510 --> 01:13:00.110
And Lot went out the door unto them, and shut the door after him, and said, I pray you,

01:13:00.230 --> 01:13:02.230
brethren, do not so wickedly.

01:13:03.030 --> 01:13:06.390
Behold now, I have two daughters which have not known man.

01:13:06.930 --> 01:13:11.990
Let me, I pray you, bring them out unto you, and do ye to them as is good in your eyes,

01:13:11.990 --> 01:13:17.710
only unto these men do nothing, for therefore came they unto the shadow of my roof.

01:13:18.330 --> 01:13:20.390
And they said, Stand back.

01:13:20.810 --> 01:13:26.130
And they said again, This one fellow came into Sojourn, and he will needs be a judge.

01:13:26.630 --> 01:13:29.270
Now will we deal worse with thee than with them.

01:13:29.790 --> 01:13:34.790
And they pressed sore upon the man, even Lot, and came near to break the door.

01:13:35.690 --> 01:13:40.790
But the men put forth their hand, and pulled Lot into the house to them, and shut, too,

01:13:40.790 --> 01:13:41.310
the door.

01:13:41.970 --> 01:13:46.930
And they smote the men that were at the door of the house with blindness, both small and

01:13:46.930 --> 01:13:50.250
great, so that they wearied themselves to find the door.

01:13:51.170 --> 01:13:54.930
And the men said unto Lot, Hast thou here any besides?

01:13:55.490 --> 01:14:01.050
Sons-in-law, and thy sons, and thy daughters, and whatsoever thou hast in the city, bring

01:14:01.050 --> 01:14:02.310
them out of this place.

01:14:02.650 --> 01:14:07.850
For we will destroy this place, because the cry of them is wax and great, before the face

01:14:07.850 --> 01:14:11.430
of the Lord, and the Lord has sent us to destroy it.

01:14:12.350 --> 01:14:18.370
And Lot went out, and spake unto his sons-in-law, which married his daughters, and said, Up,

01:14:18.570 --> 01:14:22.050
get you out of this place, for the Lord will destroy the city.

01:14:23.170 --> 01:14:26.450
But he seemed as one that mocked unto his sons-in-law.

01:14:27.630 --> 01:14:33.290
And when the morning arose, then the angels hastened Lot, saying, Arise, take thy wife

01:14:33.290 --> 01:14:38.350
which are here, lest thou be consumed in the iniquity of the city.

01:14:39.330 --> 01:14:44.350
And while he lingered, the men laid hold upon his hand, and upon the hand of his wife, and

01:14:44.350 --> 01:14:49.390
upon the hand of his two daughters, the Lord being merciful unto him, and they brought

01:14:49.390 --> 01:14:51.990
him forth, and set him without the city.

01:14:53.270 --> 01:14:58.160
And it came to pass, when they had brought them forth abroad, that he said, Escape for

01:14:58.160 --> 01:15:02.740
Look not behind thee, neither stay thou in all the plain.

01:15:03.280 --> 01:15:05.980
Escape to the mountain, lest thou be consumed.

01:15:06.960 --> 01:15:10.300
And Lot said unto them, Oh, not so, my lord.

01:15:10.840 --> 01:15:16.260
Behold now, thy servant hath found grace in thy sight, and thou hast magnified thy mercy,

01:15:16.400 --> 01:15:21.460
which thou hast shewed unto me in saving my life, and I cannot escape to the mountain,

01:15:21.780 --> 01:15:24.000
lest some evil take me, and I die.

01:15:24.900 --> 01:15:29.240
Behold thou, this city is near to flee unto, and it is a little one.

01:15:29.600 --> 01:15:34.120
Oh, let me escape thither, is it not a little one, and my soul shall live.

01:15:34.640 --> 01:15:40.140
And he said unto him, See, I have accepted thee concerning this thing also, that I will

01:15:40.140 --> 01:15:43.580
not overthrow this city, for the which thou hast spoken.

01:15:44.620 --> 01:15:49.460
Haste thee, escape thither, for I cannot do anything till thou become thither.

01:15:50.160 --> 01:15:53.040
Therefore the name of the city was called Zohar.

01:15:54.440 --> 01:15:58.180
The sun was risen upon the earth when Lot entered into Zohar.

01:15:58.860 --> 01:16:04.800
Then the Lord rained upon Sodom and upon Gomorrah brimstone and fire from the Lord out of heaven,

01:16:05.220 --> 01:16:10.460
and he overthrew those cities and all the plain and all the inhabitants of the cities

01:16:10.460 --> 01:16:12.800
and that which grew upon the ground.

01:16:13.420 --> 01:16:18.380
But his wife looked back from behind him, and she became a pillar of salt.

01:16:20.120 --> 01:16:24.700
And Abraham got up early in the morning to the place where he stood before the Lord,

01:16:25.120 --> 01:16:29.500
and he looked toward Sodom and Gomorrah and toward all the land of the plain,

01:16:29.920 --> 01:16:34.720
and beheld and lo, the smoke of the country went up as the smoke of a furnace.

01:16:36.120 --> 01:16:41.620
And it came to pass, when God destroyed the cities of the plain, that God remembered Abraham

01:16:41.620 --> 01:16:48.160
and sent Lot out of the midst of the overthrow when he overthrew the cities in the which Lot dwelt.

01:16:49.060 --> 01:16:54.020
And Lot went up out of Zohar and dwelt in the mountain and his two daughters with him,

01:16:54.220 --> 01:16:59.640
for he feared to dwell in Zohar, and he dwelt in a cave, he and his two daughters.

01:17:00.620 --> 01:17:05.960
And the firstborn said unto the younger, Our father is old, and there is not a man in the

01:17:05.960 --> 01:17:09.300
earth to come in unto us after the manner of all the earth.

01:17:09.960 --> 01:17:15.080
Come, let us make our father drink wine, and we will lie with him, that we may preserve

01:17:15.080 --> 01:17:16.280
seed of our father.

01:17:17.300 --> 01:17:22.140
And they made their father drink wine that night, and the firstborn went in and lay with

01:17:22.140 --> 01:17:26.740
her father, and he perceived not when she lay down, nor when she arose.

01:17:28.080 --> 01:17:33.460
And it came to pass on the morrow that the firstborn said unto the younger, Behold, I

01:17:33.460 --> 01:17:39.060
lay yesternight with my father, let us make him drink wine this night also, and go thou

01:17:39.060 --> 01:17:42.780
in, and lie with him, that we may preserve seed of our father.

01:17:43.620 --> 01:17:48.540
And they made their father drink wine that night also, and the younger arose and lay

01:17:48.540 --> 01:17:53.140
with him, and he perceived not when she lay down, nor when she arose.

01:17:53.960 --> 01:17:57.780
Thus were both the daughters of Lot with child by their father.

01:17:58.920 --> 01:18:05.020
And the firstborn bare a son, and called his name Moab, the same as the father of the Moabites

01:18:05.020 --> 01:18:06.060
unto this day.

01:18:06.860 --> 01:18:13.040
And the younger she also bare a son, and called his name Benamai, the same as the father of

01:18:13.040 --> 01:18:15.220
the children of Ammon unto this day.

01:18:17.700 --> 01:18:21.460
An Abraham journeyed from thence toward the

01:18:21.460 --> 01:18:26.800
south country, and dwelt between Kadesh and Shur, and sojourned in Girar.

01:18:27.460 --> 01:18:33.660
And Abraham said of Sarah his wife, She is my sister, and Abimelek king of Girar sent,

01:18:33.660 --> 01:18:34.740
and took Sarah.

01:18:35.680 --> 01:18:42.020
But God came to Abimelek in a dream by night, and said to him, Behold thou art but a dead

01:18:42.020 --> 01:18:46.400
man, for the woman which thou hast taken, for she is a man's wife.

01:18:47.080 --> 01:18:53.040
But Abimelek had not come near her, and he said, Lord, wilt thou slay also a righteous

01:18:53.040 --> 01:18:53.520
nation?

01:18:54.320 --> 01:19:00.540
Said he not unto me, She is my sister, and she, even she herself, said, He is my brother.

01:19:01.120 --> 01:19:05.640
In the integrity of my heart, in the innocency of my hands, have I done this.

01:19:06.580 --> 01:19:12.180
And God said unto him in a dream, Yea, I know that thou didst this in the integrity of thy

01:19:12.180 --> 01:19:16.120
heart, for I also withheld thee from sinning against me.

01:19:16.520 --> 01:19:19.140
Therefore suffered I thee not to touch her.

01:19:20.240 --> 01:19:25.500
Now therefore restore the man his wife, for he is a prophet, and he shall pray for thee,

01:19:25.500 --> 01:19:26.820
and thou shalt live.

01:19:27.280 --> 01:19:33.200
And if thou restore her not, know thou that thou shalt surely die, thou and all that are

01:19:33.200 --> 01:19:33.660
thine.

01:19:34.860 --> 01:19:40.020
Therefore Abimelek rose early in the morning, and called all his servants, and told all

01:19:40.020 --> 01:19:43.580
these things in their ears, and the men were sore afraid.

01:19:45.040 --> 01:19:50.160
Then Abimelek called Abraham, and said unto him, What hast thou done unto us?

01:19:50.160 --> 01:19:55.300
And what have I offended thee, that thou hast brought on me and on my kingdom a great sin?

01:19:55.980 --> 01:19:59.040
Thou hast done deeds unto me that ought not to be done.

01:19:59.900 --> 01:20:04.720
And Abimelek said unto Abraham, What sawest thou that thou hast done this thing?

01:20:05.540 --> 01:20:11.360
And Abraham said, Because I thought surely the fear of God is not in this place, and

01:20:11.360 --> 01:20:13.520
they will slay me for my wife's sake.

01:20:14.120 --> 01:20:19.360
And yet indeed she is my sister, she is the daughter of my father, but not the daughter

01:20:19.360 --> 01:20:22.060
of my mother, and she became my wife.

01:20:22.780 --> 01:20:27.780
And it came to pass, when God caused me to wander from my father's house, that I said

01:20:27.780 --> 01:20:33.000
unto her, This is thy kindness which thou shalt show unto me, and every place whither

01:20:33.000 --> 01:20:36.200
we shall come, say of me, He is my brother.

01:20:37.340 --> 01:20:42.640
And Abimelek took sheep, and oxen, and men's servants, and women's servants, and gave them

01:20:42.640 --> 01:20:46.000
unto Abraham, and restored him Sarah his wife.

01:20:46.560 --> 01:20:52.240
And Abimelek said, Behold, my land is before thee, dwell where it pleaseth thee.

01:20:52.960 --> 01:20:59.520
And unto Sarah he said, Behold, I have given thy brother a thousand pieces of silver, behold,

01:20:59.660 --> 01:21:04.820
he is to thee a covering of the eyes unto all that are with thee and with all other.

01:21:05.400 --> 01:21:06.960
Thus she was reproved.

01:21:08.100 --> 01:21:13.920
So Abraham prayed unto God, and God healed Abimelek, and his wife, and his maid-servants,

01:21:13.920 --> 01:21:15.400
and they bear children.

01:21:16.140 --> 01:21:21.700
For the Lord had fast closed up all the wombs of the house of Abimelek because of Sarah,

01:21:22.000 --> 01:21:23.140
Abraham's wife.

01:21:26.700 --> 01:21:32.440
And the Lord visited Sarah as he had said, and the Lord did unto Sarah as he had spoken.

01:21:33.220 --> 01:21:39.380
For Sarah conceived and bare Abraham a son in his old age, at the set time of which God

01:21:39.380 --> 01:21:40.660
had spoken to him.

01:21:41.300 --> 01:21:46.880
And Abraham called the name of his son that was born unto him, whom Sarah bare to him,

01:21:47.140 --> 01:21:47.660
Isaac.

01:21:48.640 --> 01:21:54.600
And Abraham circumcised his son Isaac being eight days old, as God had commanded him.

01:21:55.300 --> 01:22:00.040
And Abraham was an hundred years old when his son Isaac was born unto him.

01:22:01.200 --> 01:22:06.980
And Sarah said, God hath made me to laugh, so that all that hear will laugh with me.

01:22:06.980 --> 01:22:13.260
And she said, Who would have said unto Abraham that Sarah should have given children suck,

01:22:13.780 --> 01:22:16.420
for I have borne him a son in his old age?

01:22:17.120 --> 01:22:23.000
And the child grew and was weaned, and Abraham made a great feast the same day that Isaac

01:22:23.000 --> 01:22:24.180
was weaned.

01:22:24.760 --> 01:22:30.380
And Sarah saw the son of Hagar, the Egyptian, which she had borne unto Abraham, mocking.

01:22:31.340 --> 01:22:37.420
Wherefore she said unto Abraham, Cast out this bondwoman and her son, for the son of

01:22:37.420 --> 01:22:41.540
this bondwoman shall not be heir with my son, even with Isaac.

01:22:42.360 --> 01:22:46.540
And the thing was very grievous in Abraham's sight because of his son.

01:22:47.520 --> 01:22:53.660
And God said unto Abraham, Let it not be grievous in thy sight because of the lad and because

01:22:53.660 --> 01:22:59.000
of thy bondwoman, in all that Sarah hath said unto thee, hearken unto her voice.

01:22:59.000 --> 01:23:02.100
For in Isaac shall thy seed be called.

01:23:03.520 --> 01:23:08.860
And also of the son of the bondwoman will I make a nation, because he is thy seed.

01:23:10.140 --> 01:23:15.580
And Abraham rose up early in the morning and took bread and a bottle of water and gave

01:23:15.580 --> 01:23:20.500
it unto Hagar, putting it on her shoulder, and the child, and sent her away.

01:23:20.920 --> 01:23:24.580
And she departed and wandered in the wilderness of Beersheba.

01:23:25.520 --> 01:23:30.540
And the water was spent in the bottle, and she cast the child under one of the shrubs.

01:23:31.480 --> 01:23:36.960
And she went and sat her down over against him a good way off, as it were a bow-shot,

01:23:37.440 --> 01:23:40.720
for she said, Let me not see the death of the child.

01:23:41.240 --> 01:23:45.460
And she sat over against him and lifted up her voice and wept.

01:23:46.500 --> 01:23:51.800
And God heard the voice of the lad, and the angel of God called to Hagar out of heaven

01:23:51.800 --> 01:23:54.920
and said unto her, What aileth thee, Hagar?

01:23:55.380 --> 01:23:59.340
Fear not, for God hath heard the voice of the lad where he is.

01:24:00.340 --> 01:24:06.100
Arise, lift up the lad, and hold him in thine hand, for I will make him a great nation.

01:24:07.240 --> 01:24:13.080
And God opened her eyes and she saw a well of water, and she went and filled the bottle

01:24:13.080 --> 01:24:15.540
with water and gave the lad drink.

01:24:16.360 --> 01:24:22.360
And God was with the lad, and he grew and dwelt in the wilderness and became an archer.

01:24:22.980 --> 01:24:28.020
And he dwelt in the wilderness of Peran, and his mother took him a wife out of the land

01:24:28.020 --> 01:24:28.720
of Egypt.

01:24:29.660 --> 01:24:35.360
And it came to pass at that time that Abimlek and Phicol, the chief captain of his host,

01:24:35.800 --> 01:24:40.460
spake unto Abraham, saying, God is with thee in all that thou doest.

01:24:41.020 --> 01:24:47.380
Thou therefore swear unto me hereby God, that thou will not deal falsely with me, nor with

01:24:47.380 --> 01:24:53.220
my son, nor with my son's son, but according to the kindness that I have done unto thee,

01:24:53.540 --> 01:24:57.780
thou shalt do unto me, and to the land wherein thou hast sojourned.

01:24:58.400 --> 01:25:00.880
And Abraham said, I will swear.

01:25:02.160 --> 01:25:07.500
And Abraham reproved Abimlek because of a well of water which Abimlek's servants had

01:25:07.500 --> 01:25:09.060
violently taken away.

01:25:09.740 --> 01:25:15.900
And Abimlek said, I want not who hath done this thing, neither didst thou tell me, neither

01:25:15.900 --> 01:25:18.120
yet heard I of it, but to-day.

01:25:19.040 --> 01:25:24.860
And Abraham took sheep and oxen and gave them unto Abimlek, and both of them made a covenant.

01:25:26.060 --> 01:25:29.620
And Abraham set seven eulams of the flock by themselves.

01:25:30.300 --> 01:25:36.240
And Abimlek said unto Abraham, What mean these seven eulams which thou hast set by themselves?

01:25:36.980 --> 01:25:42.680
And he said, For these seven eulams shalt thou take of my hand that they may be a witness

01:25:42.680 --> 01:25:45.260
unto me that I have digged this well.

01:25:46.300 --> 01:25:51.700
Wherefore he called that place Beersheba, because there they swear both of them.

01:25:52.600 --> 01:25:58.540
Thus they made a covenant at Beersheba, then Abimlek rose up, and Phicol the chief captain

01:25:58.540 --> 01:26:02.100
of his host, and they returned into the land of the Philistines.

01:26:02.820 --> 01:26:08.480
And Abraham planted a grove in Beersheba, and called there on the name of the Lord the

01:26:08.480 --> 01:26:09.820
everlasting God.

01:26:11.000 --> 01:26:14.880
And Abraham sojourned in the Philistines land many days.

01:26:18.720 --> 01:26:25.020
And it came to pass after these things that God did tempt Abraham, and said unto him Abraham,

01:26:25.400 --> 01:26:28.600
And he said, Behold, here I am.

01:26:29.080 --> 01:26:34.920
And he said, Take now thy son, thine only son Isaac, whom thou lovest, and get thee

01:26:34.920 --> 01:26:40.520
into the land of Moriah, and offer him there for a burnt offering upon one of the mountains

01:26:40.520 --> 01:26:42.000
which I will tell thee of.

01:26:43.240 --> 01:26:48.740
And Abraham rose up early in the morning, and saddled his ass, and took two of his young

01:26:48.740 --> 01:26:54.300
men with him, and Isaac his son, and claved the wood for the burnt offering, and rose

01:26:54.300 --> 01:26:57.960
up, and went unto the place of which God had told him.

01:26:58.860 --> 01:27:04.460
Then on the third day Abraham lifted up his eyes, and saw the place afar off.

01:27:05.360 --> 01:27:11.400
And Abraham said unto his young men, Abide ye here with the ass, and I and the lad will

01:27:11.400 --> 01:27:14.600
go yonder and worship, and come again to you.

01:27:15.320 --> 01:27:21.200
And Abraham took the wood of the burnt offering, and laid it upon Isaac his son, and he took

01:27:21.200 --> 01:27:25.520
the fire in his hand and a knife, and they went both of them together.

01:27:26.840 --> 01:27:33.540
And Isaac spake unto Abraham his father, and said, My father, and he said, Here am I, my

01:27:33.540 --> 01:27:33.980
son.

01:27:34.420 --> 01:27:39.720
And he said, Behold the fire and the wood, but where is the lamb for a burnt offering?

01:27:40.560 --> 01:27:46.100
And Abraham said, My son, God will provide himself a lamb for a burnt offering.

01:27:46.700 --> 01:27:48.660
So they went both of them together.

01:27:49.340 --> 01:27:54.760
And they came to the place which God had told him of, and Abraham built an altar there,

01:27:55.020 --> 01:28:01.040
and laid the wood in order, and bound Isaac his son, and laid him on the altar upon the

01:28:01.040 --> 01:28:01.300
wood.

01:28:02.500 --> 01:28:07.260
And Abraham stretched forth his hand, and took the knife to slay his son.

01:28:08.640 --> 01:28:14.540
And the angel of the Lord called unto him out of heaven, and said, Abraham, Abraham!

01:28:14.980 --> 01:28:17.180
And he said, Here am I.

01:28:17.960 --> 01:28:24.160
And he said, Lay not thine hand upon the lad, neither do thou anything unto him, for now

01:28:24.160 --> 01:28:30.160
I know that thou fearest God, seeing thou hast not withheld thy son, thine only son,

01:28:30.200 --> 01:28:30.900
from me.

01:28:32.060 --> 01:28:38.420
And Abraham lifted up his eyes, and looked, and behold, behind him a ram caught in a thicket

01:28:38.420 --> 01:28:39.400
by his horns.

01:28:40.060 --> 01:28:45.400
And Abraham went, and took the ram, and offered him up for a burnt offering, in the stead

01:28:45.400 --> 01:28:46.240
of his son.

01:28:47.740 --> 01:28:53.560
And Abraham called the name of that place Jehovah Jireh, as it is said to this day,

01:28:53.760 --> 01:28:56.080
In the mount of the Lord it shall be seen.

01:28:57.200 --> 01:29:03.020
And the angel of the Lord called unto Abraham out of heaven the second time, and said, By

01:29:03.020 --> 01:29:09.480
myself have I sworn, saith the Lord, for because thou hast done this thing, and hast not withheld

01:29:09.480 --> 01:29:15.520
thy son, thine only son, that in blessing I will bless thee, and in multiplying I will

01:29:15.520 --> 01:29:21.040
multiply thy seed as the stars of the heaven, and as the sand which is upon the seashore,

01:29:21.480 --> 01:29:27.160
and thy seed shall possess the gate of his enemies, and in thy seed shall all the nations

01:29:27.160 --> 01:29:31.020
of the earth be blessed, because thou hast obeyed my voice.

01:29:31.960 --> 01:29:37.480
So Abraham returned unto his young men, and they rose up and went together to Beersheba,

01:29:37.900 --> 01:29:40.200
and Abraham dwelt at Beersheba.

01:29:41.340 --> 01:29:47.400
And it came to pass, after these things, that it was told Abraham, saying, Behold, Milka,

01:29:47.520 --> 01:29:54.860
she hath also borne children unto thy brother Nahor, whose his first-born, and Boz his brother,

01:29:54.860 --> 01:30:03.240
and Chemuel the father of Aram, and Chesed, and Hazo, and Pildash, and Jidlaf, and Bethuel.

01:30:04.220 --> 01:30:10.480
And Bethuel begat Rebekah. These eight Milka did bear to Nahor, Abraham's brother.

01:30:11.620 --> 01:30:18.980
And his concubine, whose name was Ruma, she bore also Tiba, and Gaham, and Thehash, and

01:30:18.980 --> 01:30:19.500
Meika.

01:30:23.640 --> 01:30:28.860
And Sarah was one hundred and seven and twenty years old. These were the years of the life

01:30:28.860 --> 01:30:29.580
of Sarah.

01:30:30.380 --> 01:30:37.000
And Sarah died in Kirjath Arba, the same as Hebron in the land of Canaan. And Abraham came

01:30:37.000 --> 01:30:39.560
to mourn for Sarah, and to weep for her.

01:30:40.500 --> 01:30:46.560
And Abraham stood up from before his dead, and spake unto the sons of Heth, saying, I

01:30:46.560 --> 01:30:52.260
am a stranger and a sojourner with you. Give me a possession of a burying place with you,

01:30:52.400 --> 01:30:55.100
that I may bury my dead out of my sight.

01:30:56.360 --> 01:31:02.460
And the children of Heth answered Abraham, saying unto him, Hear us, my lord, thou art

01:31:02.460 --> 01:31:08.500
a mighty prince among us. In the choice of our sepulchres bury thy dead. None of us shall

01:31:08.500 --> 01:31:12.840
withhold from thee his sepulcher, but that thou mayest bury thy dead.

01:31:13.580 --> 01:31:18.960
And Abraham stood up and bowed himself to the people of the land, even to the children

01:31:18.960 --> 01:31:25.160
of Heth. And he communed with them, saying, If it be your mind that I should bury my dead

01:31:25.160 --> 01:31:31.500
out of my sight, hear me, and entreat for me, to Ephraim the son of Zohar, that he may

01:31:31.500 --> 01:31:37.760
give me the cave of Machpila, which he hath, which is in the end of his field. For as much

01:31:37.760 --> 01:31:43.080
money as it is worth he shall give it me for a possession of a burying place amongst you.

01:31:44.060 --> 01:31:49.120
And Ephraim dwelt among the children of Heth, and Ephraim the Hittite answered Abraham in

01:31:49.120 --> 01:31:53.940
the audience of the children of Heth, even of all that went in at the gate of his city,

01:31:54.240 --> 01:32:01.320
saying, Nay, my lord, hear me. The field give I thee, and the cave that is therein I give

01:32:01.320 --> 01:32:07.100
thee, in the presence of the sons of my people give I thee, bury thy dead.

01:32:08.160 --> 01:32:14.220
And Abraham bowed down himself before the people of the land, and he spake unto Ephraim

01:32:14.220 --> 01:32:19.760
in the audience of the people of the land, saying, But if thou wilt give it, I pray thee,

01:32:20.100 --> 01:32:26.360
hear me, I will give thee money for the field, take it of me, and I will bury my dead there.

01:32:27.420 --> 01:32:33.760
And Ephraim answered Abraham, saying unto him, My lord, hearken unto me. The land is

01:32:33.760 --> 01:32:39.340
worth four hundred shekels of silver. What is that betwixt me and thee? Bury therefore

01:32:39.340 --> 01:32:39.920
thy dead.

01:32:41.020 --> 01:32:46.340
And Abraham hearkened unto Ephraim, and Abraham weighed to Ephraim the silver which he had

01:32:46.340 --> 01:32:51.900
named in the audience of the sons of Heth, four hundred shekels of silver, current money

01:32:51.900 --> 01:32:52.760
with the merchant.

01:32:54.020 --> 01:32:59.760
And the field of Ephraim, which was in Machpelah, which was before Mamrie, the field and the

01:32:59.760 --> 01:33:04.460
cave which was therein, and all the trees that were in the field, that were in all the

01:33:04.460 --> 01:33:10.080
borders round about, were made sure unto Abraham for a possession in the presence of the children

01:33:10.080 --> 01:33:13.640
of Heth before all that went in at the gate of his city.

01:33:14.740 --> 01:33:20.860
And after this Abraham buried Sarah his wife in the cave of the field of Machpelah, before

01:33:20.860 --> 01:33:27.140
Mamrie, the same as Hebron in the land of Canaan. And the field and the cave that is

01:33:27.140 --> 01:33:32.760
therein were made sure unto Abraham for a possession of a burying place by the sons

01:33:32.760 --> 01:33:33.480
of Heth.

01:34:06.440 --> 01:34:12.820
And Abraham was old and well stricken in age, and the LORD had blessed Abraham in all things.

01:34:13.800 --> 01:34:19.100
And Abraham said unto his eldest servant of his house, that ruled over all that he had,

01:34:19.680 --> 01:34:25.180
Put, I pray thee, thy hand under my thigh, and I will make thee swear by the LORD, the

01:34:25.180 --> 01:34:30.820
God of heaven, and the God of the earth, that thou shalt not take a wife unto my son of

01:34:30.820 --> 01:34:36.540
the daughters of the Canaanites, among whom I dwell, but thou shalt go unto my country,

01:34:36.760 --> 01:34:40.400
and to my kindred, and take a wife unto my son Isaac.

01:34:41.360 --> 01:34:46.200
And the servant said unto him, Peradventure the woman will not be willing to follow me

01:34:46.200 --> 01:34:51.740
unto this land, must I need to bring thy son again unto the land from whence thou camest.

01:34:52.600 --> 01:34:57.960
And Abraham said unto him, Beware thou that thou bring not my son thither again.

01:34:58.760 --> 01:35:03.960
The LORD God of heaven, which took me from my father's house, and from the land of my

01:35:03.960 --> 01:35:09.440
kindred, and which spake unto me, and that swear unto me, saying, Unto thy seed will

01:35:09.440 --> 01:35:15.040
I give this land, he shall send his angel before thee, and thou shalt take a wife unto

01:35:15.040 --> 01:35:16.600
my son from thence.

01:35:17.240 --> 01:35:22.080
And if the woman will not be willing to follow thee, then thou shalt be clear from this my

01:35:22.080 --> 01:35:24.980
oath, only bring not my son thither again.

01:35:25.600 --> 01:35:31.100
And the servant put his hand under the thigh of Abraham his master, and sweared to him

01:35:31.100 --> 01:35:32.320
concerning that matter.

01:35:33.740 --> 01:35:39.500
And the servant took ten camels of the camels of his master, and departed, for all the goods

01:35:39.500 --> 01:35:46.340
of his master were in his hand, and he arose and went to Mesopotamia unto the city of Nahor.

01:35:47.100 --> 01:35:52.640
And he made his camels to kneel down without the city by a well of water at the time of

01:35:52.640 --> 01:35:56.300
the evening, even the time that women go out to draw water.

01:35:57.280 --> 01:36:04.080
And he said, O LORD God of my master Abraham, I pray thee, send me good speed this day,

01:36:04.420 --> 01:36:07.040
and show kindness unto my master Abraham.

01:36:08.260 --> 01:36:13.140
Behold I stand here by the well of water, and the daughters of the men of the city come

01:36:13.140 --> 01:36:14.420
out to draw water.

01:36:15.060 --> 01:36:20.580
And let it come to pass, that the damsel to whom I shall say, Let down thy pitcher, I

01:36:20.580 --> 01:36:22.060
pray thee, that I may drink.

01:36:22.480 --> 01:36:26.920
And she shall say, Drink, and I will give thy camels drink also.

01:36:27.640 --> 01:36:33.200
Let the same be she that thou hast appointed for thy servant Isaac, and thereby shall

01:36:33.200 --> 01:36:36.580
I know that thou hast showed kindness unto my master.

01:36:37.880 --> 01:36:44.120
And it came to pass, before he had done speaking, that behold Rebecca came out, who was born

01:36:44.880 --> 01:36:50.440
of Milka, the wife of Nahor, Abraham's brother, with her pitcher upon her shoulder.

01:36:51.720 --> 01:36:57.340
And the damsel was very fair to look upon, a virgin, neither had any man known her.

01:36:57.620 --> 01:37:01.640
And she went down to the well, and filled her pitcher, and came up.

01:37:02.640 --> 01:37:07.740
And the servant ran to meet her, and said, Let me, I pray thee, drink a little water

01:37:07.740 --> 01:37:08.560
of thy pitcher.

01:37:09.160 --> 01:37:11.580
And she said, Drink, my lord.

01:37:11.880 --> 01:37:16.460
And she hasted, and let down her pitcher upon her hand, and gave him drink.

01:37:17.560 --> 01:37:22.760
And when she had done giving him drink, she said, I will draw water for thy camels also,

01:37:23.080 --> 01:37:24.420
until they have done drinking.

01:37:25.320 --> 01:37:30.400
And she hasted, and emptied her pitcher into the trough, and ran again unto the well to

01:37:30.400 --> 01:37:33.280
draw water, and drew for all his camels.

01:37:34.140 --> 01:37:39.560
And the man wondering at her held his peace, to wit whether the lord had made his journey

01:37:39.560 --> 01:37:41.000
prosperous or not.

01:37:42.000 --> 01:37:46.900
And it came to pass, as the camels had done drinking, that the man took a golden earring

01:37:46.900 --> 01:37:52.020
of half a shekel weight, and two bracelets for her hands of ten shekels weight of gold,

01:37:52.520 --> 01:37:54.760
and said, Whose daughter art thou?

01:37:55.080 --> 01:37:59.720
Tell me, I pray thee, is there room in thy father's house for us to lodge in?

01:38:00.320 --> 01:38:05.540
And she said unto him, I am the daughter of Bethuel, the son of Milka, which she bear

01:38:05.540 --> 01:38:06.500
unto Nahor.

01:38:07.160 --> 01:38:13.500
She said moreover unto him, We have both straw and provender enough, and room to lodge in.

01:38:14.620 --> 01:38:17.760
And the man bowed down his head, and worshipped the lord.

01:38:18.280 --> 01:38:24.060
And he said, Blessed be the lord God of my master Abraham, who hath not left destitute

01:38:24.060 --> 01:38:30.400
my master of his mercy and his truth, I being in the way, the lord led me to the house of

01:38:30.400 --> 01:38:31.560
my master's brethren.

01:38:32.640 --> 01:38:36.840
And the damsel ran, and told them of her mother's house these things.

01:38:38.380 --> 01:38:43.900
And Rebecca had a brother, and his name was Laban, and Laban ran out unto the man, unto

01:38:43.900 --> 01:38:44.460
the well.

01:38:45.300 --> 01:38:50.500
And it came to pass, when he saw the earring and bracelets upon his sister's hands, and

01:38:50.500 --> 01:38:56.060
he heard the words of Rebecca his sister, saying, Thus spake the man unto me, that he

01:38:56.060 --> 01:38:59.860
came unto the man, and behold he stood by the camels at the well.

01:39:00.600 --> 01:39:05.340
And he said, Come in thou blessed of the lord, wherefore standest thou without?

01:39:05.720 --> 01:39:08.460
For I have prepared the house, and room for the camels.

01:39:09.300 --> 01:39:14.860
And the man came into the house, and he unguarded his camels, and gave straw and provender for

01:39:14.860 --> 01:39:19.740
the camels, and water to wash his feet, and the men's feet that were with him.

01:39:20.840 --> 01:39:26.340
And there was set meat before him to eat, but he said, I will not eat until I have told

01:39:26.340 --> 01:39:27.020
mine errand.

01:39:27.580 --> 01:39:29.220
And he said, Speak on.

01:39:29.860 --> 01:39:35.940
And he said, I am Abraham's servant, and the lord hath blessed my master greatly, and he

01:39:35.940 --> 01:39:41.900
is become great, and he hath given him flocks, and herds, and silver, and gold, and men's

01:39:41.900 --> 01:39:45.560
servants, and maidservants, and camels, and asses.

01:39:45.980 --> 01:39:51.780
And Sarah, my master's wife, bare a son to my master, when she was old, and unto him

01:39:51.780 --> 01:39:53.540
hath he given all that he hath.

01:39:54.240 --> 01:39:59.940
And my master made me swear, saying, Thou shalt not take a wife to my son of the daughters

01:39:59.940 --> 01:40:05.680
of the Canaanites, in whose land I dwell, but thou shalt go unto my father's house,

01:40:05.940 --> 01:40:09.020
and to my kindred, and take a wife unto my son.

01:40:09.770 --> 01:40:14.100
And I said unto my master, Peradventure, the woman will not follow me.

01:40:14.640 --> 01:40:20.160
And he said unto me, The lord before whom I walk will send his angel with thee, and

01:40:20.160 --> 01:40:26.160
prosper thy way, and thou shalt take a wife for my son of my kindred, and of my father's

01:40:26.160 --> 01:40:26.580
house.

01:40:27.280 --> 01:40:32.440
Then shalt thou be clear from this my oath, when thou comest to my kindred, and if they

01:40:32.440 --> 01:40:35.560
give not thee one, thou shalt be clear from my oath.

01:40:36.100 --> 01:40:42.700
And I came this day unto the well, and said, O Lord God of my master Abraham, if now thou

01:40:42.700 --> 01:40:48.860
do prosper my way which I go, behold, I stand by the well of water, and it shall come to

01:40:48.860 --> 01:40:54.580
pass that when the Virgin cometh forth to draw water, and I say to her, Give me, I pray

01:40:54.580 --> 01:41:00.460
thee, a little water of thy pitcher to drink, and she say to me, Both drink thou, and I

01:41:00.460 --> 01:41:05.560
will also draw for thy camels, let the same be the woman whom the Lord hath appointed

01:41:05.560 --> 01:41:07.200
out for my master's son.

01:41:08.000 --> 01:41:13.460
And before I had done speaking in mine heart, behold, Rebecca came forth with her pitcher

01:41:13.460 --> 01:41:19.020
on her shoulder, and she went down unto the well, and drew water, and I said unto her,

01:41:19.240 --> 01:41:24.580
Let me drink, I pray thee, and she made haste, and let down her pitcher from her shoulder,

01:41:25.000 --> 01:41:28.480
and said, Drink, and I will give thy camels drink also.

01:41:29.000 --> 01:41:32.060
So I drank, and she made the camels drink also.

01:41:32.700 --> 01:41:35.760
And I asked her, and said, Whose daughter art thou?

01:41:36.000 --> 01:41:42.280
And she said, The daughter of Bethuel, Nahor's son, whom Milka bear unto him, and I put the

01:41:42.280 --> 01:41:45.660
earring upon her face, and the bracelets upon her hands.

01:41:46.360 --> 01:41:51.580
And I bowed down my head, and worshipped the Lord, and blessed the Lord God of my master

01:41:51.580 --> 01:41:56.780
Abraham, which had led me in the right way to take my master's brother's daughter unto

01:41:56.780 --> 01:41:57.380
his son.

01:41:58.500 --> 01:42:04.180
And now, if ye will deal kindly and truly with my master, tell me, and if not, tell

01:42:04.180 --> 01:42:07.760
me, that I may turn to the right hand, or to the left.

01:42:08.880 --> 01:42:14.500
Then Laban and Bethuel answered, and said, The thing proceedeth from the Lord, we cannot

01:42:14.500 --> 01:42:16.240
speak unto thee bad or good.

01:42:17.400 --> 01:42:23.160
Behold Rebecca is before thee, take her and go, and let her be thy master's son's wife,

01:42:23.440 --> 01:42:24.780
as the Lord hath spoken.

01:42:25.940 --> 01:42:30.980
And it came to pass that when Abraham's servant heard their words, he worshipped the Lord

01:42:30.980 --> 01:42:32.800
bowing himself to the earth.

01:42:33.580 --> 01:42:38.860
And the servant brought forth jewels of silver and jewels of gold and raiment, and gave them

01:42:38.860 --> 01:42:43.900
to Rebecca, and he gave also to her brother and to her mother precious things.

01:42:44.780 --> 01:42:49.620
And they did eat and drink, he and the men that were with him, and tarried all night.

01:42:49.920 --> 01:42:54.460
And they rose up in the morning, and he said, Send me away unto my master.

01:42:55.540 --> 01:43:00.980
And her brother and her mother said, Let the damsel abide with us a few days, at the least

01:43:00.980 --> 01:43:03.220
ten, after that she shall go.

01:43:04.040 --> 01:43:10.060
And he said unto them, Hinder me not, seeing the Lord hath prospered my way, send me away

01:43:10.060 --> 01:43:11.680
that I may go to my master.

01:43:12.520 --> 01:43:16.580
And they said, We will call the damsel and inquire at her mouth.

01:43:16.580 --> 01:43:21.460
And they called Rebecca, and said unto her, Wilt thou go with this man?

01:43:21.720 --> 01:43:23.640
And she said, I will go.

01:43:24.540 --> 01:43:29.100
And they sent away Rebecca, their sister, and her nurse, and Abraham's servant, and

01:43:29.100 --> 01:43:29.660
his men.

01:43:30.680 --> 01:43:35.920
And they blessed Rebecca, and said unto her, Thou art our sister, be thou the mother of

01:43:35.920 --> 01:43:40.900
thousands of millions, and let thy seed possess the gate of those which hate them.

01:43:41.800 --> 01:43:47.300
And Rebecca arose, and her damsels, and they rode upon the camels, and followed the man,

01:43:47.640 --> 01:43:50.400
and the servant took Rebecca, and went his way.

01:43:51.620 --> 01:43:56.480
And Isaac came from the way of the well Lehi Roy, for he dwelt in the south country.

01:43:57.300 --> 01:44:02.060
And Isaac went out to meditate in the field at the even tide, and he lifted up his eyes,

01:44:02.100 --> 01:44:04.700
and saw, and behold, the camels were coming.

01:44:05.520 --> 01:44:10.620
And Rebecca lifted up her eyes, and when she saw Isaac she lighted off the camel.

01:44:11.420 --> 01:44:15.960
For she had said unto the servant, What man is this that walketh in the field to meet

01:44:15.960 --> 01:44:16.440
us?

01:44:16.800 --> 01:44:22.240
And the servant had said, It is my master, therefore she took a veil and covered herself.

01:44:23.340 --> 01:44:26.100
And the servant told Isaac all things that he had done.

01:44:26.860 --> 01:44:32.060
And Isaac brought her into his mother Sarah's tent, and took Rebecca, and she became his

01:44:32.060 --> 01:44:37.100
wife, and he loved her, and Isaac was comforted after his mother's death.

01:44:41.660 --> 01:44:45.900
Then again Abraham took a wife, and her name was Keturah.

01:44:46.380 --> 01:44:52.700
And she bare him Zimran, and Jokshin, and Medan, and Midian, and Ishbak, and Shua.

01:44:53.700 --> 01:44:56.220
And Jokshin begat Sheba, and Dedan.

01:44:56.780 --> 01:45:01.160
And the sons of Dedan were Ashurim, and Latushim, and Leumim.

01:45:01.720 --> 01:45:08.220
And the sons of Midian, Ephah, and Ephur, and Hanak, and Abida, and Eldayah.

01:45:09.380 --> 01:45:11.700
All these were the children of Keturah.

01:45:12.900 --> 01:45:15.520
And Abraham gave all that he had unto Isaac.

01:45:16.420 --> 01:45:21.560
But unto the sons of the concubines, which Abraham had, Abraham gave gifts, and sent

01:45:21.560 --> 01:45:26.720
them away from Isaac his son, while he yet lived, eastward, unto the east country.

01:45:27.820 --> 01:45:33.140
And these were the days of the years of Abraham's life which he lived, and a hundred threescore,

01:45:33.280 --> 01:45:34.400
and fifteen years.

01:45:35.880 --> 01:45:41.700
Then Abraham gave up the ghost, and died in a good old age, an old man, and full of years,

01:45:42.020 --> 01:45:43.660
and was gathered to his people.

01:45:44.980 --> 01:45:49.640
And his sons Isaac and Ishmael buried him in the cave of Machpelah, in the field of

01:45:49.640 --> 01:45:55.720
Ephron the son of Zohar the Hittite, which is before Mamre, the field which Abraham purchased

01:45:55.720 --> 01:45:56.900
unto the sons of Heth.

01:45:57.320 --> 01:46:00.500
There was Abraham buried, and Sarah his wife.

01:46:02.000 --> 01:46:07.940
And it came to pass, after the death of Abraham, that God blessed his son Isaac, and Isaac

01:46:07.940 --> 01:46:09.720
dwelt by the well Lehi Roy.

01:46:10.880 --> 01:46:16.400
Now these are the generations of Ishmael, Abraham's son, whom Hagar the Egyptian, Sarah's

01:46:16.400 --> 01:46:18.560
handmaid, bare unto Abraham.

01:46:19.440 --> 01:46:24.460
And these are the names of the sons of Ishmael, by their names, according to their generations,

01:46:24.980 --> 01:46:32.260
the firstborn of Ishmael, Nebejeth, and Kedar, and Adbeel, and Mibsum, and Mishma, and Duma,

01:46:32.560 --> 01:46:38.180
and Massa, Hader, and Tima, Jeter, Nefesh, and Kedema.

01:46:38.760 --> 01:46:43.260
These are the sons of Ishmael, and these are their names, by their towns, and by their

01:46:43.260 --> 01:46:46.720
castles, twelve princes according to their nations.

01:46:47.840 --> 01:46:52.640
And these are the years of the life of Ishmael, and a hundred and thirty and seven years,

01:46:52.640 --> 01:46:56.720
and he gave up the ghost, and died, and was gathered unto his people.

01:46:57.740 --> 01:47:03.600
And they dwelt from Havilah unto Shur, that is, before Egypt, as thou goest toward Assyria,

01:47:03.980 --> 01:47:06.360
and he died in the presence of all his brethren.

01:47:08.000 --> 01:47:11.200
And these are the generations of Isaac, Abraham's son.

01:47:11.780 --> 01:47:17.620
Abraham begat Isaac, and Isaac was forty years old when he took Rebekah to wife, the daughter

01:47:17.620 --> 01:47:22.700
of Bethuel, the Syrian, of Paedon Aram, the sister to Laban, the Syrian.

01:47:23.720 --> 01:47:29.120
And Isaac entreated the Lord for his wife, because she was barren, and the Lord was entreated

01:47:29.120 --> 01:47:31.620
of him, and Rebekah his wife conceived.

01:47:32.400 --> 01:47:38.460
And the children struggled together within her, and she said, If it be so, why am I thus?

01:47:38.780 --> 01:47:40.900
And she went to inquire of the Lord.

01:47:41.740 --> 01:47:46.920
And the Lord said unto her, Two nations are in thy womb, and two manner of people shall

01:47:46.920 --> 01:47:51.980
be separated from thy bowels, and the one people shall be stronger than the other people,

01:47:52.280 --> 01:47:54.080
and the elder shall serve the younger.

01:47:55.220 --> 01:48:00.060
And when her days to be delivered were fulfilled, behold, there were twins in her womb.

01:48:00.780 --> 01:48:06.040
And the first came out red, all over like an hairy garment, and they called his name

01:48:06.040 --> 01:48:06.680
Esau.

01:48:07.300 --> 01:48:13.120
And after that came his brother out, and his hand took hold on Esau's heel, and his name

01:48:13.120 --> 01:48:17.700
was called Jacob, and Isaac was three score years old when she bare them.

01:48:18.860 --> 01:48:24.500
And the boys grew, and Esau was a cunning hunter, a man of the field, and Jacob was

01:48:24.500 --> 01:48:26.520
a plain man, dwelling in tents.

01:48:27.480 --> 01:48:32.840
And Isaac loved Esau because he did eat of his venison, but Rebekah loved Jacob.

01:48:33.820 --> 01:48:39.980
And Jacob sawed pottage, and Esau came from the field, and he was faint, and Esau said

01:48:39.980 --> 01:48:46.360
to Jacob, Feed me, I pray thee, with that same red pottage, for I am faint. Therefore

01:48:46.360 --> 01:48:47.940
his name was called Edom.

01:48:48.960 --> 01:48:52.340
And Jacob said, Sell me this day thy birthright.

01:48:53.100 --> 01:48:58.640
And Esau said, Behold, I am at the point to die, and what profit shall this birthright

01:48:58.640 --> 01:48:59.480
do to me?

01:48:59.920 --> 01:49:02.840
And Jacob said, Swear to me this day.

01:49:03.180 --> 01:49:06.960
And he swear unto him, and he sold his birthright unto Jacob.

01:49:07.820 --> 01:49:13.380
Then Jacob gave Esau bread and pottage of lentils, and he did eat and drink, and rose

01:49:13.380 --> 01:49:17.740
up and went his way. Thus Esau despised his birthright.

01:49:21.760 --> 01:49:26.420
And there was a famine in the land beside the first famine that was in the days of Abraham,

01:49:27.060 --> 01:49:32.900
and Isaac went unto Abimelek, king of the Philistines, unto Gerar. And the Lord appeared

01:49:32.900 --> 01:49:38.420
unto him, and said, Go not down into Egypt, dwell in the land which I shall tell thee

01:49:38.420 --> 01:49:44.520
of. Sojourn in this land, and I will be with thee, and will bless thee. For unto thee,

01:49:44.600 --> 01:49:50.280
and unto thy seed, I will give all these countries, and I will perform the oath which I swear

01:49:50.280 --> 01:49:56.840
unto Abraham thy father. And I will make thy seed to multiply as the stars of heaven, and

01:49:56.840 --> 01:50:02.260
will give unto thy seed all these countries. And in thy seed shall all the nations of the

01:50:02.260 --> 01:50:08.760
earth be blessed, because that Abraham obeyed my voice, and kept my charge, my commandments,

01:50:09.120 --> 01:50:11.180
my statutes, and my laws.

01:50:12.320 --> 01:50:17.940
And Isaac dwelt in Gerar, and the men of the place asked him of his wife, and he said,

01:50:18.220 --> 01:50:24.620
She is my sister, for he feared to say, She is my wife, lest, said he, the men of the

01:50:24.620 --> 01:50:30.700
place should kill me for Rebekah, because she was fair to look upon. And it came to

01:50:30.700 --> 01:50:36.320
he had been there a long time, that Abimelech, king of the Philistines, looked out at a window,

01:50:36.700 --> 01:50:43.580
and saw, and behold, Isaac was sporting with Rebekah his wife. And Abimelech called Isaac,

01:50:43.700 --> 01:50:49.860
and said, Behold, of assurity, she is thy wife, and how saidst thou, She is my sister?

01:50:50.480 --> 01:50:57.520
And Isaac said unto him, Because I said, lest I die for her. And Abimelech said, What is

01:50:57.520 --> 01:51:02.700
this thou hast done unto us? One of the people might lightly have lied with thy wife, and

01:51:02.700 --> 01:51:07.880
thou shouldest have brought guiltiness upon us. And Abimelech charged all his people,

01:51:08.100 --> 01:51:14.940
saying, He that toucheth this man or his wife shall surely be put to death. Then Isaac sowed

01:51:14.940 --> 01:51:19.720
in that land, and received in the same year and hundredfold, and the Lord blessed him.

01:51:20.120 --> 01:51:26.080
And the man waxed great, and went forward, and grew until he became very great, for he

01:51:26.080 --> 01:51:31.100
had possession of flocks, and possession of herds, and great store of servants, and

01:51:31.100 --> 01:51:36.300
the Philistines envied him. For all the wells which his father's servants had digged in

01:51:36.300 --> 01:51:41.420
the days of Abraham his father, the Philistines had stopped them, and filled them with earth.

01:51:42.480 --> 01:51:49.480
And Abimelech said unto Isaac, Go from us, for thou art much mightier than we. And Isaac

01:51:49.480 --> 01:51:54.320
departed thence, and pitched his tent in the valley of Girhar, and dwelt there.

01:51:55.200 --> 01:51:59.920
And Isaac digged again the wells of water which they had digged in the days of Abraham

01:51:59.920 --> 01:52:05.420
his father, for the Philistines had stopped them after the death of Abraham, and he called

01:52:05.420 --> 01:52:11.480
their names after the names by which his father had called them. And Isaac's servants digged

01:52:11.480 --> 01:52:17.840
in the valley, and found there a well of springing water. And the herdmen of Girhar did strive

01:52:17.840 --> 01:52:23.780
with Isaac's herdmen, saying, The water is ours. And he called the name of the well Esek,

01:52:23.780 --> 01:52:30.320
because they strove with him. And they digged another well, and strove for that also, and

01:52:30.320 --> 01:52:36.080
he called the name of it Sitna. And he removed from thence, and digged another well, and

01:52:36.080 --> 01:52:41.660
for that they strove not. And he called the name of it Rehoboth, and he said, For now

01:52:41.660 --> 01:52:47.240
the Lord hath made room for us, and we shall be fruitful in the land. And he went up from

01:52:47.240 --> 01:52:53.480
thence to Beersheba. And the Lord appeared unto him the same night, and said, I am the

01:52:53.480 --> 01:52:59.620
God of Abraham, thy father. Fear not, for I am with thee, and will bless thee, and multiply

01:52:59.620 --> 01:53:05.780
thy seed for my servant Abraham's sake. And he built an altar there, and called upon the

01:53:05.780 --> 01:53:11.000
name of the Lord, and pitched his tent there, and there Isaac's servants digged a well.

01:53:12.700 --> 01:53:18.460
Then Abimlek went to him from Girhar, and Ahazeth, one of his friends, and Phicol, the

01:53:18.460 --> 01:53:25.040
captain of his army. And Isaac said unto them, Wherefore come ye to me, seeing ye hate me,

01:53:25.080 --> 01:53:31.160
and have sent me away from you? And they said, We saw certainly that the Lord was with thee,

01:53:31.340 --> 01:53:37.220
and we said, Let there be now an oath betwixt us, even betwixt us and thee, and let us

01:53:37.220 --> 01:53:42.420
make a covenant with thee, that thou wilt do us no hurt, as we have not touched thee,

01:53:42.640 --> 01:53:47.760
and as we have done unto thee nothing but good, and have sent thee away in peace. Thou

01:53:47.760 --> 01:53:53.480
art now the blessed of the Lord. And he made them a feast, and they did eat and drink.

01:53:53.980 --> 01:53:59.080
And they rose up at times in the morning, and swear one to another, and Isaac sent them

01:53:59.080 --> 01:54:05.500
away, and they departed from him in peace. And it came to pass the same day that Isaac's

01:54:05.500 --> 01:54:10.100
servants came, and told him concerning the well which they had digged, and said unto

01:54:10.100 --> 01:54:16.900
him, We have found water. And he called it Sheba, therefore the name of the city is Beersheba

01:54:16.900 --> 01:54:23.820
unto this day. And Esau was forty years old when he took to wife Judith the daughter of

01:54:23.820 --> 01:54:30.220
Berei the Hittite, and Bashameth the daughter of Elan the Hittite, which were a grief of

01:54:30.220 --> 01:54:33.520
mind unto Isaac and to Rebekah.

01:54:36.500 --> 01:54:41.360
And it came to pass that when Isaac was old, and his eyes were dim, so that he could not

01:54:42.040 --> 01:54:48.940
he called Esau his eldest son, and said unto him, My son, and he said unto him, Behold,

01:54:49.040 --> 01:54:56.960
here am I. And he said, Behold now, I am old, and I know not the day of my death. Now therefore

01:54:56.960 --> 01:55:02.100
take, I pray thee, thy weapons, thy quiver, and thy bow, and go out to the field, and

01:55:02.100 --> 01:55:07.800
take me some venison, and make me savoury meat such as I love, and bring it to me that

01:55:07.800 --> 01:55:11.760
I may eat, that my soul may bless thee before I die.

01:55:12.920 --> 01:55:18.840
And Rebekah heard when Isaac spake to Esau his son, and Esau went to the field to hunt

01:55:18.840 --> 01:55:20.560
for venison, and to bring it.

01:55:21.700 --> 01:55:28.020
And Rebekah spake unto Jacob her son, saying, Behold, I heard thy father speak unto Esau

01:55:28.020 --> 01:55:33.900
thy brother, saying, Bring me venison, and make me savoury meat that I may eat, and bless

01:55:33.900 --> 01:55:40.120
thee before the Lord before my death. Now therefore, my son, obey my voice according

01:55:40.120 --> 01:55:46.600
to that which I command thee. Go now to the flock, and fetch me from thence two good kids

01:55:46.600 --> 01:55:52.380
of the goats, and I will make them savoury meat for thy father such as he loveth, and

01:55:52.380 --> 01:55:56.900
thou shalt bring it to thy father that he may eat, and that he may bless thee before

01:55:56.900 --> 01:55:57.660
his death.

01:55:58.360 --> 01:56:04.920
And Jacob said to Rebekah his mother, Behold, Esau my brother is a hairy man, and I am a

01:56:04.920 --> 01:56:10.740
smooth man. My father peradventure will feel me, and I shall seem to him as a deceiver,

01:56:11.180 --> 01:56:14.000
and I shall bring a curse upon me, and not a blessing.

01:56:14.920 --> 01:56:21.220
And his mother said unto him, Upon me be thy curse, my son, only obey my voice, and go

01:56:21.220 --> 01:56:21.940
fetch me them.

01:56:22.520 --> 01:56:27.900
And he went and fetched and brought them to his mother, and his mother made savoury meat

01:56:27.900 --> 01:56:34.720
such as his father loved. And Rebekah took goodly raiment of her eldest son Esau, which

01:56:34.720 --> 01:56:40.380
were with her in the house, and put them upon Jacob, her younger son. And she put the skins

01:56:40.380 --> 01:56:45.660
of the kids of the goats upon his hands, and upon the smooth of his neck, and she gave

01:56:45.660 --> 01:56:51.080
the savoury meat and the bread which she had prepared into the hand of her son Jacob.

01:56:52.240 --> 01:56:59.480
And he came unto his father and said, My father, and he said, Here am I, who art thou my son?

01:57:00.020 --> 01:57:05.820
And Jacob said unto his father, I am Esau thy first born, I have done according as thou

01:57:05.820 --> 01:57:12.120
batest me, arise, I pray thee, sit and eat of my venison, that thy soul may bless me.

01:57:12.760 --> 01:57:18.840
And Isaac said unto his son, How is it that thou hast found it so quickly, my son? And

01:57:18.840 --> 01:57:22.000
he said, Because the Lord thy God brought it to me.

01:57:22.880 --> 01:57:28.840
And Isaac said unto Jacob, Come near, I pray thee, that I may feel thee, my son, whether

01:57:28.840 --> 01:57:35.600
thou be my very son Esau or not. And Jacob went near unto Isaac his father, and he felt

01:57:35.600 --> 01:57:42.420
him, and said, The voice is Jacob's voice, but the hands are the hands of Esau. And

01:57:42.420 --> 01:57:47.740
he discerned him not, because his hands were hairy as his brother Esau's hands, so he

01:57:47.740 --> 01:57:56.400
blessed him. And he said, Art thou my very son Esau? And he said, I am. And he said,

01:57:56.720 --> 01:58:01.660
Bring it near to me, and I will eat of my son's venison, that my soul may bless thee.

01:58:02.140 --> 01:58:06.840
And he brought it near to him, and he did eat, and he brought him wine, and he drank.

01:58:07.900 --> 01:58:14.080
And his father Isaac said unto him, Come near now, and kiss me, my son. And he came near

01:58:14.080 --> 01:58:19.880
and kissed him, and he smelled the smell of his raiment, and blessed him, and said, See,

01:58:19.960 --> 01:58:26.040
the smell of my son is as the smell of a field which the Lord hath blessed. Therefore God

01:58:26.040 --> 01:58:31.340
give thee of the dew of heaven, and the fatness of the earth, and plenty of corn and wine.

01:58:32.100 --> 01:58:37.920
Let people serve thee, and nations bow down to thee. Be Lord over thy brethren, and let

01:58:37.920 --> 01:58:43.460
thy mother's sons bow down to thee. Cursed be every one that curseth thee, and blessed

01:58:43.460 --> 01:58:44.960
be he that blesseth thee.

01:58:45.980 --> 01:58:51.300
And it came to pass, as soon as Isaac had made an end of blessing Jacob, and Jacob was

01:58:51.300 --> 01:58:56.320
yet scarce gone out from the presence of Isaac his father, that Esau his brother came

01:58:56.320 --> 01:59:02.600
in from his hunting. And he also had made savoury meat, and brought it unto his father,

01:59:02.940 --> 01:59:08.760
and said unto his father, Let my father arise and eat of his son's venison, that thy soul

01:59:08.760 --> 01:59:16.860
may bless me. And Isaac his father said unto him, Who art thou? And he said, I am thy son,

01:59:16.860 --> 01:59:24.160
thy firstborn Esau. And Isaac trembled very exceedingly, and said, Who? Where is he that

01:59:24.160 --> 01:59:29.740
hath taken venison, and brought it me, and I have eaten of all before thou camest, and

01:59:29.740 --> 01:59:36.080
have blessed him? Yea, and he shall be blessed. And when Esau heard the words of his father,

01:59:36.420 --> 01:59:42.560
he cried with a great and exceeding bitter cry, and said unto his father, Bless me, even

01:59:42.560 --> 01:59:49.720
me also, O my father. And he said, Thy brother came with subtlety, and hath taken away thy

01:59:49.720 --> 01:59:56.520
blessing. And he said, Is not he rightly named Jacob? For he hath supplanted me these two

01:59:56.520 --> 02:00:03.540
times. He took away my birthright, and behold, now he hath taken away my blessing. And he

02:00:03.540 --> 02:00:09.900
said, Hast thou not reserved a blessing for me? And Isaac answered and said unto Esau,

02:00:10.480 --> 02:00:15.000
Behold, I have made him thy lord, and all his brethren have I given to him for servants,

02:00:15.480 --> 02:00:20.480
and with corn and wine have I sustained him. And what shall I do now unto thee, my son?

02:00:21.100 --> 02:00:27.720
And Esau said unto his father, Hast thou but one blessing, my father? Bless me, even me

02:00:27.720 --> 02:00:34.740
also, O my father. And Esau lifted up his voice and wept. And Isaac his father answered

02:00:34.740 --> 02:00:40.200
and said unto him, Behold, thy dwelling shall be the fatness of the earth and of the dew

02:00:40.200 --> 02:00:46.260
of heaven from above, and by thy sword shalt thou live, and shalt serve thy brother, and

02:00:46.260 --> 02:00:50.900
it shall come to pass, when thou shalt have the dominion, that thou shalt break his yoke

02:00:50.900 --> 02:00:57.560
from off thy neck. And Esau hated Jacob because of the blessing wherewith his father blessed

02:00:57.560 --> 02:01:04.040
him. And Esau said in his heart, The days of mourning for my father are at hand. Then

02:01:04.040 --> 02:01:10.680
I will slay my brother Jacob. And these words of Esau, her elder son, were told to Rebecca,

02:01:11.360 --> 02:01:16.920
and she sent and called Jacob her younger son, and said unto him, Behold, thy brother

02:01:16.920 --> 02:01:23.440
Esau, as touching thee, doth comfort himself, purposing to kill thee. Now therefore, my

02:01:23.440 --> 02:01:30.100
son, obey my voice, and arise, flee thou to Laban, my brother, to Heron, and tarry with

02:01:30.100 --> 02:01:35.760
him a few days, until thy brother's fury turn away, until thy brother's anger turn

02:01:35.760 --> 02:01:41.300
away from thee, and he forget that which thou hast done to him. Then I will send and fetch

02:01:41.300 --> 02:01:46.280
thee from thence. Why should I be deprived also of you both in one day?

02:01:47.580 --> 02:01:53.380
And Rebecca said to Isaac, I am weary of my life because of the daughters of Heth. If

02:01:53.380 --> 02:01:57.920
Jacob take a wife of the daughters of Heth, such as these which are of the daughters of

02:01:57.920 --> 02:02:00.960
land, what good shall my life do me?

02:02:33.320 --> 02:02:38.860
An Isaac called Jacob, and blessed him, and charged him, and said unto him, Thou shalt

02:02:38.860 --> 02:02:41.400
not take a wife of the daughters of Canaan.

02:02:42.580 --> 02:02:47.920
Arise, go to Paedon Aram, to the house of Bethuel, thy mother's father, and take thee

02:02:47.920 --> 02:02:51.260
a wife from thence, of the daughters of Laban, thy mother's brother.

02:02:51.980 --> 02:02:57.080
And God Almighty bless thee, and make thee fruitful, and multiply thee, that thou mayest

02:02:57.740 --> 02:03:04.260
of people, and give thee the blessing of Abraham, to thee and to thy seed with thee, that thou

02:03:04.260 --> 02:03:09.500
mayest inherit the land wherein thou art a stranger, which God gave unto Abraham.

02:03:10.620 --> 02:03:16.220
And Isaac sent away Jacob, and he went to Paedon Aram, unto Laban, son of Bethuel the

02:03:16.220 --> 02:03:20.060
Syrian, the brother of Rebekah, Jacob's and Esau's mother.

02:03:21.340 --> 02:03:26.440
When Esau saw that Isaac had blessed Jacob, and sent him away to Paedon Aram, to take

02:03:26.440 --> 02:03:32.140
him a wife from thence, and that as he blessed him, he gave him a charge, saying, Thou shalt

02:03:32.140 --> 02:03:37.560
not take a wife of the daughters of Canaan, and that Jacob obeyed his father and his mother,

02:03:37.800 --> 02:03:39.500
and was gone to Paedon Aram.

02:03:39.940 --> 02:03:45.840
And Esau, seeing that the daughters of Canaan pleased not Isaac his father, then went Esau

02:03:45.840 --> 02:03:51.820
unto Ishmael, and took unto the wives which he had, Maeleth the daughter of Ishmael, Abraham's

02:03:51.820 --> 02:03:55.160
son, the sister of Nebajeth, to be his wife.

02:03:56.280 --> 02:04:01.820
And Jacob went out from Beersheba, and went toward Haran, and he lighted upon a certain

02:04:01.820 --> 02:04:07.140
place, and tarried there all night, because the sun was set, and he took of the stones

02:04:07.140 --> 02:04:12.000
of that place, and put them for his pillows, and lay down in that place to sleep.

02:04:12.720 --> 02:04:18.320
And he dreamed, and behold a ladder set up on the earth, and the top of it reached to

02:04:18.320 --> 02:04:23.100
heaven, and behold the angels of God ascending and descending on it.

02:04:23.900 --> 02:04:30.400
And behold the Lord stood above it, and said, I am the Lord God of Abraham thy father, and

02:04:30.400 --> 02:04:37.320
the God of Isaac, the land whereon thou liest, to thee will I give it, and to thy seed, and

02:04:37.320 --> 02:04:42.120
thy seed shall be as the dust of the earth, and thou shalt spread abroad to the west,

02:04:42.300 --> 02:04:47.860
and to the east, and to the north, and to the south, and in thee and in thy seed shall

02:04:47.860 --> 02:04:50.160
all the families of the earth be blessed.

02:04:50.980 --> 02:04:56.520
And behold I am with thee, and will keep thee in all places whither thou goest, and will

02:04:56.520 --> 02:05:01.920
bring thee again into this land, for I will not leave thee until I have done that which

02:05:01.920 --> 02:05:03.580
I have spoken of to thee.

02:05:05.240 --> 02:05:10.980
And Jacob awaked out of his sleep, and he said, Surely the Lord is in this place, and

02:05:10.980 --> 02:05:11.940
I knew it not.

02:05:12.380 --> 02:05:15.920
And he was afraid, and said, How dreadful is this place!

02:05:15.920 --> 02:05:20.540
This is none other but the house of God, and this is the gate of heaven.

02:05:21.760 --> 02:05:26.780
And Jacob rose up early in the morning, and took the stone that he had put for his pillows,

02:05:27.240 --> 02:05:31.040
and set it up for a pillar, and poured oil upon the top of it.

02:05:31.740 --> 02:05:37.000
And he called the name of that place Bethel, but the name of that city was called Loz at

02:05:37.000 --> 02:05:37.660
the first.

02:05:38.720 --> 02:05:44.380
And Jacob vowed a vow, saying, If God will be with me, and will keep me in this way that

02:05:44.380 --> 02:05:49.880
I go, and will give me bread to eat, and raiment to put on, so that I come again to

02:05:49.880 --> 02:05:53.940
my father's house in peace, then shall the Lord be my God.

02:05:54.380 --> 02:05:59.700
And this stone, which I have set for a pillar, shall be God's house, and of all that thou

02:05:59.700 --> 02:06:03.220
shalt give me, I will surely give the tenth unto thee.

02:06:06.540 --> 02:06:11.500
Then Jacob went on his journey, and came into the land of the people of the east.

02:06:12.120 --> 02:06:17.440
And he looked, and behold a well in the field, and lo, there were three flocks of sheep

02:06:17.440 --> 02:06:23.420
lying by it, for out of that well they watered the flocks, and a great stone was upon the

02:06:23.420 --> 02:06:24.200
well's mouth.

02:06:24.780 --> 02:06:29.240
And thither were all the flocks gathered, and they rolled the stone from the well's

02:06:29.240 --> 02:06:34.480
mouth, and watered the sheep, and put the stone again upon the well's mouth in his place.

02:06:35.320 --> 02:06:39.200
And Jacob said unto them, My brethren, whence be ye?

02:06:39.440 --> 02:06:41.680
And they said, Of Heron are we.

02:06:42.280 --> 02:06:45.840
And he said unto them, Know ye Laban, the son of Nahor?

02:06:46.140 --> 02:06:47.960
And they said, We know him.

02:06:48.460 --> 02:06:50.640
And he said unto them, Is he well?

02:06:51.080 --> 02:06:56.060
And they said, He is well, and behold, Rachel, his daughter, cometh with the sheep.

02:06:56.840 --> 02:07:02.260
And he said, Lo, it is yet high day, neither is it time that the cattle should be gathered

02:07:02.260 --> 02:07:02.780
together.

02:07:03.460 --> 02:07:05.980
Water ye the sheep, and go, and feed them.

02:07:06.440 --> 02:07:11.720
And they said, We cannot, until all the flocks be gathered together, until they roll the

02:07:11.720 --> 02:07:14.800
stone from the well's mouth, then we water the sheep.

02:07:15.920 --> 02:07:21.140
And while he yet spake with them, Rachel came with her father's sheep, for she kept them.

02:07:22.000 --> 02:07:26.880
And it came to pass, when Jacob saw Rachel, the daughter of Laban, his mother's brother,

02:07:26.880 --> 02:07:32.200
and the sheep of Laban, his mother's brother, that Jacob went near, and rolled the stone

02:07:32.200 --> 02:07:36.400
from the well's mouth, and watered the flock of Laban, his mother's brother.

02:07:37.280 --> 02:07:41.460
And Jacob kissed Rachel, and lifted up his voice, and wept.

02:07:42.740 --> 02:07:47.600
And Jacob told Rachel that he was her father's brother, and that he was Rebekah's son.

02:07:47.760 --> 02:07:49.820
And she ran, and told her father.

02:07:50.880 --> 02:07:55.980
And it came to pass, when Laban heard the tidings of Jacob, his sister's son, that he

02:07:55.980 --> 02:08:00.560
ran to meet him, and embraced him, and kissed him, and brought him to his house.

02:08:00.940 --> 02:08:03.140
And he told Laban all these things.

02:08:04.000 --> 02:08:08.260
And Laban said to him, Surely thou art my bone and my flesh.

02:08:08.740 --> 02:08:11.180
And he abode with him the space of a month.

02:08:12.420 --> 02:08:17.460
And Laban said unto Jacob, Because thou art my brother, shouldest thou therefore serve

02:08:17.460 --> 02:08:20.800
me for naught, tell me, what shall thy wages be?

02:08:21.440 --> 02:08:23.400
And Laban had two daughters.

02:08:23.820 --> 02:08:27.680
The name of the elder was Leah, and the name of the younger was Rachel.

02:08:28.660 --> 02:08:32.860
Leah was tender-eyed, but Rachel was beautiful and well-favoured.

02:08:33.560 --> 02:08:39.760
And Jacob loved Rachel, and said, I will serve thee seven years for Rachel, thy younger daughter.

02:08:40.680 --> 02:08:45.780
And Laban said, It is better that I give her to thee, than that I should give her to another

02:08:45.780 --> 02:08:46.240
man.

02:08:46.620 --> 02:08:47.680
Abide with me.

02:08:48.220 --> 02:08:54.040
And Jacob served seven years for Rachel, and they seemed unto him but a few days for the

02:08:54.040 --> 02:08:55.320
love he had to her.

02:08:56.660 --> 02:09:02.500
And Jacob said unto Laban, Give me my wife, for my days are fulfilled, that I may go in

02:09:02.500 --> 02:09:03.260
unto her.

02:09:03.900 --> 02:09:07.780
And Laban gathered together all the men of the place, and made a feast.

02:09:08.700 --> 02:09:13.560
And it came to pass in the evening that he took Leah his daughter, and brought her to

02:09:13.560 --> 02:09:15.540
him, and he went in unto her.

02:09:16.230 --> 02:09:21.400
And Laban gave unto his daughter Leah Zilpah his maid for an handmaid.

02:09:21.680 --> 02:09:25.240
And it came to pass that in the morning, behold, it was Leah.

02:09:25.760 --> 02:09:29.220
And he said to Laban, What is this thou hast done unto me?

02:09:29.580 --> 02:09:31.660
Did not I serve with thee for Rachel?

02:09:32.240 --> 02:09:34.420
Wherefore then hast thou beguiled me?

02:09:35.280 --> 02:09:40.520
And Laban said, It must not be so done in our country, to give the younger before the

02:09:40.520 --> 02:09:41.180
first born.

02:09:41.900 --> 02:09:47.080
Fulfill her week, and we will give thee this also, for the service which thou shalt serve

02:09:47.080 --> 02:09:49.460
with me yet seven other years.

02:09:50.420 --> 02:09:55.540
And Jacob did so, and fulfilled her week, and he gave him Rachel his daughter to wife

02:09:55.540 --> 02:09:56.260
also.

02:09:57.480 --> 02:10:02.460
And Laban gave to Rachel his daughter Bilhah, his handmaid, to be her maid.

02:10:03.280 --> 02:10:09.200
And he went in also unto Rachel, and he loved also Rachel more than Leah, and served with

02:10:09.200 --> 02:10:11.040
him yet seven other years.

02:10:12.260 --> 02:10:17.380
And when the Lord saw that Leah was hated, he opened her womb, but Rachel was barren.

02:10:18.200 --> 02:10:24.220
And Leah conceived, and bear a son, and she called his name Reuben, for she said, Surely

02:10:24.220 --> 02:10:29.220
the Lord hath looked upon my affliction, now therefore my husband will love me.

02:10:30.060 --> 02:10:35.860
And she conceived again, and bear a son, and said, Because the Lord hath heard that I was

02:10:35.860 --> 02:10:39.620
hated, he hath therefore given me this son also.

02:10:39.780 --> 02:10:42.180
And she called his name Simeon.

02:10:42.600 --> 02:10:48.380
And she conceived again, and bear a son, and said, Now this time will my husband be joined

02:10:48.380 --> 02:10:51.360
unto me, because I have borne him three sons.

02:10:51.920 --> 02:10:53.900
Therefore was his name called Levi.

02:10:54.920 --> 02:11:00.420
And she conceived again, and bear a son, and she said, Now will I praise the Lord.

02:11:00.420 --> 02:11:04.520
Therefore she called his name Judah, and left Baring.

02:11:08.100 --> 02:11:13.840
And when Rachel saw that she bear Jacob no children, Rachel envied her sister, and said

02:11:13.840 --> 02:11:17.100
unto Jacob, Give me children, or else I die.

02:11:18.160 --> 02:11:23.960
And Jacob's anger was kindled against Rachel, and he said, Am I in God's stead, who hath

02:11:23.960 --> 02:11:25.840
withheld from thee the fruit of the womb?

02:11:26.640 --> 02:11:29.580
And she said, Behold my maid Bilha.

02:11:30.060 --> 02:11:35.800
Go in unto her, and she shall bear upon my knees, that I may also have children by her.

02:11:36.640 --> 02:11:41.580
And she gave him Bilha her handmaid to wife, and Jacob went in unto her.

02:11:42.700 --> 02:11:45.760
And Bilha conceived, and bear Jacob a son.

02:11:46.220 --> 02:11:52.540
And Rachel said, God hath judged me, and hath also heard my voice, and hath given me a son.

02:11:52.540 --> 02:11:55.320
Therefore she called his name Dan.

02:11:56.340 --> 02:12:00.980
And Bilha, Rachel's maid, conceived again, and bear Jacob a second son.

02:12:01.820 --> 02:12:07.240
And Rachel said, With great wrestlings have I wrestled with my sister, and I have prevailed.

02:12:07.700 --> 02:12:09.740
And she called his name Naphtali.

02:12:10.960 --> 02:12:16.180
When Leah saw that she had left Baring, she took Zilpah, her maid, and gave her Jacob

02:12:16.180 --> 02:12:16.880
to wife.

02:12:17.630 --> 02:12:20.200
And Zilpah Leah's maid, bear Jacob a son.

02:12:20.740 --> 02:12:22.780
And Leah said, A troop cometh.

02:12:23.080 --> 02:12:24.720
And she called his name Gad.

02:12:26.100 --> 02:12:29.160
And Zilpah Leah's maid, bear Jacob a second son.

02:12:30.120 --> 02:12:34.180
And Leah said, Happy am I, for the daughters will call me blessed.

02:12:34.700 --> 02:12:36.300
And she called his name Asher.

02:12:38.100 --> 02:12:43.300
And Reuben went in the days of wheat harvest, and found mandrakes in the field, and brought

02:12:43.300 --> 02:12:44.780
them unto his mother Leah.

02:12:45.340 --> 02:12:49.980
Then Rachel said to Leah, Give me, I pray thee, of thy son's mandrakes.

02:12:50.500 --> 02:12:56.300
And she said unto her, Is it a small matter that thou hast taken my husband, and wouldest

02:12:56.300 --> 02:12:58.940
thou take away my son's mandrakes also?

02:12:59.420 --> 02:13:04.700
And Rachel said, Therefore he shall lie with thee to-night for thy son's mandrakes.

02:13:05.660 --> 02:13:11.300
And Jacob came out of the field in the evening, and Leah went out to meet him, and said, Thou

02:13:11.300 --> 02:13:15.920
must come in unto me, for surely I have hired thee with my son's mandrakes.

02:13:16.520 --> 02:13:18.120
And he lay with her that night.

02:13:19.200 --> 02:13:24.060
And God harkened unto Leah, and she conceived, and bear Jacob the fifth son.

02:13:24.860 --> 02:13:30.580
And Leah said, God hath given me my hire, because I have given my maiden to my husband.

02:13:31.140 --> 02:13:33.060
And she called his name Issachar.

02:13:34.000 --> 02:13:37.740
And Leah conceived again, and bear Jacob the sixth son.

02:13:38.580 --> 02:13:44.660
And Leah said, God hath endued me with a good dowry, now will my husband dwell with me,

02:13:44.860 --> 02:13:46.820
because I have borne him six sons.

02:13:47.580 --> 02:13:49.320
And she called his name Zebulun.

02:13:50.200 --> 02:13:53.880
And afterwards she bear a daughter, and called her name Dinah.

02:13:55.620 --> 02:13:59.660
And God remembered Rachel, and God harkened to her, and opened her womb.

02:14:00.260 --> 02:14:05.980
And she conceived, and bear a son, and said, God hath taken away my reproach.

02:14:05.980 --> 02:14:11.560
And she called his name Joseph, and said, The Lord shall add to me another son.

02:14:12.660 --> 02:14:17.420
And it came to pass, when Rachel had borne Joseph, that Jacob said unto Laban,

02:14:17.840 --> 02:14:22.180
Send me away, that I may go unto mine own place, and to my country.

02:14:23.200 --> 02:14:27.600
Give me my wives and my children, for whom I have served thee, and let me go,

02:14:28.020 --> 02:14:30.660
for thou knowest my service which I have done thee.

02:14:31.260 --> 02:14:36.180
And Laban said unto him, I pray thee, if I have found favour in thine eyes,

02:14:36.400 --> 02:14:41.340
tarry, for I have learned by experience that the Lord hath blessed me for thy sake.

02:14:41.920 --> 02:14:45.600
And he said, Appoint me thy wages, and I will give it.

02:14:46.060 --> 02:14:51.400
And he said unto him, Thou knowest how I have served thee, and how thy cattle was with me.

02:14:51.840 --> 02:14:57.140
For it was little which thou hadst before I came, and it is now increased unto a multitude,

02:14:57.500 --> 02:15:03.460
and the Lord hath blessed thee since my coming, and now when shall I provide for mine own house also?

02:15:04.160 --> 02:15:06.540
And he said, What shall I give thee?

02:15:07.020 --> 02:15:10.040
And Jacob said, Thou shalt not give me anything.

02:15:10.580 --> 02:15:14.880
If thou wilt do this thing for me, I will again feed and keep thy flock.

02:15:15.800 --> 02:15:21.440
I will pass through all thy flock to-day, removing from thence all the speckled and spotted cattle,

02:15:21.780 --> 02:15:26.360
and all the brown cattle among the sheep, and the spotted and speckled among the goats,

02:15:26.360 --> 02:15:28.580
and of such shall be my hire.

02:15:29.440 --> 02:15:35.740
So shall my righteousness answer for me in time to come, when it shall come for my hire before thy face.

02:15:36.440 --> 02:15:40.900
Every one that is not speckled and spotted among the goats, and brown among the sheep,

02:15:41.280 --> 02:15:43.320
that shall be counted stolen with me.

02:15:44.020 --> 02:15:48.340
And Laban said, Behold, I would it might be according to thy word.

02:15:49.000 --> 02:15:52.840
And he removed that day the he-goats that were ring-straked and spotted,

02:15:52.840 --> 02:15:58.140
and all the she-goats that were speckled and spotted, and every one that had some white in it,

02:15:58.300 --> 02:16:02.340
and all the brown among the sheep, and gave them into the hand of his sons.

02:16:03.240 --> 02:16:09.600
And he set three days' journey betwixt himself and Jacob, and Jacob fed the rest of Laban's flocks.

02:16:10.600 --> 02:16:15.400
And Jacob took him rods of green poplar and of the hazel and chestnut tree,

02:16:15.820 --> 02:16:20.420
and piled white strakes in them, and made the white appear which was in the rods.

02:16:21.080 --> 02:16:26.480
And he set the rods which he had piled before the flocks and the gutters and the watering-troughs

02:16:26.480 --> 02:16:30.580
when the flocks came to drink, that they should conceive when they came to drink.

02:16:31.280 --> 02:16:37.080
And the flocks conceived before the rods, and brought forth cattle ring-straked, speckled, and spotted.

02:16:38.060 --> 02:16:43.080
And Jacob did separate the lambs, and set the faces of the flocks toward the ring-straked

02:16:43.080 --> 02:16:47.780
and all the brown in the flock of Laban, and he put his own flocks by themselves,

02:16:47.780 --> 02:16:50.140
and put them not on to Laban's cattle.

02:16:51.120 --> 02:16:54.880
And it came to pass, when soever the stronger cattle did conceive,

02:16:55.260 --> 02:16:59.080
that Jacob laid the rods before the eyes of the cattle and the gutters,

02:16:59.320 --> 02:17:01.400
that they might conceive among the rods.

02:17:02.020 --> 02:17:07.000
But when the cattle were feeble, he put them not in, so the feebler were Laban's,

02:17:07.000 --> 02:17:08.860
and the stronger Jacob's.

02:17:09.140 --> 02:17:13.660
And the man increased exceedingly, and had much cattle and maid-servants,

02:17:13.660 --> 02:17:17.560
and men-servants, and camels, and asses.

02:17:20.020 --> 02:17:23.020
And he heard the words of Laban's sons, saying,

02:17:23.280 --> 02:17:26.340
Jacob hath taken away all that was our father's,

02:17:26.460 --> 02:17:30.180
and of that which was our father's hath he gotten all this glory.

02:17:31.160 --> 02:17:36.620
And Jacob beheld the countenance of Laban, and, behold, it was not toward him as before.

02:17:37.680 --> 02:17:39.380
And the LORD said unto Jacob,

02:17:39.380 --> 02:17:44.700
Return unto the land of thy fathers, and to thy kindred, and I will be with thee.

02:17:45.500 --> 02:17:49.620
And Jacob sent and called Rachel and Leah to the field unto his flock,

02:17:50.100 --> 02:17:53.340
and said unto them, I see your father's countenance,

02:17:53.580 --> 02:17:58.780
that it is not toward me as before, but the God of my father hath been with me.

02:17:59.100 --> 02:18:02.600
And ye know that with all my power I have served your father.

02:18:03.200 --> 02:18:07.520
And your father hath deceived me, and changed my wages ten times,

02:18:07.520 --> 02:18:10.300
but God suffered him not to hurt me.

02:18:11.080 --> 02:18:14.040
If he said thus, The speckled shall be thy wages,

02:18:14.420 --> 02:18:16.180
then all the cattle bear speckled.

02:18:16.620 --> 02:18:19.900
And if he said thus, The ring-straked shall be thy hire,

02:18:20.360 --> 02:18:22.440
then bear all the cattle ring-straked.

02:18:23.200 --> 02:18:27.400
Thus God hath taken away the cattle of your father, and given them to me.

02:18:28.040 --> 02:18:31.040
And it came to pass at the time that the cattle conceived,

02:18:31.440 --> 02:18:34.260
that I lifted up mine eyes, and saw in a dream,

02:18:34.260 --> 02:18:37.420
and behold, the rams which leaped upon the cattle

02:18:37.420 --> 02:18:39.980
were ring-straked, speckled, and grizzled.

02:18:40.840 --> 02:18:45.740
And the angel of God spake unto me in a dream, saying, Jacob, and I said,

02:18:46.000 --> 02:18:46.880
Here am I.

02:18:47.300 --> 02:18:51.100
And he said, Lift up now thine eyes, and see all the rams

02:18:51.100 --> 02:18:54.960
which leap upon the cattle are ring-straked, speckled, and grizzled,

02:18:55.320 --> 02:18:58.180
for I have seen all that Laban doeth unto thee.

02:18:58.860 --> 02:19:02.440
I am the God of Bethel, where thou anointed'st the pillar,

02:19:02.440 --> 02:19:04.980
and where thou vowed'st to vow unto me.

02:19:05.300 --> 02:19:08.080
Now arise, get thee out from this land,

02:19:08.460 --> 02:19:10.680
and return unto the land of thy kindred.

02:19:11.820 --> 02:19:14.460
And Rachel and Lee answered, and said unto him,

02:19:14.760 --> 02:19:19.140
Is there yet any portion or inheritance for us in our father's house?

02:19:19.620 --> 02:19:21.700
Are we not counted of him strangers?

02:19:22.200 --> 02:19:25.920
For he hath sold us, and hath quite devoured also our money.

02:19:26.600 --> 02:19:29.540
For all the riches which God hath taken from our father,

02:19:29.540 --> 02:19:32.060
that is ours, and our children's.

02:19:32.160 --> 02:19:35.660
Now then, whatsoever God had said unto thee, Do.

02:19:36.680 --> 02:19:40.880
Then Jacob rose up, and set his sons and his wives upon camels,

02:19:41.300 --> 02:19:45.500
and he carried away all his cattle, and all his goods which he had gotten,

02:19:45.840 --> 02:19:49.220
the cattle of his getting, which he had gotten in pagan Aram,

02:19:49.620 --> 02:19:52.660
for to go to Isaac his father in the land of Canaan.

02:19:53.580 --> 02:19:57.540
And Laban went to shear his sheep, and Rachel had stolen the images

02:19:57.540 --> 02:19:59.560
that were her father's.

02:19:59.560 --> 02:20:02.940
And Jacob stole away unawares to Laban the Syrian,

02:20:03.340 --> 02:20:05.480
in that he told him not that he fled.

02:20:06.160 --> 02:20:09.600
So he fled with all that he had, and he rose up,

02:20:09.720 --> 02:20:13.580
and passed over the river, and set his face toward the Mount Gilead.

02:20:14.580 --> 02:20:17.880
And it was told Laban on the third day that Jacob was fled.

02:20:18.740 --> 02:20:23.240
And he took his brethren with him, and pursued after him seven days' journey,

02:20:23.560 --> 02:20:25.820
and they overtook him in the Mount Gilead.

02:20:26.420 --> 02:20:31.680
And God came to Laban the Syrian in a dream by night, and said unto him,

02:20:31.900 --> 02:20:35.720
Take heed that thou speak not to Jacob, either good or bad.

02:20:36.560 --> 02:20:38.440
Then Laban overtook Jacob.

02:20:39.040 --> 02:20:41.340
Now Jacob had pitched his tent in the mount,

02:20:41.780 --> 02:20:44.920
and Laban with his brethren pitched in the Mount of Gilead.

02:20:45.640 --> 02:20:50.400
And Laban said to Jacob, What hast thou done, that thou hast stolen away

02:20:50.400 --> 02:20:53.360
unawares to me, and carried away my daughters,

02:20:53.360 --> 02:20:55.820
as captives taken with the sword?

02:20:56.780 --> 02:21:00.900
Wherefore didst thou flee away secretly, and steal away from me,

02:21:01.020 --> 02:21:04.700
and didst not tell me that I might have sent thee away with mirth,

02:21:04.720 --> 02:21:07.560
and with songs, with tabret, and with harp,

02:21:08.080 --> 02:21:11.340
and hast not suffered me to kiss my sons and my daughters?

02:21:11.980 --> 02:21:14.480
Thou hast now done foolishly in so doing.

02:21:15.220 --> 02:21:17.940
It is in the power of my hand to do you hurt.

02:21:18.480 --> 02:21:22.200
But the God of your father spake unto me yesternight, saying,

02:21:22.200 --> 02:21:26.720
Take thou heed that thou speak not to Jacob, either good or bad.

02:21:27.700 --> 02:21:31.780
And now, though thou wouldst needs be gone, because thou soar longest

02:21:31.780 --> 02:21:36.200
after thy father's house, yet wherefore hast thou stolen my gods?

02:21:37.040 --> 02:21:41.900
And Jacob answered and said to Laban, Because I was afraid, for I said,

02:21:42.160 --> 02:21:45.760
Peradventure thou wouldst take by force thy daughters from me.

02:21:46.840 --> 02:21:50.300
With whomsoever thou findest thy gods, let him not live,

02:21:50.300 --> 02:21:55.120
before our brethren discern thou what is thine with me, and take it to thee.

02:21:55.480 --> 02:21:58.260
For Jacob knew not that Rachel had stolen them.

02:21:59.100 --> 02:22:02.840
And Laban went into Jacob's tent, and into Leah's tent, and

02:22:02.840 --> 02:22:06.180
into the two maidservants' tents, but he found them not.

02:22:06.780 --> 02:22:10.200
Then went he out of Leah's tent, and entered into Rachel's tent.

02:22:11.240 --> 02:22:15.080
Now Rachel had taken the images, and put them in the camel's furniture,

02:22:15.340 --> 02:22:16.600
and sat upon them.

02:22:17.000 --> 02:22:19.960
And Laban searched all the tent, but found them not.

02:22:20.800 --> 02:22:24.920
And she said to her father, Let it not displease my lord that I cannot

02:22:24.920 --> 02:22:28.680
rise up before thee, for the custom of women is upon me.

02:22:29.060 --> 02:22:31.440
And he searched, but found not the images.

02:22:32.800 --> 02:22:35.200
And Jacob was wroth, and showed with Laban.

02:22:35.580 --> 02:22:39.420
And Jacob answered and said to Laban, What is my trespass?

02:22:39.760 --> 02:22:43.720
What is my sin, that thou hast so hotly pursued after me?

02:22:44.360 --> 02:22:48.480
Whereas thou hast searched all my stuff, what hast thou found of all thy

02:22:48.480 --> 02:22:52.360
household stuff, said it here before my brethren and thy brethren,

02:22:52.720 --> 02:22:54.840
that they may judge betwixt us both.

02:22:55.320 --> 02:22:59.780
This twenty years have I been with thee, thy yews and thy she-goats

02:22:59.780 --> 02:23:03.920
have not cast their young, and the rams of thy flock have I not eaten.

02:23:04.700 --> 02:23:09.000
That which was torn of beasts I brought not unto thee, I bear the loss

02:23:09.000 --> 02:23:14.120
of it, of my hand didst thou require it, whether stolen by day or stolen

02:23:14.120 --> 02:23:14.860
by night.

02:23:15.380 --> 02:23:20.020
Thus I was, in the day the drought consumed me, and the frost by night,

02:23:20.320 --> 02:23:22.760
and my sleep departed from mine eyes.

02:23:23.620 --> 02:23:27.920
Thus have I been twenty years in thy house, I served thee fourteen

02:23:27.920 --> 02:23:32.620
years for thy two daughters, and six years for thy cattle, and thou hast

02:23:32.620 --> 02:23:35.040
changed my wages ten times.

02:23:35.860 --> 02:23:40.580
Except the God of my father, the God of Abraham, and the fear of Isaac

02:23:40.580 --> 02:23:44.800
had been with me, surely thou had sent me away now empty.

02:23:45.460 --> 02:23:49.620
God had seen mine affliction and the labor of my hands, and rebuked

02:23:49.620 --> 02:23:50.720
thee yester-night.

02:23:52.160 --> 02:23:56.540
And Laban answered and said unto Jacob, These daughters are my daughters,

02:23:56.760 --> 02:24:00.980
and these children are my children, and these cattle are my cattle, and

02:24:00.980 --> 02:24:05.420
all that thou seest is mine, and what can I do this day unto these my

02:24:05.420 --> 02:24:08.840
daughters, or unto their children which they have borne?

02:24:09.540 --> 02:24:14.580
Now therefore come thou, let us make a covenant, I and thou, and let

02:24:14.580 --> 02:24:17.220
it be for a witness between me and thee.

02:24:17.940 --> 02:24:20.960
And Jacob took a stone, and set it up for a pillar.

02:24:21.940 --> 02:24:26.500
And Jacob said unto his brethren, Gather stones, and they took stones,

02:24:26.740 --> 02:24:29.980
and made a heap, and they did eat there upon the heap.

02:24:31.180 --> 02:24:35.320
And Laban called it G-gar-say-a-dutha, but Jacob called it Gaelid.

02:24:36.120 --> 02:24:40.440
And Laban said, This heap is a witness between me and thee this day.

02:24:40.960 --> 02:24:45.060
Therefore was the name of it called Gaelid, and Mizpah, for he said,

02:24:45.360 --> 02:24:49.560
The Lord watch between me and thee, when we are absent one from another.

02:24:50.500 --> 02:24:54.360
If thou shalt afflict my daughters, or if thou shalt take other wives

02:24:54.360 --> 02:24:57.200
beside my daughters, no man is with us.

02:24:57.580 --> 02:25:00.380
See, God is witness betwixt me and thee.

02:25:01.180 --> 02:25:05.960
And Laban said to Jacob, Behold this heap, and behold this pillar which

02:25:05.960 --> 02:25:08.180
I have cast betwixt me and thee.

02:25:08.720 --> 02:25:13.020
This heap be witness, and this pillar be witness, that I will not pass

02:25:13.020 --> 02:25:17.280
over this heap to thee, and that thou shalt not pass over this heap and

02:25:17.280 --> 02:25:19.440
this pillar unto me for harm.

02:25:20.540 --> 02:25:24.540
The God of Abraham, and the God of Nahor, the God of their father,

02:25:25.040 --> 02:25:26.160
judge betwixt us.

02:25:26.160 --> 02:25:29.560
And Jacob swear by the fear of his father Isaac.

02:25:30.960 --> 02:25:35.100
Then Jacob offered sacrifice upon the mount, and called his brethren

02:25:35.100 --> 02:25:35.940
to eat bread.

02:25:36.400 --> 02:25:39.880
And they did eat bread, and tarried all night in the mount.

02:25:41.020 --> 02:25:44.940
And early in the morning Laban rose up, and kissed his sons and his

02:25:44.940 --> 02:25:46.560
daughters, and blessed them.

02:25:46.900 --> 02:25:50.080
And Laban departed, and returned unto his place.

02:26:01.100 --> 02:26:04.440
www.logoslibrary.org.

02:26:36.680 --> 02:26:41.860
And Jacob went on his way, and the angels of God met him. And when Jacob saw them,

02:26:41.860 --> 02:26:48.600
he said, This is God's host, and he called the name of that place Mayoneum. And Jacob

02:26:48.600 --> 02:26:54.360
sent messengers before him to Esau his brother unto the land of Seir, the country of Edom.

02:26:54.900 --> 02:27:00.980
And he commanded them, saying, Thus shall ye speak unto my lord Esau. Thy servant Jacob

02:27:00.980 --> 02:27:07.400
saith thus, I have sojourned with Laban, and stayed there until now. And I have oxen and

02:27:07.400 --> 02:27:13.480
asses, flocks, and men's servants, and women's servants. And I have sent to tell my lord

02:27:13.480 --> 02:27:20.140
that I may find grace in thy sight. And the messengers returned to Jacob, saying, We came

02:27:20.140 --> 02:27:30.120
to thy brother Esau, and also he cometh to meet thee and four hundred men with him. Then

02:27:30.120 --> 02:27:35.300
the people that was with him, and the flocks and herds, and the camels, into two bands.

02:27:35.920 --> 02:27:41.240
And said, If Esau come to the one company, and smite it, then the other company which

02:27:41.240 --> 02:27:48.440
is left shall escape. And Jacob said, O God of my father Abraham, and God of my father

02:27:48.440 --> 02:27:54.800
Isaac, the Lord which said unto me, Return unto thy country, and to thy kindred, and

02:27:55.480 --> 02:28:01.520
with thee. I am not worthy of the least of all the mercies and of all the truth which

02:28:01.520 --> 02:28:07.500
thou hast shewed unto thy servant, for with my staff I passed over this Jordan, and now

02:28:07.500 --> 02:28:13.640
I am become two bands. Deliver me, I pray thee, from the hand of my brother, from the

02:28:13.640 --> 02:28:19.080
hand of Esau, for I fear him lest he will come and smite me, and the mother with the

02:28:19.080 --> 02:28:25.080
children. And thou saidest, I will surely do thee good, and make thy seed as the sand

02:28:25.080 --> 02:28:31.860
of the sea, which cannot be numbered for multitude. And he lodged there that same night, and took

02:28:31.860 --> 02:28:37.840
of that which came to his hand a present for Esau his brother. Two hundred she-goats, and

02:28:37.840 --> 02:28:43.520
twenty he-goats, two hundred ewes, and twenty rams, thirty milk-camels with their colts,

02:28:43.520 --> 02:28:50.740
forty kine, and ten bulls, twenty she-asses, and ten foals. And he delivered them into

02:28:50.740 --> 02:28:56.920
the hand of his servants, every drove by themselves, and said unto his servants, Pass over before

02:28:56.920 --> 02:29:03.200
me, and put a space betwixt drove and grove. And he commanded the foremost, saying, When

02:29:03.200 --> 02:29:09.360
Esau my brother meeteth thee, and asketh thee, saying, Whos art thou, and whither goest thou,

02:29:09.360 --> 02:29:16.200
and whos are these before thee? Then thou shalt say, They be thy servant Jacob's, it

02:29:16.200 --> 02:29:23.040
is a present sent unto my lord Esau, and behold also he is behind us. And so commanded he

02:29:23.040 --> 02:29:28.580
the second, and the third, and all that followed the droves, saying, On this manner shall ye

02:29:28.580 --> 02:29:35.400
speak unto Esau when ye find him. And say ye moreover, Behold, thy servant Jacob is

02:29:35.400 --> 02:29:40.820
behind us. For he said, I will appease him with the present that goeth before me, and

02:29:40.820 --> 02:29:47.380
afterward I will see his face. Peradventure he will accept of me. So went the present

02:29:47.380 --> 02:29:53.440
over before him, and himself lodged that night in the company. And he rose up that night,

02:29:53.560 --> 02:29:58.980
and took his two wives, and his two women's servants, and his eleven sons, and passed

02:29:58.980 --> 02:30:04.500
over the ford Jabbok. And he took them, and sent them over the brook, and sent over that

02:30:04.500 --> 02:30:10.160
he had. And Jacob was left alone, and there wrestled a man with him until the breaking

02:30:10.160 --> 02:30:15.940
of the day. And when he saw that he prevailed not against him, he touched the hollow of

02:30:15.940 --> 02:30:21.260
his thigh, and the hollow of Jacob's thigh was out of joint as he wrestled with him.

02:30:21.620 --> 02:30:28.360
And he said, Let me go, for the day breaketh. And he said, I will not let thee go, except

02:30:28.720 --> 02:30:36.780
me. And he said unto him, What is thy name? And he said, Jacob. And he said, Thy name

02:30:36.780 --> 02:30:43.280
shall be called no more Jacob, but Israel, for as a prince hast thou power with God and

02:30:43.280 --> 02:30:50.760
with men, and hast prevailed. And Jacob asked him, and said, Tell me, I pray thee, thy name.

02:30:51.140 --> 02:30:57.080
And he said, Wherefore is it that thou dost ask after my name? And he blessed him there.

02:30:58.500 --> 02:31:05.100
And Jacob called the name of the place Peniel, for I have seen God face to face, and my life

02:31:05.100 --> 02:31:12.240
is preserved. And as he passed over Penuel, the sun rose upon him, and he halted upon

02:31:12.240 --> 02:31:18.900
his thigh. Therefore the children of Israel eat not of the sinew which shrank, which is

02:31:18.900 --> 02:31:24.180
upon the hollow of the thigh unto this day, because he touched the hollow of Jacob's thigh

02:31:24.180 --> 02:31:26.760
in the sinew that shrank.

02:31:29.300 --> 02:31:35.580
And Jacob lifted up his eyes, and looked, and behold Esau came, and with him four hundred

02:31:35.580 --> 02:31:41.600
men. And he divided the children unto Leah, and unto Rachel, and unto the two handmaids.

02:31:42.440 --> 02:31:47.500
Then he put the handmaids and their children foremost, and Leah and her children after,

02:31:47.500 --> 02:31:54.340
and Rachel and Joseph hindermost. And he passed over before them, and bowed himself to the

02:31:54.340 --> 02:32:01.020
ground seven times, until he came near to his brother. And Esau ran to meet him, and

02:32:01.020 --> 02:32:07.040
embraced him, and fell on his neck, and kissed him, and they wept. And he lifted up his eyes,

02:32:07.120 --> 02:32:12.880
and saw the women and the children, and said, Who are those with thee? and he said, The

02:32:12.880 --> 02:32:19.400
children which God hath graciously given that I servant. Then the handmaids came near, they

02:32:19.400 --> 02:32:24.980
and their children, and they bowed themselves. And Leah also with her children came near,

02:32:25.260 --> 02:32:30.660
and bowed themselves, and after came Joseph near, and Rachel, and they bowed themselves.

02:32:31.360 --> 02:32:37.320
And he said, What meanest thou by all this drove which I met? and he said, These are

02:32:37.320 --> 02:32:43.980
find grace in the sight of my Lord. And Esau said, I have enough, my brother, keep that

02:32:43.980 --> 02:32:51.220
thou hast unto thyself. And Jacob said, Nay, I pray thee, if now I have found grace in

02:32:51.220 --> 02:32:57.600
thy sight, then receive my present at my hand, for therefore I have seen thy face as though

02:32:57.600 --> 02:33:03.820
I had seen the face of God, and thou wast pleased with me. Take, I pray thee, my blessing

02:33:03.820 --> 02:33:08.980
that is brought to thee, because God hath dealt graciously with me, and because I have

02:33:08.980 --> 02:33:15.620
enough. And he urged him, and he took it. And he said, Let us take our journey, and

02:33:15.620 --> 02:33:21.460
let us go, and I will go before thee. And he said unto him, My Lord knoweth that the

02:33:21.460 --> 02:33:26.400
children are tender, and the flocks and herds with young are with me, and if men should

02:33:26.400 --> 02:33:32.800
overdrive them one day, all the flock will die. Let my Lord, I pray thee, pass over before

02:33:32.800 --> 02:33:38.660
his servant, and I will lead on softly, according as the cattle that goeth before me, and the

02:33:38.660 --> 02:33:45.740
children be able to endure, until I come unto my Lord, unto Seir. And Esau said, Let me

02:33:45.740 --> 02:33:50.800
now leave with thee some of the folk that are with me. And he said, What needeth it,

02:33:50.980 --> 02:33:57.080
let me find grace in the sight of my Lord. So Esau returned that day on his way unto

02:33:57.080 --> 02:34:03.240
Seir. And Jacob journeyed to Succoth, and built him in house, and made boots for his

02:34:03.240 --> 02:34:09.400
cattle. Therefore the name of the place is called Succoth. And Jacob came to Shalem,

02:34:09.560 --> 02:34:14.760
a city of Shechem, which is in the land of Canaan, when he came from Payton Aram, and

02:34:14.760 --> 02:34:20.530
pitched his tent before the city. And he bought a parcel of a field where he had spread his

02:34:20.530 --> 02:34:25.650
tent, at the hand of the children of Hamor, Shechem's father, for an hundred pieces of

02:34:25.650 --> 02:34:31.410
money. And he erected there an altar, and called it El Elohi Israel.

02:34:33.610 --> 02:34:37.610
And Dinah, the daughter of Leah, which she

02:34:37.610 --> 02:34:43.430
bare unto Jacob, went out to see the daughters of the land. And when Shechem, the son of

02:34:43.430 --> 02:34:49.630
Hamor the Hivite, prince of the country, saw her, he took her, and lay with her, and defiled

02:34:49.630 --> 02:34:56.130
her. And his soul clave unto Dinah, the daughter of Jacob, and he loved the damsel, and spake

02:34:56.130 --> 02:35:02.550
kindly unto the damsel. And Shechem spake unto his father Hamor, saying, Get me this

02:35:02.550 --> 02:35:08.870
damsel to wife. And Jacob heard that he had defiled Dinah, his daughter, that his sons

02:35:08.870 --> 02:35:15.170
were with his cattle in the field, and Jacob held his peace until they were come. And Hamor,

02:35:15.170 --> 02:35:20.410
the father of Shechem, went out unto Jacob to commune with him. And the sons of Jacob

02:35:20.410 --> 02:35:24.870
came out of the field when they heard it, and the men were grieved, and they were very

02:35:24.870 --> 02:35:30.010
wroth because he had wrought folly in Israel in lying with Jacob's daughter, which thing

02:35:30.010 --> 02:35:36.750
ought not to be done. And Hamor communed with them, saying, The soul of my son Shechem longeth

02:35:36.750 --> 02:35:42.790
for your daughter. I pray you give her him to wife. And make ye marriages with us, and

02:35:42.790 --> 02:35:47.590
give your daughters unto us, and take our daughters unto you. And ye shall dwell with

02:35:47.590 --> 02:35:53.150
us, and the land shall be before you. Dwell and trade ye therein, and get you possessions

02:35:53.150 --> 02:35:59.470
therein. And Shechem said unto her father, and unto her brethren, Let me find grace in

02:35:59.470 --> 02:36:05.430
your eyes, and what ye shall say unto me, I will give. Ask me never so much dowry and

02:36:05.430 --> 02:36:10.950
gift, and I will give according as ye shall say unto me. But give me the damsel to wife.

02:36:11.910 --> 02:36:17.790
And the sons of Jacob answered Shechem and Hamor his father deceitfully, and said, Because

02:36:17.790 --> 02:36:22.970
he had defiled Dinah their sister. And they said unto them, We cannot do this thing to

02:36:22.970 --> 02:36:29.410
give our sister to one that is uncircumcised, for that were a reproach unto us. But in this

02:36:29.410 --> 02:36:34.850
will we consent unto you, if ye will be as we be, that every male of you be circumcised.

02:36:35.190 --> 02:36:40.010
Then will we give our daughters unto you, and we will take your daughters to us, and

02:36:40.010 --> 02:36:45.310
we will dwell with you, and we will become one people. But if ye will not hearken unto

02:36:45.310 --> 02:36:51.650
us to be circumcised, then will we take our daughter, and we will be gone. And their words

02:36:51.650 --> 02:36:57.530
pleased Hamor and Shechem Hamor's son. And the young man deferred not to do the thing,

02:36:57.590 --> 02:37:02.450
because he had delight in Jacob's daughter, and he was more honorable than all the house

02:37:02.450 --> 02:37:08.690
of his father. And Hamor and Shechem his son came unto the gate of their city, and communed

02:37:08.690 --> 02:37:13.690
with the men of their city, saying, These men are peaceable with us, therefore let them

02:37:13.690 --> 02:37:19.050
dwell in the land and trade therein. For the land, behold, it is large enough for them.

02:37:19.470 --> 02:37:25.650
Let us take their daughters to us for wives, and let us give them our daughters. Only herein

02:37:25.650 --> 02:37:31.070
will the men consent unto us, for to dwell with us, to be one people, if every male among

02:37:31.070 --> 02:37:36.870
us be circumcised as they are circumcised. Shall not their cattle and their substance

02:37:36.870 --> 02:37:41.890
and every beast of theirs be ours? Only let us consent unto them, and they will dwell

02:37:41.890 --> 02:37:47.690
with us. And unto Hamor and unto Shechem his son hearkened all that went out of the gate

02:37:47.690 --> 02:37:53.090
of his city, and every male was circumcised all that went out of the gate of his city.

02:37:54.210 --> 02:37:59.250
And it came to pass on the third day, when they were sore, that two of the sons of Jacob,

02:37:59.590 --> 02:38:05.410
Simeon and Levi, Dinah's brethren, took each man his sword, and came upon the city boldly,

02:38:05.410 --> 02:38:11.270
and slew all the males. And they slew Hamor and Shechem his son with the edge of the sword,

02:38:11.610 --> 02:38:17.490
and took Dinah out of Shechem's house, and went out. The sons of Jacob came upon the

02:38:17.490 --> 02:38:23.330
slain and spoiled the city, because they had defiled their sister. They took their sheep,

02:38:23.490 --> 02:38:27.930
and their oxen, and their asses, and that which was in the city, and that which was

02:38:27.930 --> 02:38:32.430
in the field, and all their wealth, and all their little ones, and their wives took they

02:38:32.430 --> 02:38:35.730
captive, and spoiled even all that was in the house.

02:38:36.970 --> 02:38:39.030
And Jacob said to Simeon and Levi,

02:38:39.390 --> 02:38:44.690
E have troubled me to make me to stink among the inhabitants of the land, among the Canaanites

02:38:44.690 --> 02:38:49.970
and the Perizzites, and I, being few in number, they shall gather themselves together against

02:38:49.970 --> 02:38:54.290
me and slay me, and I shall be destroyed, I and my house.

02:38:54.890 --> 02:38:55.830
And they said,

02:38:56.150 --> 02:38:59.150
Should he deal with our sister as with an harlot?

02:39:02.630 --> 02:39:04.410
And God said unto Jacob,

02:39:04.790 --> 02:39:10.310
Arise, go up to Bethel, and dwell there, and make there an altar unto God, that appeared

02:39:10.310 --> 02:39:13.610
unto thee when thou fledtest from the face of Esau thy brother.

02:39:14.550 --> 02:39:18.330
Then Jacob said unto his household, and to all that were with him,

02:39:18.590 --> 02:39:24.270
Put away the strange gods that are among you, and be clean, and change your garments. And

02:39:24.270 --> 02:39:30.350
go up to Bethel, and I will make there an altar unto God, who answered me in the day

02:39:30.350 --> 02:39:33.830
of my distress, and was with me in the way which I went.

02:39:34.770 --> 02:39:40.010
And they gave unto Jacob all the strange gods which were in their hand, and all their earrings

02:39:40.010 --> 02:39:44.650
which were in their ears, and Jacob hid them under the oak which was by Shechem.

02:39:45.830 --> 02:39:50.330
And they journeyed, and the terror of God was upon the cities that were round about

02:39:50.330 --> 02:39:53.450
them, and they did not pursue after the sons of Jacob.

02:39:54.510 --> 02:39:59.990
So Jacob came to Luz, which is in the land of Canaan, that is, Bethel, he and all the

02:39:59.990 --> 02:40:05.370
people that were with him. And he built there an altar, and called the place El-Bethel,

02:40:05.630 --> 02:40:09.630
because there God appeared unto him when he fled from the face of his brother.

02:40:10.550 --> 02:40:16.390
But Deborah, Rebecca's nurse, died, and she was buried beneath Bethel under an oak, and

02:40:16.390 --> 02:40:18.970
the name of it was called El-Anbaikoth.

02:40:20.010 --> 02:40:25.290
And God appeared unto Jacob again, when he came out of Paedon Aram, and blessed him.

02:40:25.750 --> 02:40:31.110
And God said unto him, Thy name is Jacob, thy name shall not be called any more Jacob,

02:40:31.430 --> 02:40:35.170
but Israel shall be thy name. And he called his name Israel.

02:40:36.190 --> 02:40:43.130
And God said unto him, I am God Almighty, be fruitful and multiply, a nation and a company

02:40:43.130 --> 02:40:48.770
of nations shall be of thee, and kings shall come out of thy loins. And the land which

02:40:48.770 --> 02:40:54.550
I give Abraham and Isaac to thee I will give it, and to thy seed after thee will I give

02:40:54.550 --> 02:40:55.210
the land.

02:40:56.350 --> 02:40:59.570
And God went up from him in the place where he talked with him.

02:41:00.530 --> 02:41:05.210
And Jacob set up a pillar in the place where he talked with him, even a pillar of stone,

02:41:05.530 --> 02:41:11.110
and he poured a drink offering thereon, and he poured oil thereon. And Jacob called the

02:41:11.110 --> 02:41:14.030
name of the place where God spake with him Bethel.

02:41:14.910 --> 02:41:19.790
And they journeyed from Bethel, and there was but a little way to come to Ephrath, and

02:41:19.790 --> 02:41:25.430
Rachel travailed, and she had hard labor. And it came to pass, when she was in hard

02:41:25.430 --> 02:41:32.350
labor, that the midwife said unto her, Fear not, thou shalt have this son also. And it

02:41:32.350 --> 02:41:38.170
came to pass, as her soul was in departing, for she died, that she called his name Ben-Onai,

02:41:38.170 --> 02:41:44.750
but his father called him Benjamin. And Rachel died, and was buried in the way to Ephrath,

02:41:44.890 --> 02:41:51.130
which is Bethlehem. And Jacob set a pillar upon her grave, that is the pillar of Rachel's

02:41:51.130 --> 02:41:52.610
grave unto this day.

02:41:54.410 --> 02:42:00.010
And Israel journeyed, and spread his tent beyond the tower of Edar. And it came to pass,

02:42:00.050 --> 02:42:05.430
when Israel dwelt in that land that Reuben went, and lay with Bilha his father's concubine,

02:42:05.430 --> 02:42:12.330
and Israel heard it. Now the sons of Jacob were twelve. The sons of Leah, Reuben, Jacob's

02:42:12.330 --> 02:42:19.010
first born, and Simeon, and Levi, and Judah, and Issachar, and Zebulun. The sons of Rachel,

02:42:19.270 --> 02:42:25.550
Joseph, and Benjamin. And the sons of Bilha, Rachel's handmaid, Dan, and Naphtali. And

02:42:25.550 --> 02:42:30.810
the sons of Zilpah, Leah's handmaid, Gad, and Asher. These were the sons of Jacob, which

02:42:30.810 --> 02:42:37.770
were born to him, and paid in Aram. And Jacob came unto Isaac his father, unto Mamre, unto

02:42:37.770 --> 02:42:44.390
the city of Arba, which is Hebron, where Abraham and Isaac sojourned. And the days of Isaac

02:42:44.390 --> 02:42:50.550
were a hundred and four score years. And Isaac gave up the ghost, and died, and was gathered

02:42:50.550 --> 02:42:57.050
unto his people, being old and full of days. And his sons Esau and Jacob buried him.

02:42:58.270 --> 02:43:02.750
Now these are the generations of Esau, who

02:43:02.750 --> 02:43:09.390
is Edom. Esau took his wives of the daughters of Canaan, Adah the daughter of Elan the Hittite,

02:43:09.790 --> 02:43:15.630
and Ahol Abbaamah the daughter of Anah the daughter of Zibion the Hivite, and Bashamath

02:43:15.630 --> 02:43:23.670
Ishmael's daughter, sister of Nebejath. And Adah bare to Esau a life-faz, and Bashamath

02:43:23.670 --> 02:43:30.730
bare rule. And Ahol Abbaamah, Berjish, and Jalim, and Korah, these were the sons of Esau,

02:43:30.850 --> 02:43:36.390
which were born unto him in the land of Canaan. And Esau took his wives, and his sons, and

02:43:36.390 --> 02:43:41.090
his daughters, and all the persons of his house, and his cattle, and all his beasts,

02:43:41.190 --> 02:43:46.290
and all his substance, which he had got in the land of Canaan, and went into the country

02:43:46.290 --> 02:43:51.150
from the face of his brother Jacob. For their riches were more than that they might dwell

02:43:51.150 --> 02:43:55.850
together, and the land wherein they were strangers could not bear them because of their cattle.

02:43:56.990 --> 02:44:04.250
Thus Esau dwelt in Mount Seir. Esau is Edom. And these are the generations of Esau, the

02:44:04.250 --> 02:44:10.590
father of the Edomites in Mount Seir. These are the names of Esau's sons. Eliphaz, the

02:44:10.590 --> 02:44:17.490
son of Edah, the wife of Esau, rule, the son of Bashamath, the wife of Esau. And the sons

02:44:17.490 --> 02:44:25.510
of Eliphaz were Timon, Omar, Zepho, and Gatam, and Kenaz. And Timna was concubine to Eliphaz,

02:44:25.670 --> 02:44:31.930
Esau's son, and she bore to Eliphaz Amalek. These were the sons of Edah, Esau's wife.

02:44:32.970 --> 02:44:38.590
And these were the sons of Rul, Nahath, and Zirah, Shammah, and Mizzah. These were the

02:44:38.590 --> 02:44:44.730
sons of Bashamath, Esau's wife. And these were the sons of Ahalibamah, the daughter

02:44:44.730 --> 02:44:51.930
of Ana, the daughter of Zibian, Esau's wife. And she bore to Esau, Jeash, and Jalem, and

02:44:51.930 --> 02:44:58.490
Korah. These were the dukes of the sons of Esau, the sons of Eliphaz, the firstborn son

02:44:58.490 --> 02:45:06.470
of Esau, duke Timon, duke Omar, duke Zepho, duke Kenaz, duke Korah, duke Gatam, and duke

02:45:06.470 --> 02:45:12.210
Amalek. These are the dukes that came of Eliphaz in the land of Edom. These were the sons of

02:45:12.210 --> 02:45:19.970
Edah. And these were the sons of Rul, Esau's son, duke Nahath, duke Zirah, duke Shammah,

02:45:20.070 --> 02:45:25.230
duke Mizzah. These were the dukes that came of Rul in the land of Edom. These were the

02:45:25.230 --> 02:45:32.090
sons of Bashamath, Esau's wife. And these were the sons of Ahalibamah, Esau's wife,

02:45:32.590 --> 02:45:42.190
duke Jeash, duke Jalem, duke Korah. These were the dukes that came of Ahalibamah, the

02:45:42.190 --> 02:45:46.010
sons of Esau, who is Edom, and these are their dukes.

02:45:47.310 --> 02:45:53.830
These are the sons of Seir, the Horite, who inhabited the land, Lotan and Shobol and Zibian

02:45:53.830 --> 02:46:01.230
and Einah and Daishan and Ezer and Daishan. These are the dukes of the Horites, the children

02:46:01.230 --> 02:46:08.390
of Seir in the land of Edom. And the children of Lotan were Horai and Hemam, and Lotan's

02:46:08.390 --> 02:46:16.870
sister was Timna. And the children of Shobol were these, Alvin and Manahath and Ebel, Shifo

02:46:16.870 --> 02:46:24.190
and Onam. And these were the children of Zibian, both Aja and Einah. This was that Einah that

02:46:24.190 --> 02:46:30.530
found the mules in the wilderness as he fed the asses of Zibian his father. And the children

02:46:30.530 --> 02:46:36.470
of Einah were these, Daishan and Ahalibamah, the daughter of Einah. And these were the

02:46:36.470 --> 02:46:43.690
children of Daishan, Hemdan and Eshban and Ithran and Kiran. The children of Ezer are

02:46:43.690 --> 02:46:52.890
these, Bilhan and Zayavan and Akan. The children of Daishan are these, Uz and Aaron. These

02:46:52.890 --> 02:46:59.090
are the dukes that come of the Horites, duke Lotan, duke Shobol, duke Zibian, duke Einah,

02:46:59.290 --> 02:47:05.910
duke Daishan, duke Ezer, duke Daishan. These are the dukes that come of Horai, among their

02:47:05.910 --> 02:47:11.910
dukes in the land of Seir. And these are the kings that reigned in the land of Edom before

02:47:11.910 --> 02:47:17.710
there reigned any king over the children of Israel. And Bela, the son of Beor, reigned

02:47:17.710 --> 02:47:24.450
in Edom, and the name of his city was Dinhabah. And Bela died, and Jobab, the son of Zerah,

02:47:24.510 --> 02:47:31.490
of Basra, reigned in his stead. And Jobab died, and Husham, the land of Timani, reigned

02:47:31.490 --> 02:47:37.950
in his stead. And Husham died, and Hadad, the son of Beedad, who smote Midian in the

02:47:37.950 --> 02:47:44.930
field of Moab, reigned in his stead. And the name of his city was Avoth. And Hadad died,

02:47:45.190 --> 02:47:52.050
and Samlah, of Masrika, reigned in his stead. And Samlah died, and Saul, of Rehoboth, by

02:47:52.050 --> 02:47:58.690
the river, reigned in his stead. And Saul died, and Baal-Hanan, the son of Aqbor, reigned

02:47:58.690 --> 02:48:05.610
in his stead. And Baal-Hanan, the son of Aqbor, died, and Hadar reigned in his stead. And

02:48:05.610 --> 02:48:11.530
the name of his city was Peu, and his wife's name was Mehedabal, the daughter of Matred,

02:48:11.890 --> 02:48:17.950
the daughter of Mizahab. And these are the names of the dukes that came of Esau according

02:48:17.950 --> 02:48:24.950
to their families after their places by their names. Duke Timnah, Duke Alva, Duke Jetheth,

02:48:24.950 --> 02:48:33.470
Duke Aholibamah, Duke Elah, Duke Pinon, Duke Kienaz, Duke Timon, Duke Mibzar, Duke Magdiel,

02:48:33.890 --> 02:48:39.190
Duke Irem. These be the dukes of Edom according to their habitations in the land of their

02:48:39.190 --> 02:48:42.970
possession. He is Esau, the father of the Edomites.

02:48:54.970 --> 02:48:56.970
LogosLibrary.org

02:49:30.390 --> 02:49:35.490
And Jacob dwelt in the land wherein his father was a stranger in the land of Canaan.

02:49:36.190 --> 02:49:38.530
These are the generations of Jacob.

02:49:39.370 --> 02:49:52.050
Joseph, being seventeen years old, was feeding the flock with his brethren, and the lad was with the sons of Bilha and with the sons of Zilpah, his father's wives, and Joseph brought unto his father their evil report.

02:49:52.890 --> 02:50:01.230
Now Israel loved Joseph more than all his children, because he was the son of his old age, and he made him a coat of many colors.

02:50:02.270 --> 02:50:10.190
And when his brethren saw that their father loved him more than all his brethren, they hated him, and could not speak peaceably unto him.

02:50:10.830 --> 02:50:16.570
And Joseph dreamed a dream, and he told it his brethren, and they hated him yet the more.

02:50:17.230 --> 02:50:21.150
And he said unto them, Here, I pray you, this dream which I have dreamed.

02:50:21.930 --> 02:50:33.290
For behold, we were binding sheaves in the field, and lo, my sheaf arose, and also stood upright, and behold, your sheaves stood round about, and made obeisance to my sheaf.

02:50:33.290 --> 02:50:41.010
And his brethren said to him, Shalt thou indeed reign over us, or shalt thou indeed have dominion over us?

02:50:41.390 --> 02:50:45.010
And they hated him yet the more for his dreams and for his words.

02:50:46.390 --> 02:50:57.410
And he dreamed yet another dream, and told it his brethren, and said, Behold, I have dreamed a dream more, and behold, the sun and the moon and the eleven stars made obeisance to me.

02:50:57.410 --> 02:51:06.130
And he told it to his father and to his brethren, and his father rebuked him, and said unto him, What is this dream that thou hast dreamed?

02:51:06.650 --> 02:51:12.110
Shall I and thy mother and thy brethren indeed come to bow down ourselves to thee to the earth?

02:51:12.530 --> 02:51:16.430
And his brethren envied him, but his father observed the saying.

02:51:17.630 --> 02:51:20.630
And his brethren went to feed their father's flock in Shechem.

02:51:21.230 --> 02:51:25.790
And Israel said unto Joseph, Do not thy brethren feed the flock in Shechem?

02:51:26.350 --> 02:51:28.290
Come, and I will send thee unto them.

02:51:28.570 --> 02:51:30.590
And he said to him, Here am I.

02:51:31.290 --> 02:51:38.950
And he said to him, Go, I pray thee, see whether it be well with thy brethren, and well with the flocks, and bring me word again.

02:51:39.450 --> 02:51:43.470
So he sent him out of the vale of Hebron, and he came to Shechem.

02:51:44.290 --> 02:51:48.570
And a certain man found him, and behold, he was wandering in the field.

02:51:48.870 --> 02:51:51.870
And the man asked him, saying, What seekest thou?

02:51:52.470 --> 02:51:57.770
And he said, I seek my brethren, tell me, I pray thee, where they feed their flocks.

02:51:58.630 --> 02:52:04.230
And the man said, They are departed hence, for I heard them say, Let us go to Dothan.

02:52:04.970 --> 02:52:08.750
And Joseph went after his brethren, and found them in Dothan.

02:52:08.750 --> 02:52:16.490
And when they saw him afar off, even before he came near unto them, they conspired against him to slay him.

02:52:17.210 --> 02:52:21.230
And they said one to another, Behold, this dreamer cometh.

02:52:21.850 --> 02:52:26.130
Come now, therefore, and let us slay him, and cast him into some pit.

02:52:26.570 --> 02:52:32.410
And we will say some evil beast hath devoured him, and we shall see what will become of his dreams.

02:52:33.270 --> 02:52:39.510
And Reuben heard it, and he delivered him out of their hands, and said, Let us not kill him.

02:52:40.030 --> 02:52:42.670
And Reuben said unto them, Shed no blood.

02:52:43.150 --> 02:52:47.830
But cast him into this pit that is in the wilderness, and lay no hand upon him,

02:52:48.370 --> 02:52:52.470
that he might rid him out of their hands, to deliver him to his father again.

02:52:53.710 --> 02:52:59.750
And it came to pass, when Joseph was come unto his brethren, that they stripped Joseph out of his coat,

02:52:59.750 --> 02:53:05.030
his coat of many colours that was on him, and they took him and cast him into a pit,

02:53:05.470 --> 02:53:08.270
and the pit was empty, there was no water in it.

02:53:09.030 --> 02:53:10.850
And they sat down to eat bread.

02:53:11.210 --> 02:53:16.670
They lifted up their eyes, and looked, and behold, a company of Ishmaelites came from Gilead,

02:53:16.870 --> 02:53:22.590
with their camels bearing spicery, and balm, and myrrh, going to carry it down to Egypt.

02:53:23.630 --> 02:53:29.790
And Judah said unto his brethren, What profit is it if we slay our brother and conceal his blood?

02:53:30.570 --> 02:53:35.430
Come, and let us sell him to the Ishmaelites, and let not our hand be upon him,

02:53:35.590 --> 02:53:37.670
for he is our brother and our flesh.

02:53:38.190 --> 02:53:39.730
And his brethren were content.

02:53:41.210 --> 02:53:46.990
Then there passed by Midianites' merchantmen, and they drew and lifted up Joseph out of the pit,

02:53:47.390 --> 02:53:51.070
and sold Joseph to the Ishmaelites for twenty pieces of silver,

02:53:51.070 --> 02:53:53.550
and they brought Joseph into Egypt.

02:53:54.790 --> 02:54:01.010
And Reuben returned unto the pit, and behold, Joseph was not in the pit, and he rent his clothes.

02:54:01.890 --> 02:54:07.810
And he returned unto his brethren, and said, The child is not, and I, whither shall I go?

02:54:08.690 --> 02:54:13.530
And they took Joseph's coat, and killed a kid of goats, and dipped the coat in the blood.

02:54:13.930 --> 02:54:18.430
And they set the coat of many colours, and they brought it to their father, and said,

02:54:18.430 --> 02:54:23.130
This have we found, know now whether it be thy son's coat or no.

02:54:23.970 --> 02:54:29.450
And he knew it, and said, It is my son's coat, an evil beast hath devoured him,

02:54:29.790 --> 02:54:32.390
Joseph is without doubt rent in pieces.

02:54:33.530 --> 02:54:39.830
And Jacob rent his clothes, and put sackcloth upon his loins, and mourned for his son many days.

02:54:40.670 --> 02:54:46.690
And all his sons and all his daughters rose up to comfort him, but he refused to be comforted,

02:54:46.690 --> 02:54:51.250
and he said, For I will go down into the grave unto my son, mourning.

02:54:52.050 --> 02:54:53.990
Thus his father wept for him.

02:54:55.190 --> 02:55:02.070
And the Midianites sold him into Egypt unto Potiphar, an officer of Pharaohs, and captain of the guard.

02:55:05.390 --> 02:55:09.330
And it came to pass at that time that Judah went down from his brethren,

02:55:09.810 --> 02:55:13.010
and turned into a certain Adulamite, whose name was Hira.

02:55:13.790 --> 02:55:18.510
And Judah saw there a daughter of a certain Canaanite, whose name was Shua,

02:55:18.870 --> 02:55:21.150
and he took her, and went in unto her.

02:55:21.730 --> 02:55:25.450
And she conceived, and bare a son, and he called his name Er.

02:55:26.530 --> 02:55:30.850
And she conceived again, and bare a son, and she called his name Onan.

02:55:32.050 --> 02:55:36.810
And she yet again conceived, and bare a son, and called his name Shelah.

02:55:37.110 --> 02:55:39.490
And he was at Kizib, when she bare him.

02:55:40.290 --> 02:55:44.470
And Judah took a wife for Er his firstborn, whose name was Tamar.

02:55:45.490 --> 02:55:50.650
And Er, Judah's firstborn, was wicked in the sight of the Lord, and the Lord slew him.

02:55:51.510 --> 02:55:58.650
And Judah said unto Onan, Go in unto thy brother's wife, and marry her, and raise up seed to thy brother.

02:55:59.630 --> 02:56:05.890
And Onan knew that the seed should not be his, and it came to pass, when he went in unto his brother's wife,

02:56:05.890 --> 02:56:10.190
that he spilled it on the ground, lest that he should give seed to his brother.

02:56:11.210 --> 02:56:16.150
And the thing which he did displeased the Lord, wherefore he slew him also.

02:56:17.630 --> 02:56:24.350
Then said Judah to Tamar his daughter-in-law, Remain a widow at thy father's house, till Shelah my son be grown.

02:56:24.910 --> 02:56:29.210
For he said, Lest per adventure he die also, as his brethren did.

02:56:30.030 --> 02:56:32.910
And Tamar went and dwelt in her father's house.

02:56:33.710 --> 02:56:37.850
And in process of time the daughter of Shua, Judah's wife, died.

02:56:38.390 --> 02:56:44.990
And Judah was comforted, and went up unto his sheep-sherers to Timnath, he and his friend Hira the Adulamite.

02:56:45.950 --> 02:56:51.850
And it was told Tamar, saying, Behold, thy father-in-law goeth up to Timnath to share his sheep.

02:56:52.810 --> 02:56:57.050
And she put her widow's garments off from her, and covered her with a veil,

02:56:57.050 --> 02:57:01.950
and wrapped herself, and sat in an open place, which is by the way to Timnath.

02:57:02.170 --> 02:57:06.470
For she saw that Shelah was grown, and she was not given unto him to wife.

02:57:08.070 --> 02:57:13.270
When Judah saw her, he thought her to be in harlot, because she had covered her face.

02:57:13.890 --> 02:57:19.710
And he turned unto her by the way, and said, Go to, I pray thee, let me come in unto thee.

02:57:19.910 --> 02:57:22.530
For he knew not that she was his daughter-in-law.

02:57:22.530 --> 02:57:27.070
And she said, What wilt thou give me, that thou mayest come in unto me?

02:57:27.570 --> 02:57:30.530
And he said, I will send thee a kid from the flock.

02:57:31.190 --> 02:57:34.810
And she said, Wilt thou give me a pledge, till thou send it?

02:57:35.230 --> 02:57:37.970
And he said, What pledge shall I give thee?

02:57:38.430 --> 02:57:43.430
And she said, Thy signet, and thy bracelets, and thy staff that is in thine hand.

02:57:44.050 --> 02:57:47.970
And he gave it her, and came in unto her, and she conceived by him.

02:57:48.750 --> 02:57:54.970
And she arose, and went away, and laid by her veil from her, and put on the garments of her widowhood.

02:57:56.270 --> 02:58:03.330
And Judah sent the kid by the hand of his friend the Adulamite to receive his pledge from the woman's hand, but he found her not.

02:58:04.430 --> 02:58:10.050
Then he asked the men of that place, saying, Where is the harlot that was openly by the wayside?

02:58:10.330 --> 02:58:13.370
And they said, There was no harlot in this place.

02:58:14.010 --> 02:58:17.730
And he returned to Judah, and said, I cannot find her.

02:58:17.930 --> 02:58:22.010
And also the men of the place said that there was no harlot in this place.

02:58:22.930 --> 02:58:26.950
And Judah said, Let her take it to her, lest we be shamed.

02:58:27.370 --> 02:58:30.910
Behold, I sent this kid, and thou hast not found her.

02:58:31.890 --> 02:58:39.290
And it came to pass about three months after that it was told Judah, saying, Tamar, thy daughter-in-law, hath played the harlot.

02:58:39.290 --> 02:58:43.150
And also, behold, she is with child by whoredom.

02:58:43.870 --> 02:58:47.090
And Judah said, Bring her forth, and let her be burnt.

02:58:48.250 --> 02:58:54.990
When she was brought forth, she sent to her father-in-law, saying, By the man whose these are, am I with child.

02:58:55.430 --> 02:59:01.150
And she said, Discern, I pray thee, whose are these, the signet, and bracelets, and staff.

02:59:02.050 --> 02:59:10.170
And Judah acknowledged them, and said, She hath been more righteous than I, because that I gave her not to Shelah my son.

02:59:10.670 --> 02:59:12.670
And he knew her again no more.

02:59:13.770 --> 02:59:18.670
And it came to pass in the time of her travail that, behold, twins were in her womb.

02:59:19.270 --> 02:59:29.090
And it came to pass when she travailed that the one put out his hand, and the midwife took and bound upon his hand a scarlet thread, saying, This came out first.

02:59:30.050 --> 02:59:39.730
And it came to pass as he drew back his hand that, behold, his brother came out, and she said, How hast thou broken forth this breach be upon thee?

02:59:40.290 --> 02:59:42.310
Therefore his name was called Phares.

02:59:43.230 --> 02:59:49.490
And afterward came out his brother that had the scarlet thread upon his hand, and his name was called Zarah.

02:59:53.010 --> 03:00:03.970
And Joseph was brought down to Egypt, and Potiphar, an officer of Pharaoh, captain of the guard, and Egyptian, bought him of the hands of the Ishmaelites, which had brought him down thither.

03:00:04.870 --> 03:00:10.830
And the LORD was with Joseph, and he was a prosperous man, and he was in the house of his master the Egyptian.

03:00:11.510 --> 03:00:17.950
And his master saw that the LORD was with him, and that the LORD made all that he did to prosper in his hand.

03:00:18.870 --> 03:00:27.630
And Joseph found grace in his sight, and he served him, and he made him overseer over his house, and all that he had he put into his hand.

03:00:28.510 --> 03:00:42.750
And it came to pass from the time that he had made him overseer in his house, and over all that he had, that the LORD blessed the Egyptian's house for Joseph's sake, and the blessing of the LORD was upon all that he had in the house and in the field.

03:00:43.610 --> 03:00:53.650
And he left all that he had in Joseph's hand, and he knew not aught he had save the bread which he did eat, and Joseph was a goodly person and well favored.

03:00:55.010 --> 03:01:02.750
And it came to pass after these things that his master's wife cast her eyes upon Joseph, and she said, Lie with me.

03:01:02.750 --> 03:01:13.350
But he refused, and said unto his master's wife, Behold, my master watteth not what is with me in the house, and he hath committed all that he hath to my hand.

03:01:13.830 --> 03:01:26.570
There is none greater in this house than I. Neither hath he kept back any thing from me but thee, because thou art his wife. How then can I do this great wickedness and sin against God?

03:01:27.510 --> 03:01:35.650
And it came to pass as she spake to Joseph day by day that he hearkened not unto her to lie by her or to be with her.

03:01:36.590 --> 03:01:44.290
And it came to pass about this time that Joseph went into the house to do his business, and there was none of the men of the house there within.

03:01:45.010 --> 03:01:52.710
And she caught him by his garment, saying, Lie with me. And he left his garment in her hand, and fled and got him out.

03:01:53.670 --> 03:02:02.890
And it came to pass when she saw that he had left his garment in her hand, and was fled forth, that she called unto the men of her house, and spake unto them, saying,

03:02:03.270 --> 03:02:10.850
See, he hath brought in a Hebrew unto us to mock us. He came in unto me to lie with me, and I cried with a loud voice.

03:02:11.150 --> 03:02:18.750
And it came to pass when he heard that I lifted up my voice, and cried that he left his garment with me, and fled and got him out.

03:02:18.750 --> 03:02:22.930
And she laid up his garment by her until his Lord came home.

03:02:23.890 --> 03:02:32.090
And she spake unto him according to these words, saying, The Hebrew servant which thou hast brought unto us came in unto me to mock me.

03:02:32.290 --> 03:02:38.390
And it came to pass as I lifted up my voice, and cried that he left his garment with me, and fled out.

03:02:39.270 --> 03:02:49.290
And it came to pass when his master heard the words of his wife which she spake unto him, saying, After this manner did thy servant to me, that his wrath was kindled.

03:02:49.950 --> 03:02:57.810
And Joseph's master took him and put him into the prison, a place where the king's prisoners were bound, and he was there in the prison.

03:02:59.150 --> 03:03:05.330
But the Lord was with Joseph, and showed him mercy, and gave him favor in the sight of the keeper of the prison.

03:03:06.010 --> 03:03:14.950
And the keeper of the prison committed to Joseph's hand all the prisoners that were in the prison, and whatsoever they did there, he was the doer of it.

03:03:15.950 --> 03:03:24.770
The keeper of the prison looked not to anything that was under his hand, because the Lord was with him, and that which he did, the Lord made it to prosper.

03:03:28.770 --> 03:03:36.510
And it came to pass after these things that the butler of the king of Egypt and his baker had offended their lord the king of Egypt.

03:03:37.350 --> 03:03:43.970
And Pharaoh was wroth against two of his officers, against the chief of the butlers, and against the chief of the bakers.

03:03:44.770 --> 03:03:51.170
And he put them in ward in the house of the captain of the guard, into the prison, the place where Joseph was bound.

03:03:51.870 --> 03:03:58.470
And the captain of the guard charged Joseph with them, and he served them, and they continued a season in ward.

03:03:59.630 --> 03:04:10.990
And they dreamed a dream, both of them, each man his dream, and one night, each man, according to the interpretation of his dream, the butler and the baker of the king of Egypt, which were bound in the prison.

03:04:11.930 --> 03:04:17.490
And Joseph came in unto them in the morning, and looked upon them, and behold, they were sad.

03:04:18.190 --> 03:04:25.790
And he asked Pharaoh's officers that were with him in the ward of his lord's house, saying, Wherefore look ye so sadly to-day?

03:04:26.410 --> 03:04:31.330
And they said unto him, We have dreamed a dream, and there is no interpreter of it.

03:04:31.670 --> 03:04:37.970
And Joseph said unto them, Do not interpretations belong to God, tell me them, I pray you.

03:04:38.690 --> 03:04:54.470
And the chief butler told his dream to Joseph, and said to him, In my dream, behold, a vine was before me, and in the vine were three branches, and it was as though it budded, and her blossoms shot forth, and the clusters thereof brought forth ripe grapes.

03:04:55.270 --> 03:05:03.070
And Pharaoh's cup was in my hand, and I took the grapes, and pressed them into Pharaoh's cup, and I gave the cup into Pharaoh's hand.

03:05:03.070 --> 03:05:21.830
And Joseph said unto him, This is the interpretation of it. The three branches are three days. Yet within three days shall Pharaoh lift up thine head, and restore thee unto thy place, and thou shalt deliver Pharaoh's cup into his hand after the former manner when thou wast his butler.

03:05:22.570 --> 03:05:39.750
But think on me when it shall be well with thee, and show kindness, I pray thee, unto me, and make mention of me unto Pharaoh, and bring me out of this house. For indeed I was stolen away out of the land of the Hebrews, and here also have I done nothing that they should put me into the dungeon.

03:05:40.790 --> 03:05:59.070
When the chief baker saw that the interpretation was good, he said unto Joseph, I also was in my dream, and behold, I had three white baskets on my head, and in the uppermost basket there was of all manner of baked meats for Pharaoh, and the birds did eat them out of the basket upon my head.

03:05:59.070 --> 03:06:15.410
And Joseph answered and said, This is the interpretation thereof. The three baskets are three days. Yet within three days shall Pharaoh lift up thy head from off thee, and shall hang thee on a tree, and the birds shall eat thy flesh from off thee.

03:06:16.310 --> 03:06:43.330
And it came to pass the third day, which was Pharaoh's birthday, that he made a feast unto all his servants, and he lifted up the head of the chief butler and of the chief baker among his servants. And he restored the chief butler under his butler-ship again, and he gave the cup into Pharaoh's hand, but he hanged the chief baker as Joseph had interpreted to them. Yet did not the chief butler remember Joseph, but forget him.

03:07:13.330 --> 03:07:41.550
The fleshed kine did eat up the seven well-favored and fat kine, so Pharaoh awoke. And he slept and dreamed the second time, and behold, seven ears of corn came up upon one stalk, rank and good. And behold, seven thin ears and blasted with the east wind sprung up after them. And the seven thin ears devoured the seven rank and full ears, and Pharaoh awoke, and behold, it was a dream.

03:07:42.610 --> 03:07:56.630
And it came to pass in the morning that his spirit was troubled, and he sent and called for all the magicians of Egypt and all the wise men thereof, and Pharaoh told them his dream, but there was none that could interpret them unto Pharaoh.

03:07:57.830 --> 03:08:18.250
Then spake the chief butler unto Pharaoh, saying, I do remember my faults this day. Pharaoh was wroth with his servants, and put me in ward in the captain of the guard's house, both me and the chief baker. And we dreamed a dream in one night, I and he. We dreamed each man according to the interpretation of his dream.

03:08:18.250 --> 03:08:40.050
And there was there with us a young man, in Hebrew, servant to the captain of the guard, and we told him, and he interpreted to us our dreams, to each man according to his dream he did interpret. And it came to pass, as he interpreted to us, so it was. Me he restored unto mine office, and him he hanged.

03:08:40.050 --> 03:08:49.770
Then Pharaoh sent and called Joseph, and they brought him hastily out of the dungeon, and he shaved himself, and changed his raiment, and came in unto Pharaoh.

03:08:51.050 --> 03:09:00.810
And Pharaoh said unto Joseph, I have dreamed a dream, and there is none that can interpret it, and I have heard say of thee that thou canst understand a dream to interpret it.

03:09:00.810 --> 03:09:08.070
And Joseph answered Pharaoh, saying, It is not in me. God shall give Pharaoh an answer of peace.

03:09:08.810 --> 03:09:21.770
And Pharaoh said unto Joseph, In my dream, behold, I stood upon the bank of the river, and behold, there came up out of the river seven kind, fat-fleshed and well-favored, and they fed in a meadow.

03:09:21.770 --> 03:09:32.270
And behold, seven other kind came up after them, poor and very ill-favored and lean-fleshed, such as I never saw in all the land of Egypt, for badness.

03:09:32.930 --> 03:09:46.910
And the lean and the ill-favored kind did eat up the first seven fat kind. And when they had eaten them up, it could not be known that they had eaten them, but they were still ill-favored, as at the beginning. So I awoke.

03:09:46.910 --> 03:09:59.770
And I saw in my dream, and behold, seven ears came up in one stalk, full and good. And behold, seven ears, withered thin and blasted with the east wind, sprung up after them.

03:10:00.570 --> 03:10:08.130
And the thin ears devoured the seven good ears. And I told this unto the magicians, but there was none that could declare it to me.

03:10:08.790 --> 03:10:23.010
And Joseph said unto Pharaoh, The dream of Pharaoh is one. God hath showed Pharaoh what he is about to do. The seven good kind are seven years, and the seven good ears are seven years. The dream is one.

03:10:23.730 --> 03:10:33.170
And the seven thin and ill-favored kind that came up after them are seven years, and the seven empty ears blasted with the east wind shall be seven years of famine.

03:10:33.770 --> 03:10:40.050
This is the thing which I have spoken unto Pharaoh. What God is about to do he showeth unto Pharaoh.

03:10:41.450 --> 03:11:01.810
Behold, there come seven years of great plenty throughout all the land of Egypt, and there shall arise after them seven years of famine, and all the plenty shall be forgotten in the land of Egypt, and the famine shall consume the land, and the plenty shall not be known in the land by reason of that famine following, for it shall be very grievous.

03:11:02.470 --> 03:11:11.170
And for that the dream was doubled unto Pharaoh twice. It is because the thing is established by God, and God will shortly bring it to pass.

03:11:12.110 --> 03:11:27.370
Now therefore let Pharaoh look out a man discreet and wise, and set him over the land of Egypt. Let Pharaoh do this, and let him appoint officers over the land, and take up the fifth part of the land of Egypt in the seven plenteous years.

03:11:27.370 --> 03:11:46.070
And let them gather all the food of those good years that come, and lay up corn under the hand of Pharaoh, and let them keep food in the cities. And that food shall be for store to the land against the seven years of famine, but shall be in the land of Egypt, that the land perish not through the famine.

03:11:47.270 --> 03:12:00.230
And the thing was good in the eyes of Pharaoh, and in the eyes of all his servants. And Pharaoh said unto his servants, Can we find such a one as this is, a man in whom the Spirit of God is?

03:12:00.230 --> 03:12:17.630
And Pharaoh said unto Joseph, For as much as God hath shewed thee all this, there is none so discreet and wise as thou art. Thou shalt be over my house, and according unto thy word shall all my people be ruled. Only in the throne will I be greater than thou.

03:12:18.630 --> 03:12:43.130
And Pharaoh said unto Joseph, See, I have set thee over all the land of Egypt. And Pharaoh took off his ring from his hand, and put it upon Joseph's hand, and arrayed him in vestures of fine linen, and put a gold chain about his neck. And he made him to ride in the second chariot which he had, and they cried before him, Bow the knee, and he made him ruler over all the land of Egypt.

03:12:43.810 --> 03:12:51.870
And Pharaoh said unto Joseph, I am Pharaoh, and without thee shall no man lift up his hand or foot in all the land of Egypt.

03:12:52.650 --> 03:13:04.230
And Pharaoh called Joseph's name Zaphnath-Peyonea, and he gave him to wife, Azenith, the daughter of Potipharo, priest of Ann. And Joseph went out over all the land of Egypt.

03:13:05.310 --> 03:13:31.590
And Joseph was thirty years old when he stood before Pharaoh, king of Egypt. And Joseph went out from the presence of Pharaoh, and went throughout all the land of Egypt. And in the seven plenteous years the earth brought forth by handfuls. And he gathered up all the food of the seven years which were in the land of Egypt, and laid up the food in the cities. The food of the field which was round about every city laid he up in the same.

03:13:32.510 --> 03:13:58.490
And Joseph gathered corn as the sand of the sea very much until he left numbering, for it was without number. And unto Joseph were born two sons before the years of famine came which Azenith, the daughter of Potipharo, priest of Ann, bare unto him. And Joseph called the name of the firstborn Manasseh, for God said he hath made me forget all my toil and all my father's house.

03:13:59.870 --> 03:14:12.270
And the name of the second called he Ephraim, for God hath caused me to be fruitful in the land of my affliction. And the seven years of plenteousness that was in the land of Egypt were ended.

03:14:12.270 --> 03:14:34.810
And the seven years of Darth began to come, according as Joseph had said. And the Darth was in all lands, but in all the land of Egypt there was bread. And when all the land of Egypt was famished, the people cried to Pharaoh for bread. And Pharaoh said unto all the Egyptians, Go unto Joseph what he saith to you, do.

03:14:34.810 --> 03:14:54.690
And the famine was over all the face of the earth, and Joseph opened all the storehouses and sold unto the Egyptians, and the famine waxed sore in the land of Egypt. And all countries came into Egypt to Joseph for to buy corn, because that the famine was so sore in all lands.

03:15:33.350 --> 03:15:38.310
Now when Jacob saw that there was corn in Egypt, Jacob said unto his sons,

03:15:38.310 --> 03:15:49.810
Why do ye look one upon another? And he said, Behold, I have heard that there is corn in Egypt. Get you down thither, and buy for us from thence, that we may live and not die.

03:15:50.770 --> 03:16:02.510
And Joseph's ten brethren went down to buy corn in Egypt. But Benjamin, Joseph's brother, Jacob sent not with his brethren, for he said, Lest peradventure mischief befall him.

03:16:02.510 --> 03:16:09.370
And the sons of Israel came to buy corn among those that came, for the famine was in the land of Canaan.

03:16:10.510 --> 03:16:21.750
And Joseph was the governor of the land, and he it was that sold to all the people of the land. And Joseph's brethren came, and bowed down themselves before him with their faces to the earth.

03:16:22.690 --> 03:16:35.670
And Joseph saw his brethren, and he knew them, but made himself strange unto them, and spake roughly unto them. And he said unto them, Whence come ye? And they said, From the land of Canaan, to buy food.

03:16:35.670 --> 03:16:39.650
And Joseph knew his brethren, but they knew not him.

03:16:40.290 --> 03:16:48.650
And Joseph remembered the dreams which he dreamed of them, and said unto them, Ye are spies, to see the nakedness of the land, ye are come.

03:16:49.390 --> 03:16:59.770
And they said unto him, Nay, my lord, but to buy food are thy servants come. We are all one man's sons. We are true men, thy servants are no spies.

03:16:59.770 --> 03:17:05.350
And he said unto them, Nay, but to see the nakedness of the land, ye are come.

03:17:06.410 --> 03:17:16.790
And they said, Thy servants are twelve brethren, the sons of one man in the land of Canaan. And behold, the youngest is this day with our father, and one is not.

03:17:17.390 --> 03:17:31.050
And Joseph said unto them, That is it that I spake unto you, saying, Ye are spies. Hereby ye shall be proved. By the life of Pharaoh ye shall not go forth hence, except your youngest brother come hither.

03:17:31.950 --> 03:17:43.590
Send one of you, and let him fetch your brother, and ye shall be kept in prison, that your words may be proved, whether there be any truth in you. Or else, by the life of Pharaoh, surely ye are spies.

03:17:44.230 --> 03:17:47.490
And he put them all together into ward three days.

03:17:48.730 --> 03:18:02.610
And Joseph said unto them the third day, This do and live, for I fear God. If ye be true men, let one of your brethren be bound in the house of your prison. Go ye carry corn for the famine of your houses.

03:18:02.610 --> 03:18:08.990
But bring your youngest brother unto me, so shall your words be verified, and ye shall not die.

03:18:09.530 --> 03:18:10.730
And they did so.

03:18:11.410 --> 03:18:23.890
And they said one to another, We are verily guilty concerning our brother, in that we saw the anguish of his soul when he besought us, and we would not hear. Therefore is this distress come upon us.

03:18:24.530 --> 03:18:35.310
And Reuben answered them, saying, Spake I not unto you, saying, Do not sin against the child, and ye would not hear. Therefore, behold, also his blood is required.

03:18:36.270 --> 03:18:41.050
And they knew not that Joseph understood them, for he spake unto them by an interpreter.

03:18:42.510 --> 03:18:51.730
And he turned himself about from them, and wept, and returned to them again, and communed with them, and took from them Simeon, and bound him before their eyes.

03:18:52.610 --> 03:19:03.630
Then Joseph commanded to fill their sacks with corn, and to restore every man's money into his sack, and to give them provision for the way. And thus did he unto them.

03:19:03.630 --> 03:19:17.210
And they laded their asses with the corn, and departed thence. And as one of them opened his sack to give his ass provender in the inn, he espied his money, for behold, it was in his sack's mouth.

03:19:17.950 --> 03:19:31.110
And he said unto his brethren, My money is restored, and lo, it is even in my sack. And their heart failed them, and they were afraid, saying one to another, What is this that God hath done unto us?

03:19:31.830 --> 03:19:44.510
And they came unto Jacob their father, unto the land of Canaan, and told him all that befell unto them, saying, The man who is the lord of the land spake roughly to us, and took us for spies of the country.

03:19:45.250 --> 03:19:56.670
And we said unto him, We are true men, we are no spies. We be twelve brethren sons of our father. One is not, and the youngest is this day with our father in the land of Canaan.

03:19:56.670 --> 03:20:09.230
And the man, the lord of the country, said unto us, Hereby shall I know that ye are true men. Leave one of your brethren here with me, and take food for the famine of your households, and be gone.

03:20:09.810 --> 03:20:20.550
And bring your youngest brother unto me, then shall I know that ye are no spies, but that ye are true men. So will I deliver you your brother, and ye shall traffic in the land.

03:20:21.330 --> 03:20:32.210
And it came to pass, as they emptied their sacks, that behold, every man's bundle of money was in his sack, and when both they and their father saw the bundles of money, they were afraid.

03:20:33.070 --> 03:20:44.710
And Jacob their father said unto them, Me have ye bereaved of my children. Joseph is not, and Simeon is not, and ye will take Benjamin away. All these things are against me.

03:20:45.370 --> 03:20:54.890
And Reuben spake unto his father, saying, Slay my two sons if I bring him not to thee. Deliver him into my hand, and I will bring him to thee again.

03:20:55.830 --> 03:21:09.290
And he said, My son shall not go down with you, for his brother is dead, and he is left alone. If mischief befall him by the way in which ye go, then shall ye bring down my gray hairs with sorrow to the grave.

03:21:11.830 --> 03:21:23.570
And the famine was sore in the land, and it came to pass when they had eaten up the corn which they had brought out of Egypt, their father said unto them, Go again, buy us a little food.

03:21:24.150 --> 03:21:46.850
And Judah spake unto him, saying, The man did solemnly protest unto us, saying, He shall not see my face, except your brother be with you. If thou wilt send our brother with us, we will go down and buy thee food. But if thou wilt not send him, we will not go down, for the man said unto us, He shall not see my face, except your brother be with you.

03:21:46.850 --> 03:21:54.350
And Israel said, Wherefore dealt ye so ill with me as to tell the man whether ye had yet a brother?

03:21:55.170 --> 03:22:10.770
And they said, The man asked us straightly of our state, and of our kindred, saying, Is your father yet alive? Have ye another brother? And we told him, according to the tenor of these words, Could we certainly know that he would say, Bring your brother down?

03:22:11.390 --> 03:22:39.170
And Judah said unto Israel his father, Send the lad with me, and we will arise and go, that we may live and not die, both we and thou and also our little ones. I will be surety for him. Of my hand shalt thou require him. If I bring him not unto thee, and set him before thee, then let me bear the blame for ever. For except we had lingered, surely now we had returned this second time.

03:22:40.350 --> 03:22:55.550
And their father Israel said unto them, If it must be so now, do this. Take of the best fruits in the land in your vessels, and carry down the man a present, a little balm, and a little honey, spices and myrrh, nuts and almonds.

03:22:55.550 --> 03:23:21.230
And take double money in your hand, and the money that was brought again in the mouth of your sacks, carry it again in your hand. Peradventure, it was an oversight. Take also your brother, and arise, go again unto the man. And God Almighty give you mercy before the man, that he may send away your other brother, and Benjamin. If I be bereaved of my children, I am bereaved.

03:23:21.750 --> 03:23:42.550
And the men took that present, and they took double money in their hand, and Benjamin, and rose up, and went down to Egypt, and stood before Joseph. And when Joseph saw Benjamin with them, he said to the ruler of his house, Bring these men home, and slay, and make ready, for these men shall dine with me at noon.

03:23:43.410 --> 03:24:05.550
And the man did as Joseph bad, and the man brought the men into Joseph's house. And the men were afraid, because they were brought into Joseph's house. And they said, Because of the money that was returned in our sacks, at the first time are we brought in, that he may seek occasion against us, and fall upon us, and take us for bondmen, and our asses.

03:24:05.550 --> 03:24:28.530
And they came near to the steward of Joseph's house, and they communed with him at the door of the house, and said, O sir, we came indeed down at the first time to buy food. And it came to pass, when we came to the inn, that we opened our sacks, and behold, every man's money was in the mouth of his sack, our money in full weight, and we have brought it again in our hand.

03:24:28.530 --> 03:24:45.710
And other money we brought down in our hands to buy food, we cannot tell who put our money in our sacks. And he said, Peace be to you, fear not, your God, and the God of your Father, hath given you treasure in your sacks, I had your money.

03:24:45.710 --> 03:25:03.330
And he brought Simeon out unto them. And the man brought the men into Joseph's house, and gave them water, and they washed their feet, and he gave their asses provender. And they made ready the present against Joseph came at noon, for they heard that they should eat bread there.

03:25:04.050 --> 03:25:19.950
And when Joseph came home, they brought him the present, which was in their hand, into the house, and bowed themselves to him to the earth. And he asked them of their welfare, and said, Is your father well, the old man of whom ye spake? Is he yet alive?

03:25:19.950 --> 03:25:28.870
And they answered, Thy servant our father is in good health, he is yet alive. And they bowed down their heads, and made obeisance.

03:25:30.090 --> 03:25:42.550
And he lifted up his eyes, and saw his brother Benjamin, his mother's son, and said, Is this your younger brother, of whom ye spake unto me? And he said, God be gracious unto thee, my son.

03:25:43.270 --> 03:25:52.090
And Joseph made haste, for his bowels did yearn upon his brother, and he sought where to weep, and he entered into his chamber, and wept there.

03:25:52.810 --> 03:25:58.630
And he washed his face, and went out, and refrained himself, and said, Set on bread.

03:25:59.710 --> 03:26:13.850
And they set on for him by himself, and for them by themselves, and for the Egyptians, which did eat with him by themselves, because the Egyptians might not eat bread with the Hebrews, for that is an abomination unto the Egyptians.

03:26:14.890 --> 03:26:23.410
And they sat before him, the firstborn according to his birthright, and the youngest according to his youth, and the men marvelled one at another.

03:26:24.310 --> 03:26:34.670
And he took and sent messes unto them from before him, but Benjamin's mess was five times so much as any of theirs, and they drank, and were merry with him.

03:26:37.190 --> 03:26:47.510
And he commanded the steward of his house, saying, Fill the men's sacks with food as much as they can carry, and put every man's money in his sack's mouth.

03:26:48.330 --> 03:26:56.750
And put my cup, the silver cup, in the sack's mouth of the youngest, and his corn money. And he did according to the word that Joseph had spoken.

03:26:57.770 --> 03:27:02.710
As soon as the morning was light, the men were sent away, they and their asses.

03:27:03.450 --> 03:27:16.070
And when they were gone out of the city, and not yet far off, Joseph said unto his steward, Up, follow after the men, and when thou dost overtake them, say unto them, Wherefore have ye rewarded evil for good?

03:27:16.070 --> 03:27:23.490
Is not this it, in which my lord drinketh, and whereby indeed he divineth, he have done evil in so doing?

03:27:24.370 --> 03:27:27.930
And he overtook them, and he spake unto them these same words.

03:27:27.930 --> 03:27:45.950
And they said unto him, Wherefore saith my lord these words, God forbid that thy servants should do according to this thing. Behold the money which we found in our sack's mouths we brought again unto thee out of the land of Canaan. How then should we steal out of thy lord's house silver or gold?

03:27:46.610 --> 03:27:53.590
With whomsoever of thy servants it be found, both let him die, and we also will be my lord's bondman.

03:27:54.290 --> 03:28:02.530
And he said, Now also let it be according unto your words, he with whom it is found shall be my servant, and ye shall be blameless.

03:28:03.410 --> 03:28:08.890
Then they speedily took down every man his sack to the ground, and opened every man his sack.

03:28:09.530 --> 03:28:16.510
And he searched, and began at the eldest, and left at the youngest, and the cup was found in Benjamin's sack.

03:28:17.450 --> 03:28:22.330
Then they rent their clothes, and laid at every man his ass, and returned to the city.

03:28:23.770 --> 03:28:29.990
And Judah and his brethren came to Joseph's house, for he was yet there, and they fell before him on the ground.

03:28:30.510 --> 03:28:38.350
And Joseph said unto them, What deed is this that ye have done? What ye not, that such a man as I can certainly divine?

03:28:39.230 --> 03:28:45.670
And Judah said, What shall we say unto my lord? What shall we speak, or how shall we clear ourselves?

03:28:46.310 --> 03:28:54.950
God hath found out the iniquity of thy servants. Behold, we are my lord's servants, both we and he also with whom the cup is found.

03:28:55.690 --> 03:29:06.890
And he said, God forbid that I should do so, but the man in whose hand the cup is found, he shall be my servant, and ask for you, get you up in peace unto your father.

03:29:07.930 --> 03:29:20.450
Then Judah came near unto him, and said, O my lord, let thy servant, I pray thee, speak a word in my lord's ears, and let not thy anger burn against thy servant, for thou art even his Pharaoh.

03:29:21.310 --> 03:29:37.650
My lord asked his servants, saying, Have ye a father or a brother? And we said unto my lord, We have a father, an old man, and a child of his old age, a little one, and his brother is dead, and he alone is left of his mother, and his father loveth him.

03:29:38.310 --> 03:29:50.690
And thou saidst unto thy servants, Bring him down unto me, that I may set mine eyes upon him. And we said unto my lord, The lad cannot leave his father, for if he should leave his father, his father would die.

03:29:51.430 --> 03:29:57.730
And thou saidst unto thy servants, Except your youngest brother, come down with you, ye shall see my face no more.

03:29:57.730 --> 03:30:18.990
And it came to pass, when we came up unto thy servant, my father, we told him the words of my lord. And our father said, Go again, and buy us a little food. And we said, We cannot go down, if our youngest brother be with us, then will we go down, for we may not see the man's face, except our youngest brother be with us.

03:30:18.990 --> 03:30:39.050
And thy servant, my father, said unto us, Ye know that my wife bear me two sons, and the one went out from me, and I said, Surely he is torn in pieces, and I saw him not since. And if ye take this also from me, and mischief befall him, ye shall bring down my gray hairs with sorrow to the grave.

03:30:39.830 --> 03:30:59.690
Now therefore, when I come to thy servant, my father, and the lad be not with us, seeing that his life is bound up in the lad's life, it shall come to pass, when he seeth that the lad is not with us, that he will die, and thy servants shall bring down the gray hairs of thy servant our father with sorrow to the grave.

03:31:00.690 --> 03:31:28.190
For thy servant became surety for the lad unto my father, saying, If I bring him not unto thee, then I shall bear the blame to my father forever. Now therefore, I pray thee, let thy servant bide instead of the lad a bondman to my lord, and let the lad go up with his brethren. For how shall I go up to my father, and the lad be not with me, lest peradventure I see the evil that shall come on my father?

03:31:31.690 --> 03:31:49.230
Then Joseph could not refrain himself before all them that stood by him, and he cried, Cause every man to go out from me. And there stood no man with him while Joseph made himself known unto his brethren. And he wept aloud, and the Egyptians in the house of Pharaoh heard.

03:31:49.230 --> 03:32:00.070
And Joseph said unto his brethren, I am Joseph, doth my father yet live? And his brethren could not answer him, for they were troubled at his presence.

03:32:00.930 --> 03:32:20.570
And Joseph said unto his brethren, Come near to me, I pray you. And they came near. And he said, I am Joseph, your brother, whom ye sold into Egypt. Now therefore be not grieved nor angry with yourselves that ye sold me hither, for God did send me before you to preserve life.

03:32:21.250 --> 03:32:37.910
For these two years hath the famine been in the land, and yet there are five years in the which there shall neither be earring nor harvest. And God sent me before you to preserve you a posterity in the earth, and to save your lives by a great deliverance.

03:32:37.910 --> 03:32:49.370
So now it was not you that sent me hither, but God. And he hath made me a father to Pharaoh, and lord of all his house, and a ruler throughout all the land of Egypt.

03:32:50.030 --> 03:33:01.490
Haste ye, and go up to my father, and say unto him, Thus saith thy son Joseph, God hath made me lord of all Egypt, come down unto me, tarry not.

03:33:01.490 --> 03:33:22.730
And thou shalt dwell in the land of Goshen, and thou shalt be near unto me, thou and thy children, and thy children's children, and thy flocks, and thy herds, and all that thou hast. And there will I nourish thee, for yet there are five years of famine, lest thou and thy household, and all that thou hast, come to poverty.

03:33:23.590 --> 03:33:39.370
And behold, your eyes see, and the eyes of my brother Benjamin, that it is my mouth that speaketh unto you. And ye shall tell my father of all my glory in Egypt, and of all that ye have seen, and ye shall haste and bring down my father hither.

03:33:39.370 --> 03:33:52.890
And he fell upon his brother Benjamin's neck, and wept, and Benjamin wept upon his neck. Moreover he kissed all his brethren, and wept upon them, and after that his brethren talked with him.

03:33:53.730 --> 03:34:02.210
And the fame thereof was heard in Pharaoh's house, saying, Joseph's brethren are come. And it pleased Pharaoh well, and his servants.

03:34:03.290 --> 03:34:20.570
And Pharaoh said unto Joseph, Say unto thy brethren, This do ye, lay your beasts, and go, get you into the land of Canaan, and take your father and your households, and come unto me, and I will give you the good of the land of Egypt, and ye shall eat the fat of the land.

03:34:21.350 --> 03:34:36.910
Now thou art commanded, This do ye, take you wagons out of the land of Egypt for your little ones, and for your wives, and bring your father, and come. Also regard not your stuff, for the good of all the land of Egypt is yours.

03:34:37.610 --> 03:34:54.930
And the children of Israel did so, and Joseph gave them wagons according to the commandment of Pharaoh, and gave them provision for the way. To all of them he gave each man changes of raiment, but to Benjamin he gave three hundred pieces of silver, and five changes of raiment.

03:34:55.710 --> 03:35:07.710
And to his father he sent after this manner, ten asses laden with the good things of Egypt, and ten she-asses laden with corn and bread and meat for his father by the way.

03:35:08.710 --> 03:35:15.650
So he sent his brethren away, and they departed, and he said unto them, See that ye fall not out by the way.

03:35:16.430 --> 03:35:32.070
And they went up out of Egypt, and came into the land of Canaan unto Jacob their father, and told him, saying, Joseph is yet alive, and he is governor over all the land of Egypt. And Jacob's heart fainted, for he believed them not.

03:35:32.070 --> 03:35:51.750
And they told him all the words of Joseph which he had said unto them, and when he saw the wagons which Joseph had sent to carry him, the spirit of Jacob their father revived. And Israel said, It is enough, Joseph my son is yet alive, I will go and see him before I die.

03:36:02.110 --> 03:36:05.550
www.logoslibrary.org

03:36:38.610 --> 03:36:43.830
And Israel took his journey with all that he had, and came to Beersheba, and offered

03:36:43.830 --> 03:36:46.930
sacrifices unto the God of his father, Isaac.

03:36:47.990 --> 03:36:53.530
And God spake unto Israel in the visions of the night, and said, Jacob, Jacob.

03:36:53.910 --> 03:36:55.870
And he said, Here am I.

03:36:56.290 --> 03:36:59.650
And he said, I am God, the God of thy father.

03:37:00.050 --> 03:37:04.830
Fear not to go down into Egypt, for I will there make of thee a great nation.

03:37:05.190 --> 03:37:10.870
I will go down with thee into Egypt, and I will also surely bring thee up again, and

03:37:10.870 --> 03:37:13.650
Joseph shall put his hand upon thine eyes.

03:37:14.590 --> 03:37:19.830
And Jacob rose up from Beersheba, and the sons of Israel carried Jacob their father,

03:37:20.070 --> 03:37:24.890
and their little ones, and their wives, in the wagons which Pharaoh had sent to carry

03:37:24.890 --> 03:37:25.350
him.

03:37:26.210 --> 03:37:30.790
And they took their cattle, and their goods, which they had gotten in the land of Canaan,

03:37:31.070 --> 03:37:37.310
and came into Egypt, Jacob and all his seed with him, his sons and his sons' sons with

03:37:37.310 --> 03:37:42.770
him, his daughters and his sons' daughters, and all his seed brought he with him into

03:37:42.770 --> 03:37:43.330
Egypt.

03:37:44.510 --> 03:37:49.650
And these are the names of the children of Israel which came into Egypt, Jacob and his

03:37:49.650 --> 03:37:56.990
sons, Reuben, Jacob's first born, and the sons of Reuben, Hainach and Falu and Hezren

03:37:56.990 --> 03:38:05.750
and Carmi, and the sons of Simeon, Jemuel and Jamin and Ohad and Jakin and Zohar and

03:38:08.690 --> 03:38:17.150
and the sons of Levi, Gershon, Kohath and Marari, and the sons of Judah, Ur and Onan

03:38:17.150 --> 03:38:24.630
and Shelah and Phares and Zirah, but Ur and Onan died in the land of Canaan, and the sons

03:38:24.630 --> 03:38:33.270
of Phares were Hezren and Hamel, and the sons of Issachar, Tola and Fuva and Job and Shimron,

03:38:33.880 --> 03:38:41.010
and the sons of Zebulon, Seiread and Elan and Jahlil. These be the sons of Leah which

03:38:41.010 --> 03:38:46.850
she bear unto Jacob and Paedon Aram with his daughter Dinah, all the souls of his sons

03:38:46.850 --> 03:38:49.330
and his daughters were thirty and three.

03:38:50.810 --> 03:39:02.850
And the sons of Gad, Ziphion and Haggai, Shunai and Esben, Eri and Erodai and Erili, and the

03:39:05.570 --> 03:39:16.890
sons of Biraeah, Heber and Malkiel. These are the sons of Zilpah whom Laban gave to

03:39:16.890 --> 03:39:24.430
Leah his daughter and these she bear unto Jacob even sixteen souls. The sons of Rachel

03:39:24.430 --> 03:39:31.490
Jacob's wife, Joseph and Benjamin, and unto Joseph in the land of Egypt were born Manasseh

03:39:31.490 --> 03:39:38.370
and Ephraim which Azaneth the daughter of Potipharah, priest of An, bear unto him. And

03:39:38.370 --> 03:39:47.210
the sons of Benjamin were Bela and Beker and Ashbel, Gira and Naaman, Ehai and Rosh, Muppim

03:39:47.210 --> 03:39:53.810
and Huppim and Ard. These are the sons of Rachel which were born to Jacob, all the souls

03:39:53.810 --> 03:39:54.690
were fourteen.

03:39:55.630 --> 03:40:04.110
And the sons of Dan, Hushim, and the sons of Naphtali, Jaziel and Gunai and Jezer and

03:40:04.110 --> 03:40:10.150
Shilam. These are the sons of Bilhah which Laban gave unto Rachel his daughter and she

03:40:10.150 --> 03:40:16.610
bear these unto Jacob. All the souls were seven. All the souls that came with Jacob

03:40:16.610 --> 03:40:23.230
into Egypt which came out of his loins besides Jacob's son's wives, all the souls were threescore

03:40:23.230 --> 03:40:29.730
and six. And the sons of Joseph which were born him in Egypt were two souls. All the

03:40:29.730 --> 03:40:36.550
souls of the house of Jacob which came into Egypt were threescore and ten. And he sent

03:40:36.550 --> 03:40:42.210
Judah before him unto Joseph to direct his face unto Goshen and they came into the land

03:40:42.210 --> 03:40:49.090
of Goshen. And Joseph made ready his chariot and went up to meet Israel his father to Goshen

03:40:49.090 --> 03:40:55.550
and presented himself unto him and he fell on his neck and wept on his neck a good while.

03:40:56.950 --> 03:41:03.290
And Israel said unto Joseph, Now let me die since I have seen thy face because thou art

03:41:03.290 --> 03:41:10.110
yet alive. And Joseph said unto his brethren and unto his father's house, I will go up

03:41:10.110 --> 03:41:15.670
and show Pharaoh and say unto him, My brethren and my father's house which were in the land

03:41:15.670 --> 03:41:20.990
of Canaan are come unto me. And the men are shepherds for their trade hath been to feed

03:41:20.990 --> 03:41:26.590
cattle and they have brought their flocks and their herds and all that they have. And

03:41:26.590 --> 03:41:31.890
it shall come to pass when Pharaoh shall call you and shall say, What is your occupation?

03:41:32.330 --> 03:41:37.530
That ye shall say, Thy servant's trade hath been about cattle from our youth even until

03:41:37.530 --> 03:41:43.950
now, both we and also our fathers. That ye may dwell in the land of Goshen for every

03:41:43.950 --> 03:41:46.790
shepherd is an abomination unto the Egyptians.

03:41:48.730 --> 03:41:56.030
Then Joseph came and told Pharaoh and said, My father and my brethren and their

03:41:56.030 --> 03:42:01.850
flocks and their herds and all that they have are come out of the land of Canaan and behold

03:42:01.850 --> 03:42:08.330
they are in the land of Goshen. And he took some of his brethren, even five men, and presented

03:42:08.330 --> 03:42:14.570
them unto Pharaoh. And Pharaoh said unto his brethren, What is your occupation? And

03:42:14.570 --> 03:42:22.390
they said unto Pharaoh, Thy servants are shepherds, both we and also our fathers. They said moreover

03:42:22.390 --> 03:42:28.470
unto Pharaoh, For to sojourn in the land are we come, for thy servants have no pasture

03:42:28.470 --> 03:42:34.450
for their flocks, for the famine is sore in the land of Canaan. Now therefore we pray

03:42:34.450 --> 03:42:37.850
thee, let thy servants dwell in the land of Goshen.

03:42:38.790 --> 03:42:44.590
And Pharaoh spake unto Joseph, saying, Thy father and thy brethren are come unto thee,

03:42:44.930 --> 03:42:50.510
the land of Egypt is before thee, in the best of the land make thy father and brethren to

03:42:50.510 --> 03:42:56.370
dwell, in the land of Goshen let them dwell, and if thou knowest any men of activity among

03:42:56.370 --> 03:42:59.030
them, then make them rulers over my cattle.

03:43:00.030 --> 03:43:05.750
And Joseph brought in Jacob his father, and set him before Pharaoh, and Jacob blessed

03:43:05.750 --> 03:43:10.470
Pharaoh. And Pharaoh said unto Jacob, How old art thou?

03:43:11.410 --> 03:43:16.950
And Jacob said unto Pharaoh, The days of the years of my pilgrimage are an hundred and

03:43:16.950 --> 03:43:23.050
thirty years. Few and evil have the days of the years of my life been, and have not attained

03:43:23.050 --> 03:43:28.050
unto the days of the years of the life of my fathers in the days of their pilgrimage.

03:43:29.390 --> 03:43:33.230
And Jacob blessed Pharaoh, and went out from before Pharaoh.

03:43:34.870 --> 03:43:39.610
And Joseph placed his father and his brethren, and gave them a possession in the land of

03:43:39.610 --> 03:43:45.390
Egypt, in the best of the land, in the land of Ramesses, as Pharaoh had commanded.

03:43:46.410 --> 03:43:51.910
And Joseph nourished his father and his brethren, and all his father's household with bread,

03:43:51.910 --> 03:43:57.330
according to their families. And there was no bread in all the land, for

03:43:57.330 --> 03:44:02.410
the famine was very sore, so that the land of Egypt and all the land of Canaan fainted

03:44:02.410 --> 03:44:08.010
by reason of the famine. And Joseph gathered up all the money that was found in the land

03:44:08.010 --> 03:44:13.350
of Egypt and in the land of Canaan, for the corn which they bought, and Joseph brought

03:44:13.350 --> 03:44:19.650
the money into Pharaoh's house. And when money failed in the land of Egypt and in the land

03:44:19.650 --> 03:44:25.910
of Canaan, all the Egyptians came unto Joseph, and said, Give us bread, for why should we

03:44:25.910 --> 03:44:32.850
die in thy presence? for the money faileth. And Joseph said, Give your cattle, and I will

03:44:32.850 --> 03:44:38.750
give you for your cattle, if money fail. And they brought their cattle unto Joseph, and

03:44:38.750 --> 03:44:43.810
Joseph gave them bread in exchange for horses, and for the flocks, and for the cattle of

03:44:43.810 --> 03:44:49.430
the herds, and for the asses, and he fed them with bread for all their cattle for that year.

03:44:50.730 --> 03:44:56.210
When that year was ended, they came unto him the second year, and said unto him, We will

03:44:56.210 --> 03:45:02.290
not hide it from my Lord, how that our money is spent. My Lord also hath our herds of cattle.

03:45:02.830 --> 03:45:09.010
There is not aught left in the sight of my Lord, but our bodies and our lands. Wherefore

03:45:09.010 --> 03:45:15.670
shall we die before thine eyes, both we and our land? Buy us and our land for bread, and

03:45:15.670 --> 03:45:21.770
we and our land will be servants unto Pharaoh. And give us seed that we may live and not

03:45:21.770 --> 03:45:28.310
die, that the land be not desolate. And Joseph bought all the land of Egypt for Pharaoh,

03:45:28.730 --> 03:45:34.430
for the Egyptians sold every man his field because the famine prevailed over them, so

03:45:34.430 --> 03:45:40.670
the land became Pharaoh's. And as for the people, he removed them to cities from one

03:45:40.670 --> 03:45:46.790
end of the borders of Egypt even to the other end thereof. Only the land of the priests

03:45:46.790 --> 03:45:52.390
bought he not, for the priests had a portion assigned them of Pharaoh, and did eat their

03:45:52.390 --> 03:45:59.270
portion which Pharaoh gave them, wherefore they sold not their lands. Then Joseph said

03:45:59.270 --> 03:46:05.650
unto the people, Behold, I have bought you this day and your land for Pharaoh. Lo, here

03:46:05.650 --> 03:46:11.110
is seed for you, and ye shall sow the land. And it shall come to pass in the increase

03:46:11.110 --> 03:46:17.290
that ye shall give the fifth part unto Pharaoh, and four parts shall be your own, for seed

03:46:17.290 --> 03:46:22.730
of the field, and for your food, and for them of your households, and for food for your

03:46:22.730 --> 03:46:29.030
little ones. And they said, Thou hast saved our lives. Let us find grace in the sight

03:46:29.030 --> 03:46:35.890
of my Lord, and we will be Pharaoh's servants. And Joseph made it a law over the land of

03:46:35.890 --> 03:46:41.450
Egypt unto this day that Pharaoh should have the fifth part, except the land of the priests

03:46:41.450 --> 03:46:48.650
only, which became not Pharaoh's. And Israel dwelt in the land of Egypt in the country

03:46:48.650 --> 03:46:55.810
of Goshen, and they had possessions therein, and grew and multiplied exceedingly. And Jacob

03:46:55.810 --> 03:47:01.830
lived in the land of Egypt seventeen years, so the whole age of Jacob was an hundred forty

03:47:01.830 --> 03:47:08.810
and seven years. And the time drew nigh that Israel must die, and he called his son Joseph,

03:47:08.950 --> 03:47:14.990
and said unto him, If now I have found grace in thy sight, put, I pray thee, thy hand under

03:47:14.990 --> 03:47:21.990
my thigh, and deal kindly and truly with me. Bury me not, I pray thee, in Egypt. But I

03:47:21.990 --> 03:47:27.810
will lie with my fathers, and thou shalt carry me out of Egypt, and bury me in their burying

03:47:27.810 --> 03:47:35.070
place. And he said, I will do as thou hast said. And he said, Swear unto me. And he

03:47:35.070 --> 03:47:39.610
swear unto him. And Israel bowed himself upon the bed's head.

03:47:42.050 --> 03:47:46.650
And it came to pass after these things that

03:47:46.650 --> 03:47:53.530
one told Joseph, Behold, thy father is sick. And he took with him his two sons Manasseh

03:47:53.530 --> 03:48:00.630
and Ephraim. And one told Jacob, and said, Behold, thy son Joseph cometh unto thee. And

03:48:00.630 --> 03:48:03.490
Israel strengthened himself and sat upon the bed.

03:48:04.870 --> 03:48:11.570
And Jacob said unto Joseph, God Almighty appeared unto me at Luz in the land of Canaan, and

03:48:11.570 --> 03:48:17.570
blessed me, and said unto me, Behold, I will make thee fruitful and multiply thee, and

03:48:17.570 --> 03:48:22.650
I will make of thee a multitude of people, and will give this land to thy seed after

03:48:22.650 --> 03:48:29.470
thee for an everlasting possession. And now thy two sons Ephraim and Manasseh,

03:48:29.470 --> 03:48:35.110
which were born unto thee in the land of Egypt before I came unto thee into Egypt, are mine.

03:48:35.590 --> 03:48:41.750
As Reuben and Simeon they shall be mine. And thy issue, which thou begettest after them,

03:48:42.010 --> 03:48:46.730
shall be thine, and shall be called after the name of their brethren and their inheritance.

03:48:47.910 --> 03:48:54.050
And as for me, when I came from Paden, Rachel died by me in the land of Canaan in the way,

03:48:54.390 --> 03:48:59.770
when yet there was but a little way to come unto Ephrath, and I buried her there in the

03:48:59.770 --> 03:49:06.810
way of Ephrath, the same as Bethlehem. And Israel beheld Joseph's sons, and said,

03:49:06.930 --> 03:49:13.390
Who were these? And Joseph said unto his father, They are my sons, whom God hath given me in

03:49:13.390 --> 03:49:19.190
this place. And he said, Bring them, I pray thee, unto me, and I will bless them.

03:49:20.210 --> 03:49:25.750
Now the eyes of Israel were dim for age, so that he could not see, and he brought them

03:49:25.750 --> 03:49:32.810
near unto him, and he kissed them, and embraced them. And Israel said unto Joseph, I had not

03:49:32.810 --> 03:49:39.970
thought to see thy face, and lo, God hath showed me also thy seed. And Joseph brought

03:49:39.970 --> 03:49:46.690
them out from between his knees, and he bowed himself with his face to the earth. And Joseph

03:49:46.690 --> 03:49:52.430
took them both, Ephraim in his right hand toward Israel's left hand, and Manasseh in

03:49:52.430 --> 03:49:58.490
his left hand toward Israel's right hand, and brought them near unto him. And Israel

03:49:58.490 --> 03:50:03.010
stretched out his right hand, and laid it upon Ephraim's head, who was the younger,

03:50:03.370 --> 03:50:09.250
and his left hand upon Manasseh's head, guiding his hands wittingly, for Manasseh was the

03:50:09.250 --> 03:50:16.690
first born. And he blessed Joseph, and said, God, before whom my fathers Abraham and Isaac

03:50:16.690 --> 03:50:23.310
did walk, the God which fed me all my life long, unto this day, the angel which redeemed

03:50:23.310 --> 03:50:29.270
me from all evil, bless the lads, and let my name be named on them, and the name of

03:50:29.270 --> 03:50:35.110
my fathers Abraham and Isaac, and let them grow into a multitude in the midst of the

03:50:35.110 --> 03:50:41.150
earth. And when Joseph saw that his father laid his right hand upon the head of Ephraim,

03:50:41.150 --> 03:50:47.490
it displeased him, and he held up his father's hand to remove it from Ephraim's head unto

03:50:47.490 --> 03:50:54.250
Manasseh's head. And Joseph said unto his father, Not so, my father, for this is the

03:50:54.250 --> 03:51:01.250
first born, put thy right hand upon his head. And his father refused, and said, I know it,

03:51:01.250 --> 03:51:08.330
my son, I know it. He also shall become a people, and he also shall be great. But truly

03:51:08.330 --> 03:51:13.390
his younger brother shall be greater than he, and his seed shall become a multitude

03:51:13.390 --> 03:51:20.610
of nations. And he blessed them that day, saying, In thee shall Israel bless, saying,

03:51:20.850 --> 03:51:28.690
God make thee as Ephraim and as Manasseh, and he set Ephraim before Manasseh. And Israel

03:51:28.690 --> 03:51:35.630
said unto Joseph, Behold, I die, but God shall be with you and bring you again unto the land

03:51:35.630 --> 03:51:42.010
of your fathers. Moreover, I have given to thee one portion above thy brethren, which

03:51:42.010 --> 03:51:46.530
I took out of the hand of the Amorite, with my sword and with my bow.

03:51:48.450 --> 03:51:54.030
And Jacob called unto his sons, and said, Gather

03:51:54.030 --> 03:52:00.350
yourselves together, that I may tell you that which shall befall you in the last days. Gather

03:52:00.350 --> 03:52:06.130
yourselves together, and hear, ye sons of Jacob, and hearken unto Israel, your father.

03:52:07.590 --> 03:52:13.470
Reuben, thou art my first born, my might, and the beginning of my strength, the excellency

03:52:13.470 --> 03:52:21.470
of dignity, and the excellency of power. Unstable as water, thou shalt not excel, because thou

03:52:21.470 --> 03:52:27.450
wentest up to thy father's bed, then defiledst thou it. He went up to my couch.

03:52:29.190 --> 03:52:35.950
Simeon and Levi are brethren, instruments of cruelty are in their habitations. O my

03:52:35.950 --> 03:52:41.990
soul, come not thou into their secret, unto their assembly, mine honor, be not thou united,

03:52:42.570 --> 03:52:49.030
for in their anger they slew a man, and in their self-will they digged down a wall. Cursed

03:52:49.030 --> 03:52:54.750
be their anger, for it was fierce, and their wrath, for it was cruel, I will divide them

03:52:54.750 --> 03:52:57.410
in Jacob, and scatter them in Israel.

03:52:59.410 --> 03:53:04.810
Judah, thou art he whom thy brethren shall praise, thy hand shall be in the neck of

03:53:04.810 --> 03:53:11.750
thine enemies, thy father's children shall bow down before thee. Judah is a lion's whelp.

03:53:12.130 --> 03:53:18.510
From the prey, my son, thou art gone up. He stooped down, he couched as a lion, and as

03:53:18.510 --> 03:53:25.710
an old lion, who shall rouse him up? The scepter shall not depart from Judah, nor a law-giver

03:53:25.710 --> 03:53:31.630
from between his feet, until Shiloh come, and unto him shall the gathering of the people

03:53:31.630 --> 03:53:38.790
be. Binding his foal unto the vine, and his asses colt unto the choice-vine, he washed

03:53:38.790 --> 03:53:45.090
his garments in wine, and his clothes in the blood of grapes. His eyes shall be red with

03:53:45.090 --> 03:53:53.150
wine, and his teeth white with milk. Zebulon shall dwell at the haven of the sea, and he

03:53:53.150 --> 03:54:00.630
shall be for an haven of ships, and his border shall be unto Zidon. Issachar is a strong

03:54:00.630 --> 03:54:07.070
ass couching down between two burdens, and he saw that rest was good, and the land that

03:54:07.070 --> 03:54:14.450
it was pleasant, and bowed his shoulder to bear, and became a servant unto tribute. Dan

03:54:14.450 --> 03:54:20.730
shall judge his people as one of the tribes of Israel. Dan shall be a serpent by the way,

03:54:20.950 --> 03:54:28.250
an adder in the path, that biteth the horse-heels, so that his rider shall fall backward. I have

03:54:28.250 --> 03:54:35.830
waited for thy salvation, O Lord. Gad, a troop shall overcome him, but he shall overcome

03:54:35.830 --> 03:54:43.290
at the last. Out of Asher his bread shall be fat, and he shall yield royal deities.

03:54:44.650 --> 03:54:53.170
Naphtali is a hind let loose, he giveth goodly words. Joseph is a fruitful bow, even a fruitful

03:54:53.170 --> 03:54:59.410
bow by a well, whose branches run over the wall. The archers have sorely grieved him,

03:54:59.590 --> 03:55:05.750
and shot at him, and hated him. But his bow abode in strength, and the arms of his hands

03:55:05.750 --> 03:55:11.110
were made strong by the hands of the mighty God of Jacob. From thence is the shepherd

03:55:11.110 --> 03:55:17.910
the stone of Israel. Even by the God of thy father, who shall help thee, and by the Almighty,

03:55:18.170 --> 03:55:23.350
who shall bless thee with blessings of heaven above, blessings of the deep that lieth under,

03:55:23.730 --> 03:55:29.150
blessings of the breasts, and of the womb. The blessings of thy father have prevailed

03:55:29.150 --> 03:55:34.690
above the blessings of my progenitors, unto the utmost bound of the everlasting hills.

03:55:35.210 --> 03:55:40.270
They shall be on the head of Joseph, and on the crown of the head of him that was separate

03:55:40.270 --> 03:55:47.590
from his brethren. Benjamin shall raven as a wolf. In the morning he shall devour the

03:55:47.590 --> 03:55:55.330
prey, and at night he shall divide the spoil. All these are the twelve tribes of Israel,

03:55:55.670 --> 03:56:00.510
and this is it that their fathers spake unto them, and blessed them. Everyone according

03:56:00.510 --> 03:56:06.750
to his blessing, he blessed them. And he charged them, and said unto them, I am to be gathered

03:56:06.750 --> 03:56:12.550
unto my people. Bury me with my fathers in the cave that is in the field of Ephron the

03:56:12.550 --> 03:56:18.470
Hittite, in the cave that is in the field of Machpelah, which is before Mamre, and the

03:56:18.470 --> 03:56:24.230
land of Canaan, which Abraham bought with the field of Ephron the Hittite, for a possession

03:56:24.230 --> 03:56:31.530
of a burying place. There they buried Abraham, and Sarah his wife. There they buried Isaac

03:56:31.530 --> 03:56:38.290
and Rebekah his wife, and there I buried Leah. The purchase of the field, and of the cave

03:56:38.290 --> 03:56:44.830
that is therein, was from the children of Heth. And when Jacob had made an end of commanding

03:56:44.830 --> 03:56:50.890
his sons, he gathered up his feet into the bed, and yielded up the ghost, and was gathered

03:56:50.890 --> 03:56:52.110
unto his people.

03:56:54.290 --> 03:56:58.830
And Joseph fell upon his father's face, and

03:56:58.830 --> 03:57:04.750
stepped upon him, and kissed him. And Joseph commanded his servants, the physicians, to

03:57:04.750 --> 03:57:11.490
embalm his father, and the physicians embalmed Israel. And forty days were fulfilled for

03:57:11.490 --> 03:57:17.050
him, for so are fulfilled the days of those which are embalmed, and the Egyptians mourned

03:57:17.050 --> 03:57:23.670
for him three score and ten days. And when the days of his mourning were past, Joseph

03:57:23.670 --> 03:57:29.630
spake unto the house of Pharaoh, saying, If now I have found grace in your eyes, speak,

03:57:29.810 --> 03:57:37.290
I pray you, in the ears of Pharaoh, saying, My father made me swear, saying, Lo, I die,

03:57:37.690 --> 03:57:42.450
in my grave which I have digged for me, in the land of Canaan, there shalt thou bury

03:57:42.450 --> 03:57:49.450
me. Now therefore let me go up, I pray thee, and bury my father, and I will come again.

03:57:49.990 --> 03:57:55.890
And Pharaoh said, Go up, and bury thy father, according as he made thee swear.

03:57:57.250 --> 03:58:02.630
And Joseph went up to bury his father, and with him went up all the servants of Pharaoh,

03:58:03.070 --> 03:58:08.330
the elders of his house, and all the elders of the land of Egypt, and all the house of

03:58:08.330 --> 03:58:14.010
Joseph, and his brethren, and his father's house. Only their little ones, and their flocks,

03:58:14.010 --> 03:58:20.310
and their herds, they left in the land of Goshen. And there went up with him both chariots

03:58:20.310 --> 03:58:26.770
and horsemen, and it was a very great company. And they came to the threshing floor of Atad,

03:58:27.030 --> 03:58:32.850
which is beyond Jordan, and there they mourned with a great and very sore lamentation, and

03:58:32.850 --> 03:58:43.990
he made a mourning for his father seven days. And when the inhabitants of the land, the

03:58:43.990 --> 03:58:50.530
grievous mourning to the Egyptians, wherefore the name of it was called Abel-Misraim, which

03:58:50.530 --> 03:58:57.410
is beyond Jordan. And his sons did unto him according as he commanded them, for his sons

03:58:57.410 --> 03:59:03.070
carried him into the land of Canaan, and buried him in the cave of the field of Machpelah,

03:59:03.330 --> 03:59:08.310
which Abraham bought with the field for a possession of a burying-place of Ephra on

03:59:08.310 --> 03:59:15.890
the Hittite, before Mamre. And Joseph returned into Egypt, he and his brethren, and all that

03:59:15.890 --> 03:59:22.590
went up with him, to bury his father, after he had buried his father. And when Joseph's

03:59:22.590 --> 03:59:28.730
brethren saw that their father was dead, they said, Joseph will peradventure hate us, and

03:59:28.730 --> 03:59:34.630
will certainly requite us all the evil which we did unto him. And they sent a messenger

03:59:34.630 --> 03:59:41.190
unto Joseph, saying, Thy father did command before he died, saying, So shall ye say unto

03:59:41.470 --> 03:59:47.430
Joseph, Forgive, I pray thee now, the trespass of thy brethren and their sin, for they did

03:59:47.430 --> 03:59:53.150
unto thee evil, and now we pray thee, forgive the trespass of the servants of the God of

03:59:53.150 --> 04:00:00.170
thy father. And Joseph wept when they spake unto him. And his brethren also went and fell

04:00:00.170 --> 04:00:07.650
down before his face, and they said, Behold, we be thy servants. And Joseph said unto them,

04:00:07.930 --> 04:00:15.670
Fear not, for am I in the place of God. But as for you ye thought evil against me, but

04:00:15.670 --> 04:00:22.570
God meant it unto good, to bring to pass, as it is this day, to save much people alive.

04:00:23.170 --> 04:00:29.950
Now therefore fear ye not, I will nourish you and your little ones. And he comforted

04:00:29.950 --> 04:00:37.150
them and spake kindly unto them. And Joseph dwelt in Egypt, he and his father's house.

04:00:37.690 --> 04:00:43.810
And Joseph lived and a hundred and ten years. And Joseph saw Ephraim's children of the third

04:00:43.810 --> 04:00:50.010
generation. The children also of Maker, the son of Manasseh, were brought up upon Joseph's

04:00:50.010 --> 04:00:57.570
knees. And Joseph said unto his brethren, I die, and God will surely visit you and bring

04:00:57.570 --> 04:01:03.450
you out of this land, unto the land which he sware to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob.

04:01:04.270 --> 04:01:09.790
And Joseph took an oath of the children of Israel, saying, God will surely visit you,

04:01:09.930 --> 04:01:16.730
and he shall carry up my bones from hence. So Joseph died, being a hundred and ten years

04:01:16.730 --> 04:01:21.570
old, and they embalmed him, and he was put in a coffin in Egypt.
